window.PEDIA_CONTENT = {"budaya_alat_musik_angklung_1":{"id":"budaya_alat_musik_angklung_1","title_id":"Angklung","title_en":"Angklung","subtitle_id":"Alat musik bambu Sunda yang dimainkan dengan digoyang","subtitle_en":"The Sundanese bamboo instrument you play by shaking","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Jawa Barat (Sunda)","value_en":"West Java (Sundanese)"},{"icon":"park","label_id":"Bahan","label_en":"Material","value_id":"Bambu","value_en":"Bamboo"},{"icon":"music_note","label_id":"Cara main","label_en":"How to play","value_id":"Digoyang-goyang","value_en":"Shaken"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Dimainkan","label_en":"Played","value_id":"Bersama-sama","value_en":"Together as a team"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"music_note","h_id":"Apa Itu Angklung?","h_en":"What Is Angklung?","body_id":"Angklung adalah alat musik tradisional dari masyarakat Sunda di Jawa Barat. Alat musik ini dibuat dari tabung-tabung bambu yang diikat pada sebuah bingkai. Kamu memainkannya dengan cara menggoyangkannya, lalu tabung bambu akan berbenturan dan menghasilkan bunyi yang merdu. Setiap angklung punya nada sendiri, jadi semua orang harus bermain bersama agar lagunya lengkap dan indah.","body_en":"Angklung is a traditional instrument from the Sundanese people of West Java. It is made from bamboo tubes tied onto a frame. You play it by shaking it, and the bamboo tubes knock together to make a sweet, ringing sound. Each angklung has only its own note, so everyone has to play together to make the whole song complete and beautiful."},{"icon":"build","h_id":"Terbuat dari Bambu","h_en":"Made from Bamboo","body_id":"Angklung dibuat dari bambu pilihan, seperti bambu hitam dan bambu ater. Bambu dipotong dan diraut dengan hati-hati supaya menghasilkan nada yang tepat. Tabung yang besar berbunyi rendah, dan tabung yang kecil berbunyi tinggi. Setiap angklung biasanya punya 2 sampai 4 tabung yang berbunyi serempak dalam satu nada.","body_en":"Angklung is made from special bamboo, such as black bamboo and ater bamboo. The bamboo is cut and shaped very carefully so it makes exactly the right note. A big tube makes a low sound, and a small tube makes a high sound. Each angklung usually has 2 to 4 tubes that ring together as one note."},{"icon":"groups","h_id":"Bermain Bersama","h_en":"Playing Together","body_id":"Karena satu angklung hanya bisa membunyikan satu nada, alat musik ini paling seru dimainkan beramai-ramai. Setiap pemain memegang satu atau dua angklung dan menggoyangkannya saat gilirannya tiba. Seorang pemimpin di depan memberi aba-aba dengan tangannya. Kalau semua kompak, banyak angklung kecil bisa berubah menjadi satu lagu yang utuh dan indah.","body_en":"Because one angklung can only make one note, this instrument is most fun when played in a big group. Each player holds one or two angklung and shakes it when it is their turn. A leader at the front gives signals with their hands. When everyone works together, many little angklung turn into one complete, beautiful song."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Cerita Lama Angklung","h_en":"The Old Story of Angklung","body_id":"Sudah ratusan tahun lalu, orang Sunda memainkan angklung. Dahulu angklung dibunyikan dalam upacara padi untuk menghormati Dewi Sri, dewi padi, agar tanaman tumbuh subur. Angklung juga pernah dipakai untuk membangkitkan semangat para pejuang. Lama-kelamaan, angklung berkembang menjadi musik yang menghibur dan dimainkan di mana-mana.","body_en":"For hundreds of years, the Sundanese people have played angklung. Long ago, angklung was played in rice ceremonies to honor Dewi Sri, the rice goddess, so the crops would grow well. Angklung was also once used to lift the spirits of warriors. Over time, angklung grew into joyful music played in many places."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kebanggaan Indonesia","h_en":"Indonesia's Pride","body_id":"Pada tahun 2010, UNESCO mengakui angklung sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia. Artinya, angklung dianggap istimewa dan harus dijaga oleh semua orang. Sekarang angklung diajarkan di sekolah-sekolah dan dimainkan sampai ke luar negeri. Ayo kita ikut bangga dan terus melestarikan musik bambu yang ceria ini!","body_en":"In 2010, UNESCO recognized angklung as a World Cultural Heritage. That means angklung is seen as very special and should be protected by everyone. Today angklung is taught in schools and played all the way to other countries. Let's be proud and keep this cheerful bamboo music alive!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Satu angklung hanya bisa membunyikan satu nada, jadi harus dimainkan beramai-ramai!","en":"One angklung can only make one note, so it must be played in a big group!"},{"id":"Kamu memainkan angklung cukup dengan menggoyang-goyangkannya.","en":"You play angklung simply by shaking it."},{"id":"Angklung dibuat dari bambu, bukan dari logam atau kayu.","en":"Angklung is made from bamboo, not metal or wood."},{"id":"UNESCO mengakui angklung sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia pada tahun 2010.","en":"UNESCO recognized angklung as a World Heritage in 2010."},{"id":"Nama 'angklung' berasal dari bunyi 'klung' yang terdengar saat dimainkan.","en":"The name 'angklung' comes from the 'klung' sound it makes when played."},{"id":"Dahulu angklung dibunyikan dalam upacara padi untuk Dewi Sri.","en":"Long ago angklung was played in rice ceremonies for Dewi Sri."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Bambu","def_id":"Tanaman tinggi berongga yang batangnya kuat dan dipakai membuat angklung.","def_en":"A tall, hollow plant with a strong stem used to make angklung."},{"term":"Nada","def_id":"Bunyi tinggi atau rendah dalam musik.","def_en":"A high or low sound in music."},{"term":"Tabung","def_id":"Potongan bambu berbentuk pipa yang menghasilkan bunyi pada angklung.","def_en":"A pipe-shaped piece of bamboo that makes the sound in an angklung."},{"term":"Sunda","def_id":"Suku dan budaya yang berasal dari Jawa Barat.","def_en":"An ethnic group and culture from West Java."},{"term":"Warisan budaya","def_id":"Sesuatu yang berharga dari nenek moyang yang harus kita jaga.","def_en":"Something precious from our ancestors that we must protect."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3678684be69ee7c3.jpg","caption_id":"Deretan angklung bambu siap dimainkan di sebuah sanggar musik.","caption_en":"Rows of bamboo angklung ready to be played at a music studio.","credit":"dicky satarman from bandung, indonesia","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/4473eefddbfe418b.jpg","caption_id":"Angklung digantung berjajar, memperlihatkan tabung-tabung bambunya.","caption_en":"Angklung hung in a row, showing off their bamboo tubes.","credit":"Terry Ballard from Merrick, New York, USA","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/18c7b883c75fd11f.jpg","caption_id":"Satu buah angklung dengan tabung besar dan kecil pada bingkainya.","caption_en":"A single angklung with big and small tubes on its frame.","credit":"Putri siska","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3d7fcc87f64c8054.jpg","caption_id":"Foto lama anak-anak Jawa Barat memegang angklung lebih dari seratus tahun lalu.","caption_en":"An old photo of West Javanese children holding angklung over a hundred years ago.","credit":"Unknown author","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/23ccd8e4cc6ddccd.jpg","caption_id":"Satu set angklung lengkap yang dipajang di museum musik.","caption_en":"A complete set of angklung on display in a music museum.","credit":"Malibugalz","license":"CC BY 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angklung"},"budaya_batik_indonesia":{"id":"budaya_batik_indonesia","title_id":"Batik","title_en":"Batik","subtitle_id":"Kain bergambar indah yang dilukis dengan lilin malam","subtitle_en":"Beautiful patterned cloth drawn with wax","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Jawa, Indonesia","value_en":"Java, Indonesia"},{"icon":"brush","label_id":"Teknik","label_en":"Technique","value_id":"Canting & malam (lilin)","value_en":"Canting & wax"},{"icon":"checkroom","label_id":"Bahan","label_en":"Material","value_id":"Kain (katun/sutra)","value_en":"Cloth (cotton/silk)"},{"icon":"palette","label_id":"Ciri khas","label_en":"Special for","value_id":"Motif beraneka ragam","value_en":"Many kinds of patterns"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"brush","h_id":"Apa Itu Batik?","h_en":"What Is Batik?","body_id":"Batik adalah kain bergambar indah yang berasal dari Indonesia, terutama dari Pulau Jawa. Gambar atau pola pada batik dibuat dengan cara yang sangat khusus, yaitu menggunakan lilin malam yang panas. Batik bukan hanya kain biasa, melainkan sebuah karya seni. Orang Indonesia memakai batik untuk ke sekolah, ke kantor, ke pesta, sampai acara penting lainnya.","body_en":"Batik is beautiful patterned cloth that comes from Indonesia, especially from the island of Java. The pictures or patterns on batik are made in a very special way, using hot wax. Batik is not just ordinary cloth; it is a work of art. Indonesian people wear batik to school, to the office, to parties, and to other important events."},{"icon":"edit","h_id":"Canting dan Malam","h_en":"The Canting and the Wax","body_id":"Untuk membuat batik tulis, pengrajin memakai alat kecil bernama canting. Canting punya wadah kecil dan ujung pipa untuk mengeluarkan lilin malam yang panas. Lilin dilukiskan di atas kain mengikuti pola gambar. Setelah kering, kain dicelup ke pewarna. Bagian yang tertutup lilin tidak akan terkena warna, sehingga muncullah gambar yang cantik.","body_en":"To make hand-drawn batik, the crafter uses a small tool called a canting. The canting has a tiny cup and a thin spout to pour out hot wax. The wax is drawn onto the cloth following the pattern. After it dries, the cloth is dipped into dye. The parts covered by wax do not catch the color, so a beautiful picture appears."},{"icon":"format_paint","h_id":"Batik Tulis dan Batik Cap","h_en":"Hand-Drawn and Stamped Batik","body_id":"Ada dua cara utama membuat batik. Yang pertama adalah batik tulis, yaitu pola dilukis satu per satu dengan canting. Batik tulis butuh waktu lama dan sangat teliti, kadang sampai berminggu-minggu. Yang kedua adalah batik cap, yaitu pola dibuat dengan stempel tembaga, sehingga lebih cepat. Keduanya sama-sama indah dan disukai orang.","body_en":"There are two main ways to make batik. The first is hand-drawn batik, where the pattern is drawn one piece at a time with a canting. Hand-drawn batik takes a long time and great care, sometimes many weeks. The second is stamped batik, where the pattern is made with a copper stamp, so it is faster. Both are equally beautiful and loved by people."},{"icon":"auto_awesome","h_id":"Motif Penuh Makna","h_en":"Patterns Full of Meaning","body_id":"Setiap motif batik punya nama dan cerita sendiri. Ada motif Parang yang bergaris miring seperti ombak, ada motif Kawung, Mega Mendung, dan banyak motif bunga serta hewan. Dahulu, beberapa motif hanya boleh dipakai oleh keluarga raja. Sekarang siapa saja boleh memakai batik dan menikmati keindahannya.","body_en":"Every batik pattern has its own name and story. There is the Parang pattern with slanted lines like waves, there is the Kawung pattern, Mega Mendung, and many flower and animal patterns. Long ago, some patterns could only be worn by the royal family. Today anyone may wear batik and enjoy its beauty."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kebanggaan Indonesia","h_en":"Indonesia's Pride","body_id":"Pada tanggal 2 Oktober 2009, UNESCO menetapkan batik sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia dari Indonesia. Karena itu, setiap tanggal 2 Oktober kita rayakan sebagai Hari Batik Nasional. Pada hari itu, banyak orang memakai baju batik dengan bangga. Ayo kita cintai dan lestarikan batik agar tidak hilang ditelan zaman!","body_en":"On October 2, 2009, UNESCO declared batik a World Cultural Heritage from Indonesia. Because of this, every October 2 is celebrated as National Batik Day. On that day, many people proudly wear batik clothes. Let's love and protect batik so it is never lost to time!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Batik dibuat dengan melukis lilin malam panas di atas kain.","en":"Batik is made by drawing hot wax onto cloth."},{"id":"Alat kecil untuk melukis lilin disebut canting.","en":"The small tool for drawing the wax is called a canting."},{"id":"Setiap tanggal 2 Oktober dirayakan sebagai Hari Batik Nasional.","en":"Every October 2 is celebrated as National Batik Day."},{"id":"UNESCO mengakui batik sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia pada tahun 2009.","en":"UNESCO recognized batik as a World Heritage in 2009."},{"id":"Batik tulis bisa memakan waktu berminggu-minggu untuk satu kain.","en":"One hand-drawn batik cloth can take many weeks to finish."},{"id":"Setiap motif batik, seperti Parang, punya nama dan ceritanya sendiri.","en":"Each batik pattern, like Parang, has its own name and story."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Canting","def_id":"Alat kecil dengan ujung pipa untuk melukis lilin malam di atas kain.","def_en":"A small tool with a thin spout for drawing wax onto cloth."},{"term":"Malam","def_id":"Lilin khusus yang dipanaskan untuk membuat pola batik.","def_en":"A special wax that is heated to make batik patterns."},{"term":"Motif","def_id":"Pola atau gambar berulang yang menghiasi kain batik.","def_en":"A repeating pattern or picture that decorates batik cloth."},{"term":"Batik tulis","def_id":"Batik yang polanya dilukis satu per satu dengan tangan memakai canting.","def_en":"Batik whose pattern is drawn by hand, piece by piece, with a canting."},{"term":"Batik cap","def_id":"Batik yang polanya dibuat dengan stempel tembaga sehingga lebih cepat.","def_en":"Batik whose pattern is made with a copper stamp, so it is faster."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/09d194fb586a5d23.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang nenek pengrajin melukis pola batik tulis dengan canting.","caption_en":"An elderly crafter draws a batik pattern by hand with a canting.","credit":"Stephen Kennedy","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/24231244229c8455.jpg","caption_id":"Beberapa pembatik bekerja bersama membuat kain batik.","caption_en":"Several batik makers work together on a piece of cloth.","credit":"Mw.Prof.Dr. C.H.M. (Hetty) Nooy-Palm","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b2dcc550e068e505.jpg","caption_id":"Canting dipakai dari dekat untuk menorehkan lilin malam ke kain.","caption_en":"A close look at a canting laying down hot wax onto the cloth.","credit":"essenziale","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/7dc2f7001835484f.jpg","caption_id":"Kain batik kuno dengan motif Parang yang bergaris miring.","caption_en":"An antique batik cloth with the slanted Parang pattern.","credit":"Unknown author","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f6103348bd747575.jpg","caption_id":"Gedung Museum Batik tempat kain-kain batik dijaga dan dipamerkan.","caption_en":"A Batik Museum building, where batik cloths are kept and shown.","credit":"JV03 Novia Rochmawati","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batik"},"budaya_candi_prambanan":{"id":"budaya_candi_prambanan","title_id":"Candi Prambanan","title_en":"Prambanan Temple","subtitle_id":"Candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"The biggest Hindu temple in Indonesia!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Lokasi","label_en":"Location","value_id":"Perbatasan Yogyakarta & Jawa Tengah","value_en":"Border of Yogyakarta & Central Java"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Dibangun","label_en":"Built","value_id":"Sekitar tahun 850 M (abad ke-9)","value_en":"Around 850 CE (9th century)"},{"icon":"temple_hindu","label_id":"Agama","label_en":"Religion","value_id":"Hindu (untuk Trimurti)","value_en":"Hindu (for the Trimurti)"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Tinggi","label_en":"Height","value_id":"Candi Siwa setinggi 47 meter","value_en":"Shiva temple is 47 meters tall"},{"icon":"account_balance","label_id":"Nama Asli","label_en":"Original Name","value_id":"Siwagrha ('Rumah Siwa')","value_en":"Shivagrha ('House of Shiva')"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan Dunia UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO World Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"temple_hindu","h_id":"Apa Itu Prambanan?","h_en":"What Is Prambanan?","body_id":"Candi Prambanan adalah candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia. Bentuknya tinggi, ramping, dan runcing seperti gunung-gunung batu yang menjulang ke langit. Candi ini juga disebut Candi Rara Jonggrang. Banyak orang menyebutnya salah satu candi terindah di Asia Tenggara!","body_en":"Prambanan is the biggest Hindu temple in Indonesia. It is tall, slim, and pointy, like stone mountains reaching up to the sky. The temple is also called Rara Jonggrang Temple. Many people call it one of the most beautiful temples in all of Southeast Asia!"},{"icon":"groups","h_id":"Rumah Tiga Dewa","h_en":"Home of Three Gods","body_id":"Prambanan dibangun untuk memuliakan Trimurti, yaitu tiga dewa utama Hindu. Mereka adalah Brahma sang pencipta, Wisnu sang pemelihara, dan Siwa sang pemusnah. Candi yang paling besar dan tinggi adalah Candi Siwa di tengah. Di dalamnya ada patung Siwa setinggi tiga meter.","body_en":"Prambanan was built to honor the Trimurti, the three main Hindu gods. They are Brahma the creator, Vishnu the keeper, and Shiva the destroyer. The biggest and tallest building is the Shiva temple in the middle. Inside it stands a three-meter-tall statue of Shiva."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Kapan & Siapa Pembangunnya?","h_en":"When and Who Built It?","body_id":"Prambanan mulai dibangun sekitar tahun 850 Masehi, lebih dari 1.000 tahun yang lalu. Raja Rakai Pikatan memulainya pada masa Kerajaan Medang Mataram. Raja-raja sesudahnya terus memperbesar dan memperindah candi ini. Nama aslinya adalah Siwagrha, yang berarti 'Rumah Siwa'.","body_en":"Prambanan began to be built around 850 CE, more than 1,000 years ago. King Rakai Pikatan started it during the Medang Mataram Kingdom. The kings who came after kept making the temple bigger and more beautiful. Its original name was Shivagrha, which means 'House of Shiva'."},{"icon":"festival","h_id":"Tarian di Bawah Cahaya","h_en":"Dancing Under the Lights","body_id":"Sampai hari ini Prambanan menjadi tempat pertunjukan dan wisata. Pada malam hari, candi disinari lampu dan penari menampilkan kisah Ramayana di depannya. Wisatawan dari seluruh dunia datang untuk melihat keindahannya. Candi ini membuat banyak orang kagum pada budaya Indonesia.","body_en":"To this day Prambanan is a place for shows and visits. At night, the temple is lit up and dancers perform the Ramayana story in front of it. Tourists from all over the world come to see its beauty. The temple makes many people admire Indonesian culture."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Runtuh, Lalu Dibangun Lagi","h_en":"Fallen, Then Rebuilt","body_id":"Dahulu Prambanan pernah runtuh dan berubah menjadi tumpukan batu selama ratusan tahun. Gempa bumi dan waktu membuat banyak candinya roboh. Lalu orang-orang menyusun kembali batu-batunya dengan hati-hati. Sekarang Prambanan dilindungi sebagai Warisan Dunia UNESCO.","body_en":"Long ago Prambanan fell down and turned into piles of stone for hundreds of years. Earthquakes and time made many of its temples collapse. Then people carefully put the stones back together. Today Prambanan is protected as a UNESCO World Heritage site."}],"facts":[{"id":"Prambanan adalah candi Hindu terbesar di Indonesia!","en":"Prambanan is the biggest Hindu temple in Indonesia!"},{"id":"Candi Siwa di tengah tingginya mencapai 47 meter, setinggi gedung belasan lantai.","en":"The Shiva temple in the middle is 47 meters tall, like a building over ten floors high."},{"id":"Candi ini dipersembahkan untuk tiga dewa Hindu: Brahma, Wisnu, dan Siwa.","en":"The temple is dedicated to three Hindu gods: Brahma, Vishnu, and Shiva."},{"id":"Nama aslinya, Siwagrha, berarti 'Rumah Siwa'.","en":"Its original name, Shivagrha, means 'House of Shiva'."},{"id":"Prambanan dibangun lebih dari 1.000 tahun yang lalu dari batu yang disusun tanpa semen.","en":"Prambanan was built more than 1,000 years ago from stones stacked without cement."},{"id":"Pada malam hari, kisah Ramayana ditarikan di depan candi yang bercahaya.","en":"At night, the Ramayana story is danced in front of the glowing temple."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Candi","def_id":"Bangunan suci dari batu peninggalan zaman Hindu-Buddha di Nusantara.","def_en":"A stone holy building left from the Hindu-Buddhist era in the Indonesian islands."},{"term":"Trimurti","def_id":"Tiga dewa utama Hindu: Brahma, Wisnu, dan Siwa.","def_en":"The three main Hindu gods: Brahma, Vishnu, and Shiva."},{"term":"Hindu","def_id":"Salah satu agama tertua di dunia yang memuja banyak dewa.","def_en":"One of the world's oldest religions, which worships many gods."},{"term":"Ramayana","def_id":"Cerita kuno tentang Pangeran Rama yang sering ditarikan dan dimainkan.","def_en":"An ancient story about Prince Rama, often danced and performed."},{"term":"Relief","def_id":"Gambar atau cerita yang dipahat timbul pada permukaan batu candi.","def_en":"A picture or story carved so it stands out on a temple's stone surface."},{"term":"Warisan Dunia","def_id":"Tempat istimewa yang dilindungi UNESCO untuk seluruh umat manusia.","def_en":"A special place protected by UNESCO for all of humanity."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/42287c7242816945.jpg","caption_id":"Menara-menara Candi Prambanan yang tinggi dan runcing, berdiri megah di antara rumput hijau.","caption_en":"The tall, pointy towers of Prambanan Temple, standing grandly among green grass.","credit":"CEphoto, Uwe Aranas","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/92c42f475f93bd84.jpg","caption_id":"Puncak Prambanan menyembul di antara kabut pagi dan pohon-pohon kelapa.","caption_en":"Prambanan's peaks rise through the morning mist and coconut trees.","credit":"Dwi Oblo of Reuters Indonesia","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/69edac8c406826da.jpg","caption_id":"Penari membawakan kisah Ramayana pada malam hari, dengan candi yang bercahaya di belakang.","caption_en":"Dancers perform the Ramayana story at night, with the glowing temple behind them.","credit":"Maria Ismawi","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/82f3e41268621818.jpg","caption_id":"Foto lama tahun 1895 saat Prambanan masih berupa reruntuhan batu sebelum diperbaiki.","caption_en":"An old 1895 photo when Prambanan was still a pile of ruins before it was repaired.","credit":"William Henry Jackson","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Candi_Prambanan"},"budaya_tari_kecak_bali":{"id":"budaya_tari_kecak_bali","title_id":"Tari Kecak","title_en":"Kecak Dance","subtitle_id":"Tarian Bali dengan paduan suara 'cak' dari puluhan penari","subtitle_en":"A Balinese dance with the 'cak' chant of dozens of dancers","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Bali, Indonesia","value_en":"Bali, Indonesia"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Penari","label_en":"Performers","value_id":"Puluhan pria","value_en":"Dozens of men"},{"icon":"campaign","label_id":"Iringan","label_en":"Music","value_id":"Suara 'cak', tanpa alat musik","value_en":"The 'cak' chant, no instruments"},{"icon":"theater_comedy","label_id":"Cerita","label_en":"Story","value_id":"Kisah Ramayana","value_en":"The Ramayana story"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Suasana","label_en":"Setting","value_id":"Sering di sore atau malam","value_en":"Often at sunset or night"}],"sections":[{"icon":"theater_comedy","h_id":"Apa Itu Tari Kecak?","h_en":"What Is the Kecak Dance?","body_id":"Tari Kecak adalah tarian sekaligus drama khas dari Pulau Bali. Tarian ini sangat terkenal karena dimainkan oleh puluhan penari laki-laki yang duduk melingkar. Mereka tidak memakai alat musik sama sekali. Sebagai gantinya, para penari berseru 'cak-cak-cak' bersama-sama dengan irama yang cepat. Dari seruan itulah tarian ini mendapat nama 'Kecak'.","body_en":"The Kecak dance is a dance and drama from the island of Bali. It is very famous because it is performed by dozens of male dancers sitting in a circle. They do not use any musical instruments at all. Instead, the dancers chant 'cak-cak-cak' together in a fast rhythm. That chant is how the dance got the name 'Kecak'."},{"icon":"campaign","h_id":"Suara Manusia Jadi Musik","h_en":"Voices Become the Music","body_id":"Yang membuat Kecak istimewa adalah musiknya yang berasal dari suara manusia. Para penari yang duduk melingkar menyerukan 'cak' berulang-ulang dengan irama berbeda-beda. Ada yang berseru cepat, ada yang lambat, sehingga terdengar seperti orkestra. Sambil bersuara, mereka mengangkat dan menggerakkan kedua tangan ke atas. Suara puluhan orang ini terdengar sangat menggetarkan hati.","body_en":"What makes Kecak special is that its music comes from human voices. The dancers sitting in a circle chant 'cak' over and over in different rhythms. Some chant fast and some slow, so it sounds like an orchestra. While chanting, they raise and wave their arms up high. The sound of dozens of people together feels very powerful and exciting."},{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Kisah Ramayana","h_en":"The Ramayana Story","body_id":"Tari Kecak menceritakan kisah lama yang bernama Ramayana. Dalam cerita ini, Putri Shinta diculik oleh raksasa jahat bernama Rahwana. Pangeran Rama lalu berjuang untuk menyelamatkannya. Ia dibantu oleh pasukan kera dan kera putih yang gagah berani bernama Hanoman. Para penari yang duduk melingkar berperan sebagai pasukan kera dalam cerita seru ini.","body_en":"The Kecak dance tells an old story called the Ramayana. In this story, Princess Sinta is taken away by an evil giant named Ravana. Prince Rama then fights to rescue her. He is helped by an army of monkeys and a brave white monkey named Hanoman. The dancers sitting in the circle play the monkey army in this exciting story."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Did It Come From?","body_id":"Tari Kecak tumbuh dari sebuah ritual lama di Bali yang disebut Sanghyang. Pada tahun 1930-an, seorang seniman Bali bernama Wayan Limbak bekerja sama dengan pelukis dari Jerman, Walter Spies. Mereka mengubah ritual itu menjadi pertunjukan tari yang menceritakan Ramayana. Wayan Limbak lalu memperkenalkan Tari Kecak ke berbagai negara di dunia.","body_en":"The Kecak dance grew out of an old Balinese ritual called Sanghyang. In the 1930s, a Balinese artist named Wayan Limbak worked together with a German painter, Walter Spies. They turned the ritual into a dance show that tells the Ramayana. Wayan Limbak then introduced the Kecak dance to many countries around the world."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Pertunjukan yang Memukau","h_en":"An Amazing Show","body_id":"Sekarang, Tari Kecak menjadi pertunjukan yang sangat digemari, terutama oleh wisatawan di Bali. Pertunjukan sering diadakan saat matahari terbenam di tepi pantai, seperti di Pura Uluwatu yang indah. Beberapa pertunjukan bahkan menampilkan tarian api yang menegangkan. Tari Kecak membuat banyak orang kagum pada keindahan budaya Bali.","body_en":"Today, the Kecak dance is a very popular show, especially for visitors in Bali. Performances are often held at sunset by the sea, such as at the beautiful Uluwatu Temple. Some shows even feature a thrilling fire dance. The Kecak dance makes many people amazed by the beauty of Balinese culture."}],"facts":[{"id":"Tari Kecak tidak memakai alat musik sama sekali, hanya suara penari!","en":"The Kecak dance uses no instruments at all, only the dancers' voices!"},{"id":"Nama 'Kecak' berasal dari seruan 'cak-cak-cak' yang dinyanyikan penari.","en":"The name 'Kecak' comes from the 'cak-cak-cak' chant the dancers sing."},{"id":"Tarian ini dimainkan oleh puluhan penari laki-laki yang duduk melingkar.","en":"The dance is performed by dozens of male dancers sitting in a circle."},{"id":"Tari Kecak menceritakan kisah Ramayana tentang Rama dan Shinta.","en":"The Kecak dance tells the Ramayana story about Rama and Sinta."},{"id":"Kera putih pemberani dalam cerita ini bernama Hanoman.","en":"The brave white monkey in the story is named Hanoman."},{"id":"Tari Kecak diciptakan sekitar tahun 1930-an di Bali.","en":"The Kecak dance was created around the 1930s in Bali."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Ramayana","def_id":"Cerita lama tentang Pangeran Rama yang menyelamatkan Putri Shinta.","def_en":"An old story about Prince Rama rescuing Princess Sinta."},{"term":"Hanoman","def_id":"Kera putih gagah berani yang membantu Rama dalam cerita Ramayana.","def_en":"The brave white monkey who helps Rama in the Ramayana story."},{"term":"Paduan suara","def_id":"Banyak orang yang bersuara atau bernyanyi bersama-sama.","def_en":"Many people making sounds or singing together at the same time."},{"term":"Ritual","def_id":"Upacara khusus yang dilakukan dengan cara tertentu sejak dahulu.","def_en":"A special ceremony done in a certain way since long ago."},{"term":"Pura","def_id":"Tempat ibadah umat Hindu di Bali.","def_en":"A Hindu place of worship in Bali."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/434a268d42c0bbcb.jpg","caption_id":"Puluhan penari Kecak duduk melingkar mengelilingi nyala api saat malam.","caption_en":"Dozens of Kecak dancers sit in a circle around a flame at night.","credit":"Jeong seolah","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/70caa26bf68f5173.jpg","caption_id":"Para penari mengangkat tangan tinggi-tinggi sambil menyerukan 'cak'.","caption_en":"The dancers raise their arms high while chanting 'cak'.","credit":"Mr Aaron","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/fa7dc6c738c04f2e.jpg","caption_id":"Tokoh Hanoman si kera putih tampil di tengah penonton.","caption_en":"The character Hanoman, the white monkey, performs among the audience.","credit":"NarayaIsIyoSoup","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9abe45cd2fb19fe7.jpg","caption_id":"Tarian api yang menegangkan menjadi bagian seru dari pertunjukan Kecak.","caption_en":"A thrilling fire dance is an exciting part of the Kecak show.","credit":"Yuma patarihan79","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/18ef104a014c5287.jpg","caption_id":"Dilihat dari atas, ratusan penari membentuk lingkaran besar yang rapi.","caption_en":"Seen from above, hundreds of dancers form one big, neat circle.","credit":"Unknown author","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kecak"},"budaya_tari_saman":{"id":"budaya_tari_saman","title_id":"Tari Saman","title_en":"Saman Dance","subtitle_id":"Tarian Aceh dengan tepuk tangan cepat dan gerak kompak","subtitle_en":"An Aceh dance with fast claps and perfect teamwork","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Aceh (Suku Gayo)","value_en":"Aceh (Gayo people)"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Penari","label_en":"Performers","value_id":"Belasan penari, berjajar","value_en":"Many dancers, in a row"},{"icon":"campaign","label_id":"Iringan","label_en":"Music","value_id":"Tepuk tangan & nyanyian","value_en":"Claps & singing"},{"icon":"diversity_3","label_id":"Ciri khas","label_en":"Famous for","value_id":"Gerak kompak & cepat","value_en":"Fast, united moves"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Apa Itu Tari Saman?","h_en":"What Is the Saman Dance?","body_id":"Tari Saman adalah tarian tradisional dari Suku Gayo di Provinsi Aceh. Tarian ini terkenal di seluruh dunia karena gerakannya yang sangat cepat dan kompak. Para penari duduk berjajar rapat bahu-membahu, lalu bergerak bersama-sama seolah-olah satu tubuh. Tari Saman sering disebut 'Tari Seribu Tangan' karena banyaknya tangan yang bergerak serempak.","body_en":"The Saman dance is a traditional dance from the Gayo people in Aceh Province. It is famous all over the world because of its very fast and united movements. The dancers sit in a tight row, shoulder to shoulder, and move together as if they were one body. The Saman dance is often called the 'Dance of a Thousand Hands' because so many hands move at the same time."},{"icon":"back_hand","h_id":"Tepuk Tangan dan Tepuk Dada","h_en":"Clapping Hands and Chest","body_id":"Yang paling seru dari Tari Saman adalah gerakan tangannya. Para penari bertepuk tangan, menepuk dada, dan menepuk paha dengan sangat cepat. Mereka juga menggoyangkan badan dan kepala ke kiri dan ke kanan. Semua gerakan ini harus dilakukan dengan tepat dan serempak. Kalau satu penari saja salah, gerakannya bisa terlihat tidak kompak.","body_en":"The most exciting part of the Saman dance is its hand movements. The dancers clap their hands, slap their chests, and pat their thighs very fast. They also sway their bodies and heads to the left and right. All of these moves must be done exactly and at the same time. If even one dancer makes a mistake, the dance can look out of step."},{"icon":"campaign","h_id":"Nyanyian dan Pemimpin","h_en":"Singing and the Leader","body_id":"Tari Saman tidak memakai alat musik. Musiknya berasal dari tepuk tangan para penari dan nyanyian mereka. Ada seorang pemimpin yang disebut syekh. Syekh bertugas menyanyikan syair dan mengatur kapan gerakan harus cepat atau lambat. Para penari lalu menjawab nyanyian itu bersama-sama, sehingga terdengar sangat merdu dan bersemangat.","body_en":"The Saman dance uses no musical instruments. Its music comes from the dancers' claps and their singing. There is a leader called the syekh. The syekh sings the verses and decides when the moves should be fast or slow. The dancers then answer the song together, so it sounds very sweet and full of spirit."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Pesan dalam Tarian","h_en":"A Message in the Dance","body_id":"Dahulu, Tari Saman dipakai untuk menyampaikan pesan-pesan yang baik kepada masyarakat. Syair lagunya berisi nasihat tentang kebaikan, sopan santun, dan kebersamaan. Tarian ini juga mengajarkan kita untuk kompak dan saling bekerja sama. Sampai sekarang, Tari Saman sering ditampilkan dalam acara-acara penting dan perayaan di Aceh.","body_en":"Long ago, the Saman dance was used to share good messages with the people. Its song verses contain advice about kindness, good manners, and togetherness. The dance also teaches us to work as a team and help one another. Even today, the Saman dance is often performed at important events and celebrations in Aceh."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kebanggaan Indonesia","h_en":"Indonesia's Pride","body_id":"Pada tahun 2011, UNESCO mengakui Tari Saman sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia. Pengakuan ini membuat masyarakat Indonesia sangat bangga. Sekarang Tari Saman dipelajari oleh banyak anak dan ditampilkan sampai ke luar negeri. Ayo kita ikut menjaga dan melestarikan tarian yang penuh semangat ini agar tidak pernah hilang!","body_en":"In 2011, UNESCO recognized the Saman dance as a World Cultural Heritage. This recognition made Indonesian people very proud. Today the Saman dance is learned by many children and performed all the way to other countries. Let's help protect and keep this spirited dance alive so it is never lost!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Tari Saman sering disebut 'Tari Seribu Tangan' karena gerakan tangannya yang banyak dan serempak.","en":"The Saman dance is often called the 'Dance of a Thousand Hands' for its many hands moving at once."},{"id":"Tarian ini tidak memakai alat musik, hanya tepuk tangan dan nyanyian.","en":"The dance uses no instruments, only claps and singing."},{"id":"Para penari duduk berjajar rapat dan bergerak seperti satu tubuh.","en":"The dancers sit in a tight row and move like one body."},{"id":"UNESCO mengakui Tari Saman sebagai Warisan Budaya Dunia pada tahun 2011.","en":"UNESCO recognized the Saman dance as a World Heritage in 2011."},{"id":"Pemimpin Tari Saman yang menyanyi dan memberi aba-aba disebut syekh.","en":"The leader of the Saman dance who sings and gives signals is called the syekh."},{"id":"Tari Saman berasal dari Suku Gayo di Provinsi Aceh.","en":"The Saman dance comes from the Gayo people in Aceh Province."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Suku Gayo","def_id":"Kelompok masyarakat yang tinggal di dataran tinggi Provinsi Aceh.","def_en":"A group of people who live in the highlands of Aceh Province."},{"term":"Syekh","def_id":"Pemimpin Tari Saman yang menyanyi dan mengatur gerakan penari.","def_en":"The leader of the Saman dance who sings and guides the dancers' moves."},{"term":"Syair","def_id":"Kata-kata indah yang dinyanyikan dalam sebuah lagu atau tarian.","def_en":"Beautiful words that are sung in a song or dance."},{"term":"Kompak","def_id":"Bergerak atau bekerja bersama-sama dengan rapi dan serempak.","def_en":"Moving or working together neatly and at the same time."},{"term":"Warisan budaya","def_id":"Sesuatu yang berharga dari nenek moyang yang harus kita jaga.","def_en":"Something precious from our ancestors that we must protect."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/cf3e3f9a0adcac15.jpg","caption_id":"Para penari mengangkat tangan serempak dengan pakaian warna-warni yang cerah.","caption_en":"Dancers raise their hands together in bright, colorful costumes.","credit":"Herusutimbul","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/7add58c305f10a61.jpg","caption_id":"Penari laki-laki berjajar bertepuk tangan dengan busana adat Gayo merah-hitam.","caption_en":"Male dancers in a row clap their hands in red-and-black Gayo costume.","credit":"Winara al gayo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c716b9089d1b40c5.jpg","caption_id":"Ribuan penari menampilkan Tari Saman bersama dalam satu pertunjukan besar.","caption_en":"Thousands of dancers perform the Saman dance together in one huge show.","credit":"Adearmanda","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/83001be976af9ce4.jpg","caption_id":"Sekelompok penari berpose dengan busana adat Gayo yang indah.","caption_en":"A group of dancers pose in their beautiful Gayo costumes.","credit":"Fajriboy","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6bf9be7327a5f3ed.jpg","caption_id":"Foto lama masyarakat Gayo berkumpul lebih dari seratus tahun yang lalu.","caption_en":"An old photo of the Gayo people gathering more than a hundred years ago.","credit":"Unknown author","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tari_Saman"},"budaya_wayang_kulit":{"id":"budaya_wayang_kulit","title_id":"Wayang Kulit","title_en":"Shadow Puppets","subtitle_id":"Boneka kulit yang bercerita lewat bayangan!","subtitle_en":"Leather puppets that tell stories with shadows!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Budaya Jawa, Indonesia","value_en":"Javanese culture, Indonesia"},{"icon":"texture","label_id":"Bahan","label_en":"Material","value_id":"Kulit kerbau atau sapi","value_en":"Buffalo or cow leather"},{"icon":"auto_stories","label_id":"Cerita","label_en":"Stories","value_id":"Ramayana & Mahabharata","value_en":"Ramayana & Mahabharata"},{"icon":"person","label_id":"Pemain","label_en":"Performer","value_id":"Dalang (memainkan semua tokoh)","value_en":"Dalang (plays all characters)"},{"icon":"music_note","label_id":"Musik","label_en":"Music","value_id":"Gamelan & nyanyian pesinden","value_en":"Gamelan & singer's songs"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan Budaya UNESCO (2003)","value_en":"UNESCO Cultural Heritage (2003)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"theater_comedy","h_id":"Apa Itu Wayang Kulit?","h_en":"What Is Wayang Kulit?","body_id":"Wayang kulit adalah boneka pipih yang dibuat dari kulit hewan. Boneka ini dipakai untuk memainkan cerita di balik layar putih. Wayang kulit berasal dari budaya Jawa di Indonesia. Kata 'wayang' berarti 'bayangan', karena penonton melihat bayangan boneka di layar.","body_en":"Wayang kulit is a flat puppet made from animal leather. These puppets are used to act out stories behind a white screen. Wayang kulit comes from Javanese culture in Indonesia. The word 'wayang' means 'shadow', because the audience watches the puppets' shadows on the screen."},{"icon":"person","h_id":"Dalang Sang Pencerita","h_en":"The Dalang, the Storyteller","body_id":"Wayang kulit dimainkan oleh satu orang hebat bernama dalang. Dalang menggerakkan semua boneka sambil mengisi suara setiap tokoh. Ia duduk di balik kelir, yaitu layar kain putih, dengan lampu menyala di belakangnya. Sebuah dalang bisa bercerita semalam suntuk tanpa lelah!","body_en":"Wayang kulit is performed by one amazing person called the dalang. The dalang moves all the puppets while giving each character a voice. The dalang sits behind the kelir, a white cloth screen, with a lamp shining behind it. A dalang can tell a story all night long without getting tired!"},{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Cerita yang Dimainkan","h_en":"The Stories Performed","body_id":"Cerita wayang disebut lakon. Cerita yang paling terkenal berasal dari kisah Ramayana dan Mahabharata. Kisah-kisah ini bercerita tentang ksatria, raja, raksasa, dan kebaikan melawan kejahatan. Ada juga tokoh lucu bernama punakawan: Semar, Gareng, Petruk, dan Bagong.","body_en":"A wayang story is called a lakon. The most famous stories come from the Ramayana and Mahabharata. These tales are about knights, kings, giants, and good against evil. There are also funny characters called the punakawan: Semar, Gareng, Petruk, and Bagong."},{"icon":"brush","h_id":"Bagaimana Wayang Dibuat?","h_en":"How a Puppet Is Made","body_id":"Wayang kulit dibuat dari kulit kerbau, sapi, atau kambing yang sudah dikeringkan. Pengrajin memahat lubang-lubang kecil dengan alat besi tajam supaya wayang terlihat berhias indah. Tangan wayang disambung agar bisa digerakkan. Lalu wayang diberi warna emas dan cat yang cantik.","body_en":"Wayang kulit is made from dried buffalo, cow, or goat leather. Craftspeople carve tiny holes with sharp iron tools so the puppet looks beautifully decorated. The puppet's arms are joined so they can move. Then the puppet is colored with gold and pretty paint."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Harta Budaya Kita","h_en":"Our Cultural Treasure","body_id":"Wayang kulit sudah ada sejak lebih dari seribu tahun yang lalu. Dahulu, Sunan Kalijaga memakai wayang untuk mengajarkan kebaikan kepada masyarakat. Pada tahun 2003, UNESCO mengakui wayang kulit sebagai warisan budaya dunia yang indah dan berharga. Ayo kita ikut menjaga seni asli Indonesia ini!","body_en":"Wayang kulit has existed for more than a thousand years. Long ago, Sunan Kalijaga used wayang to teach good values to the people. In 2003, UNESCO recognized wayang kulit as a beautiful and precious world cultural heritage. Let's all help protect this original Indonesian art!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Kata 'wayang' berarti 'bayangan' dalam bahasa Jawa.","en":"The word 'wayang' means 'shadow' in Javanese."},{"id":"Satu dalang bisa memainkan dan menyuarakan puluhan tokoh sendirian!","en":"A single dalang can play and voice dozens of characters all alone!"},{"id":"Wayang dibuat dari kulit kerbau atau sapi, bukan dari kertas.","en":"Puppets are made from buffalo or cow leather, not from paper."},{"id":"Pertunjukan wayang diiringi musik gamelan dan nyanyian pesinden.","en":"A wayang show is accompanied by gamelan music and a singer's songs."},{"id":"Punakawan seperti Semar dan Petruk adalah tokoh lucu kesukaan penonton.","en":"The punakawan, like Semar and Petruk, are funny characters the audience loves."},{"id":"UNESCO menetapkan wayang kulit sebagai warisan budaya dunia pada tahun 2003.","en":"UNESCO named wayang kulit a world cultural heritage in 2003."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Dalang","def_id":"Orang yang memainkan wayang, mengisi suara, dan menceritakan kisahnya.","def_en":"The person who moves the puppets, voices them, and tells the story."},{"term":"Kelir","def_id":"Layar kain putih tempat bayangan wayang ditampilkan.","def_en":"The white cloth screen where the puppets' shadows appear."},{"term":"Lakon","def_id":"Cerita atau kisah yang dimainkan dalam pertunjukan wayang.","def_en":"The story or tale acted out in a wayang show."},{"term":"Gamelan","def_id":"Kelompok alat musik Jawa yang mengiringi pertunjukan wayang.","def_en":"A set of Javanese musical instruments that accompanies a wayang show."},{"term":"Punakawan","def_id":"Tokoh-tokoh pelayan yang lucu dan bijak: Semar, Gareng, Petruk, Bagong.","def_en":"The funny, wise servant characters: Semar, Gareng, Petruk, and Bagong."},{"term":"Pesinden","def_id":"Penyanyi wanita yang menyanyikan tembang saat pertunjukan wayang.","def_en":"A female singer who sings songs during a wayang show."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/30caf2d89435c2c5.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang dalang cilik mengangkat wayang kulit yang berhias rumit di balik lampu pertunjukan.","caption_en":"A young dalang lifts an intricately decorated wayang puppet behind the show's lamp.","credit":"Badroe Zaman, Semarang, Central Java","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/88fcf4bc4917deb0.jpg","caption_id":"Inilah bayangan wayang di layar; karena inilah wayang disebut seni 'bayangan'.","caption_en":"These are the puppets' shadows on the screen; this is why wayang is called the art of 'shadows'.","credit":"Jpatokal (English Wikipedia)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/018084a5b2063f22.jpg","caption_id":"Dalang menggerakkan beberapa wayang sekaligus di depan layar yang bercahaya.","caption_en":"A dalang moves several puppets at once in front of the glowing screen.","credit":"Gunawan Kartapranata","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/934d4dd073fedc8b.jpg","caption_id":"Dalang mengangkat dua gunungan berbentuk daun, biasanya untuk membuka cerita wayang.","caption_en":"A dalang raises two leaf-shaped gunungan puppets, usually to open the wayang story.","credit":"FaizAttariqi","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/198af794fca34940.jpg","caption_id":"Gambar wayang berwarna-warni memperlihatkan hiasan rumit dan bentuk khas sebuah tokoh.","caption_en":"A colorful drawing of a puppet shows the detailed decoration and special shape of one character.","credit":"Mangkunagara VII","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wayang_kulit"},"ensiklopedia_anggrek_macan":{"id":"ensiklopedia_anggrek_macan","title_id":"Anggrek Tebu","title_en":"Giant Orchid","subtitle_id":"Anggrek terbesar di dunia, berat dan tinggi!","subtitle_en":"The biggest orchid in the whole world!","data_card":[{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Tanaman anggrek","value_en":"Orchid plant"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan tropis Asia Tenggara","value_en":"Southeast Asian rainforest"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Tinggi","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Sampai 7,6 meter","value_en":"Up to 7.6 meters tall"},{"icon":"savings","label_id":"Berat","label_en":"Weight","value_id":"Bisa lebih dari 1 ton","value_en":"Can be over 1 ton"},{"icon":"local_florist","label_id":"Mekar","label_en":"Blooms","value_id":"Sekali tiap 2-4 tahun","value_en":"Once every 2-4 years"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Indonesia & Asia Tenggara","value_en":"Indonesia & SE Asia"}],"sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Anggrek Tebu?","h_en":"What Is the Giant Orchid?","body_id":"Anggrek tebu adalah anggrek terbesar di dunia. Orang juga memanggilnya Anggrek Raksasa, Anggrek Harimau, atau Ratu Anggrek. Tanaman ini bisa tumbuh sangat besar dan berat sekali. Bayangkan, ada yang beratnya lebih dari satu ton!","body_en":"The giant orchid is the biggest orchid in the world. People also call it the Giant Orchid, Tiger Orchid, or Queen of Orchids. This plant can grow huge and very heavy. Imagine, some weigh more than one ton!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Anggrek tebu tumbuh di hutan-hutan Asia Tenggara. Kamu bisa menemukannya di Indonesia, seperti di Sumatra, Jawa, Sulawesi, dan Kalimantan. Tanaman ini juga ada di Thailand, Myanmar, Vietnam, dan Malaysia. Ia suka tempat yang hangat dan terkena cahaya matahari.","body_en":"The giant orchid grows in the forests of Southeast Asia. You can find it in Indonesia, like in Sumatra, Java, Sulawesi, and Borneo. It also lives in Thailand, Myanmar, Vietnam, and Malaysia. It loves warm spots with plenty of sunshine."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Special Features","body_id":"Anggrek ini bisa tumbuh setinggi rumah! Pernah ada yang mencapai lebih dari 7 meter. Batangnya yang tebal disebut pseudobulb dan bisa sepanjang 2,5 meter. Anggrek tebu adalah tanaman epifit, artinya ia tumbuh menempel di pohon lain. Akarnya tumbuh seperti ikatan tebal yang menempel di pohon atau batu.","body_en":"This orchid can grow as tall as a house! One was even taller than 7 meters. Its thick stems are called pseudobulbs and can be 2.5 meters long. The giant orchid is an epiphyte, which means it grows clinging onto other trees. Its roots grow in thick bundles that hold onto trees or rocks."},{"icon":"local_florist","h_id":"Bunga yang Istimewa","h_en":"Its Amazing Flowers","body_id":"Bunganya berwarna kuning cerah dengan bintik-bintik merah tua. Satu tangkai bisa punya hingga 80 bunga, dan satu tanaman bisa berbunga ribuan! Anggrek ini hanya mekar sekali setiap dua sampai empat tahun. Tapi saat mekar, bunganya tetap segar dan indah sampai berminggu-minggu.","body_en":"Its flowers are bright yellow with dark red spots. One stalk can have up to 80 flowers, and one plant can bloom thousands! This orchid blooms only once every two to four years. But when it blooms, the flowers stay fresh and pretty for weeks."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Kita Jaga!","h_en":"Let's Take Care of It!","body_id":"Anggrek tebu adalah harta alam Indonesia yang langka dan istimewa. Tanaman ini tumbuh lambat dan butuh hutan yang sehat untuk hidup. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga hutan tetap hijau. Dengan begitu, anak-anak masa depan juga bisa melihat raksasa cantik ini!","body_en":"The giant orchid is a rare and special treasure of Indonesia's nature. This plant grows slowly and needs healthy forests to live. We can help by keeping forests green. That way, future children can also see this beautiful giant!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Anggrek tebu adalah anggrek terbesar di dunia!","en":"The giant orchid is the biggest orchid in the world!"},{"id":"Pernah ada yang tingginya lebih dari 7 meter, setinggi rumah.","en":"One was over 7 meters tall, as tall as a house."},{"id":"Beratnya bisa lebih dari satu ton, seperti seekor sapi besar.","en":"It can weigh over one ton, like a big cow."},{"id":"Satu tanaman pernah berbunga sampai ribuan kuntum sekaligus!","en":"One plant once bloomed with thousands of flowers at once!"},{"id":"Anggrek ini hanya mekar sekali setiap 2 sampai 4 tahun.","en":"This orchid blooms only once every 2 to 4 years."},{"id":"Ada satu yang ditanam tahun 1861 dan masih hidup hingga kini!","en":"One planted in 1861 is still alive today!"}],"glossary":[{"term":"Anggrek","def_id":"Jenis tanaman berbunga indah yang sering tumbuh menempel di pohon.","def_en":"A kind of plant with beautiful flowers that often grows on trees."},{"term":"Pseudobulb","def_id":"Batang anggrek yang tebal dan menggembung untuk menyimpan air dan makanan.","def_en":"The thick, swollen orchid stem that stores water and food."},{"term":"Epifit","def_id":"Tanaman yang tumbuh menempel di pohon lain, tapi tidak mencuri makanannya.","def_en":"A plant that grows clinging onto another tree without stealing its food."},{"term":"Mekar","def_id":"Saat kuncup bunga terbuka dan menjadi bunga yang cantik.","def_en":"When a flower bud opens up into a pretty flower."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/63ce9b63483762b3.jpg","caption_id":"Sekelompok bunga anggrek tebu kuning kecokelatan bermandi cahaya matahari.","caption_en":"A cluster of golden-brown giant orchid flowers basking in sunlight.","credit":"Meneerke bloem","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/0660c966a101239b.jpg","caption_id":"Satu bunga anggrek tebu kuning dengan bintik-bintik merah tua, di antara daun hijau.","caption_en":"A single yellow giant orchid flower with dark red spots among green leaves.","credit":"Brutusaurus","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/12eb3e4b61ec0623.jpg","caption_id":"Bunga anggrek tebu menghadap depan, memperlihatkan kelopak berbintik yang indah.","caption_en":"A giant orchid flower facing front, showing off its beautiful spotted petals.","credit":"Brutusaurus","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anggrek_tebu"},"ensiklopedia_anoa_sulawesi_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_anoa_sulawesi_1","title_id":"Anoa","title_en":"Anoa","subtitle_id":"Kerbau kerdil istimewa khas Pulau Sulawesi.","subtitle_en":"The special dwarf buffalo of Sulawesi.","data_card":[{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Class","value_id":"Mamalia (keluarga kerbau)","value_en":"Mammal (buffalo family)"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan lebat","value_en":"Thick rainforest"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Sulawesi & Pulau Buton","value_en":"Sulawesi & Buton Island"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Tinggi","label_en":"Size","value_id":"60-100 cm di pundak","value_en":"60-100 cm at the shoulder"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Diet","value_id":"Daun & tumbuhan hutan","value_en":"Leaves & forest plants"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam punah","value_en":"Endangered"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Anoa?","h_en":"What Is an Anoa?","body_id":"Anoa adalah kerbau mungil yang sering disebut kerbau kerdil. Bentuk tubuhnya mirip kerbau, tapi ukurannya jauh lebih kecil. Hewan ini hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi dan Pulau Buton di Indonesia. Karena hanya ada di sana, anoa disebut hewan endemik.","body_en":"The anoa is a tiny buffalo often called the dwarf buffalo. Its body looks like a buffalo, but it is much smaller. This animal lives only on Sulawesi Island and Buton Island in Indonesia. Because it lives only there, the anoa is called an endemic animal."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Anoa tinggal di dalam hutan hujan yang masih lebat dan jarang dilewati manusia. Pulau Sulawesi adalah rumah istimewa bagi banyak hewan yang hanya ada di sana. Salah satu kebiasaan favorit anoa adalah berkubang di lumpur. Berkubang membantu tubuhnya tetap sejuk dan bersih.","body_en":"The anoa lives deep in thick rainforests that people rarely visit. Sulawesi Island is a special home for many animals found nowhere else. One of the anoa's favorite habits is wallowing in mud. Wallowing helps keep its body cool and clean."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Special Features","body_id":"Anoa punya tanduk yang mengarah ke belakang dan dasarnya berbentuk seperti segitiga. Kepalanya mirip sapi, dan kakinya mirip banteng. Ada dua jenis anoa: anoa dataran rendah yang lebih besar, dan anoa pegunungan yang lebih kecil. Anoa pegunungan punya tanduk melingkar dan ekor pendek yang lembut.","body_en":"The anoa has horns that point backward with a triangle-shaped base. Its head looks like a cow's, and its legs look like a wild ox's. There are two kinds: the bigger lowland anoa and the smaller mountain anoa. The mountain anoa has curved horns and a short, soft tail."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa?","h_en":"Why Is It Special?","body_id":"Anoa adalah kebanggaan dan ciri khas Pulau Sulawesi. Ia tinggal di Wallacea, daerah unik yang penuh hewan dan tumbuhan yang hanya ada di sana. Anoa termasuk hewan yang pemalu dan suka menyendiri. Para ilmuwan menyayangi anoa karena ia sangat penting bagi alam Indonesia.","body_en":"The anoa is the pride and symbol of Sulawesi Island. It lives in Wallacea, a unique area full of animals and plants found only there. The anoa is a shy creature that likes to be alone. Scientists love the anoa because it is so important to Indonesia's nature."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Sekarang jumlah anoa semakin sedikit, jadi ia perlu kita lindungi. Hewan ini sudah dijaga oleh hukum Indonesia sejak tahun 1931. Anoa butuh hutan yang aman dan sehat untuk hidup. Dengan menjaga hutan, kita membantu anoa terus berkembang biak dengan bahagia.","body_en":"Today there are fewer anoa, so we need to protect it. This animal has been guarded by Indonesian law since 1931. The anoa needs safe and healthy forests to live. By protecting forests, we help the anoa keep growing happily."}],"facts":[{"id":"Anoa adalah kerbau terkecil di dunia, disebut kerbau kerdil!","en":"The anoa is the smallest wild buffalo in the world, the dwarf buffalo!"},{"id":"Anoa hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi dan Pulau Buton.","en":"The anoa lives only on Sulawesi and Buton Islands."},{"id":"Ada dua jenis: anoa pegunungan dan anoa dataran rendah.","en":"There are two kinds: the mountain anoa and the lowland anoa."},{"id":"Anoa suka berkubang di lumpur agar tubuhnya tetap sejuk.","en":"The anoa loves to wallow in mud to keep its body cool."},{"id":"Tanduk anoa berbentuk segitiga di bagian dasarnya.","en":"The anoa's horns have a triangle shape at their base."},{"id":"Anoa sudah dilindungi hukum Indonesia sejak tahun 1931.","en":"The anoa has been protected by Indonesian law since 1931."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan atau tumbuhan yang hidup hanya di satu tempat di dunia.","def_en":"An animal or plant that lives in only one place in the world."},{"term":"Berkubang","def_id":"Berguling-guling di lumpur agar tubuh tetap sejuk dan bersih dari serangga.","def_en":"Rolling around in mud to stay cool and clean of bugs."},{"term":"Wallacea","def_id":"Daerah istimewa di Indonesia, termasuk Sulawesi, yang penuh hewan unik.","def_en":"A special region of Indonesia, including Sulawesi, full of unique animals."},{"term":"Mamalia","def_id":"Hewan yang menyusui anaknya dan biasanya berbulu, seperti anoa dan sapi.","def_en":"An animal that feeds milk to its babies and usually has fur, like the anoa and cows."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9aadc51ed284047d.jpg","caption_id":"Anoa muda berdiri dan menatap kita, tubuhnya kecil seperti kerbau mini.","caption_en":"A young anoa stands and looks at us, its body small like a mini buffalo.","credit":"RianHS","license":"CC BY 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/db38c2979418f98f.jpg","caption_id":"Anoa menundukkan kepala, memperlihatkan tanduk runcing yang mengarah ke belakang.","caption_en":"An anoa lowers its head, showing its sharp horns that point backward.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/cc575629ae3b55cf.jpg","caption_id":"Anoa berwarna cokelat sedang beristirahat dengan tenang.","caption_en":"A brown anoa resting calmly.","credit":"JERRYE AND ROY KLOTZ MD","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b769606dc03bc3bc.jpg","caption_id":"Anoa dataran rendah berwarna hitam berdiri di antara rerumputan hijau.","caption_en":"A black lowland anoa stands among green plants.","credit":"Bluemoose at English Wikipedia","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anoa"},"ensiklopedia_badak_jawa":{"id":"ensiklopedia_badak_jawa","title_id":"Badak Jawa","title_en":"Javan Rhinoceros","subtitle_id":"Badak bercula satu paling langka di dunia.","subtitle_en":"The rarest one-horned rhino in the world.","data_card":[{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Class","value_id":"Mamalia besar","value_en":"Large mammal"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan dataran rendah","value_en":"Lowland rainforest"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Taman Nasional Ujung Kulon","value_en":"Ujung Kulon National Park"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Diet","value_id":"Daun & pucuk tumbuhan","value_en":"Leaves & plant shoots"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Usia","label_en":"Lifespan","value_id":"30-45 tahun","value_en":"30-45 years"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Sangat langka (kritis)","value_en":"Critically endangered"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Badak Jawa?","h_en":"What Is the Javan Rhino?","body_id":"Badak jawa adalah badak bercula satu yang tubuhnya cukup kecil di antara badak lainnya. Kulitnya tebal dan berlipat-lipat, seperti memakai baju pelindung dari baja. Hewan ini adalah salah satu badak paling langka di seluruh dunia. Culanya pendek, biasanya tidak lebih panjang dari sejengkal tangan.","body_en":"The Javan rhino is a one-horned rhino with a smaller body than most other rhinos. Its skin is thick and folded, like it is wearing armor made of steel. This animal is one of the rarest rhinos in the whole world. Its horn is short, usually no longer than a hand's span."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Hari ini, semua badak jawa liar hanya tinggal di satu tempat: Taman Nasional Ujung Kulon. Tempat ini berada di ujung paling barat Pulau Jawa, Indonesia. Dulu badak jawa hidup di banyak negara Asia, tapi sekarang tinggal sedikit. Ujung Kulon bahkan diakui dunia sebagai Situs Warisan Dunia UNESCO.","body_en":"Today, all wild Javan rhinos live in just one place: Ujung Kulon National Park. This park is on the far western tip of Java Island, Indonesia. Long ago Javan rhinos lived in many Asian countries, but now only a few remain. Ujung Kulon is even recognized as a UNESCO World Heritage Site."},{"icon":"water_drop","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Badak jawa suka tinggal di hutan dataran rendah yang lebat dan padang rumput yang basah. Hewan ini senang menyendiri dan biasanya berjalan-jalan sendirian. Mereka suka berkubang di lumpur untuk mendinginkan tubuh. Badak dewasa hampir tidak punya musuh, dan bisa hidup sampai 30 hingga 45 tahun!","body_en":"The Javan rhino loves thick lowland forests and wet grasslands. This animal enjoys being alone and usually wanders by itself. It likes to wallow in mud to cool down its body. Adult rhinos have almost no enemies, and can live up to 30 to 45 years!"},{"icon":"photo_camera","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa?","h_en":"Why Is It Special?","body_id":"Badak jawa sangat langka, jadi para ilmuwan jarang melihatnya langsung. Mereka memakai kamera jebakan yang memotret saat badak lewat. Pada tahun 2011, kamera berhasil merekam ibu-ibu badak bersama anaknya. Itu berita yang membahagiakan, karena membuktikan badak jawa masih punya bayi di alam liar!","body_en":"The Javan rhino is so rare that scientists rarely see it in person. They use camera traps that take photos when a rhino walks by. In 2011, cameras filmed mother rhinos with their babies. That was happy news, because it proved Javan rhinos still have babies in the wild!"},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Karena jumlahnya tinggal sedikit, badak jawa sangat butuh perlindungan kita. Para penjaga taman bekerja keras menjaga mereka tetap aman. Menjaga hutan Ujung Kulon tetap sehat sangat penting bagi badak. Kalau kita semua peduli, badak jawa bisa terus hidup untuk waktu yang lama.","body_en":"Because so few are left, the Javan rhino really needs our protection. Park rangers work hard to keep them safe. Keeping the Ujung Kulon forest healthy is very important for the rhinos. If we all care, the Javan rhino can keep living for a long time."}],"facts":[{"id":"Badak jawa adalah salah satu badak paling langka di dunia!","en":"The Javan rhino is one of the rarest rhinos in the world!"},{"id":"Semua badak jawa liar hanya hidup di Taman Nasional Ujung Kulon.","en":"All wild Javan rhinos live only in Ujung Kulon National Park."},{"id":"Kulitnya berlipat-lipat seperti memakai baju zirah dari baja.","en":"Its folded skin looks like armor made of steel."},{"id":"Badak jawa bisa hidup sampai 30 hingga 45 tahun di alam liar.","en":"The Javan rhino can live 30 to 45 years in the wild."},{"id":"Para ilmuwan memakai kamera jebakan untuk mengintip badak.","en":"Scientists use camera traps to peek at the rhinos."},{"id":"Tahun 2011, kamera merekam bayi badak bersama ibunya!","en":"In 2011, cameras filmed baby rhinos with their moms!"}],"glossary":[{"term":"Cula","def_id":"Tanduk keras di hidung badak; badak jawa hanya punya satu cula.","def_en":"The hard horn on a rhino's nose; the Javan rhino has just one."},{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan yang hidup hanya di satu tempat di dunia.","def_en":"An animal that lives in only one place in the world."},{"term":"Kamera jebakan","def_id":"Kamera di hutan yang memotret sendiri saat ada hewan lewat.","def_en":"A camera in the forest that snaps a photo by itself when an animal passes."},{"term":"Berkubang","def_id":"Berguling-guling di lumpur agar tubuh tetap sejuk.","def_en":"Rolling in mud to keep the body cool."},{"term":"Situs Warisan Dunia","def_id":"Tempat istimewa yang dilindungi dunia karena sangat penting bagi alam.","def_en":"A special place protected by the world because it is so important to nature."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/01c213da6cb774ae.jpg","caption_id":"Foto lama seekor badak jawa, memperlihatkan kulit tebal berlipat seperti baju zirah.","caption_en":"An old photo of a Javan rhino, showing its thick folded skin like armor.","credit":"T.Dixon. The Zoological Society of London","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/360d5dadfb2dfc50.jpg","caption_id":"Seekor induk badak bercula satu menjaga anaknya, mirip cara badak jawa merawat bayinya.","caption_en":"A one-horned rhino mother guards her calf, much like how Javan rhinos care for their babies.","credit":"Jo Oh","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/17b1a5b62b81d39f.jpg","caption_id":"Hutan hijau Taman Nasional Ujung Kulon, rumah terakhir badak jawa di alam liar.","caption_en":"The green forest of Ujung Kulon National Park, the last wild home of the Javan rhino.","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Badak_jawa"},"ensiklopedia_bekantan":{"id":"ensiklopedia_bekantan","title_id":"Bekantan","title_en":"Proboscis Monkey","subtitle_id":"Monyet berhidung panjang khas Pulau Kalimantan.","subtitle_en":"The long-nosed monkey of Borneo.","data_card":[{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Class","value_id":"Mamalia (monyet)","value_en":"Mammal (monkey)"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan, rawa & hutan pantai","value_en":"Forests, swamps & coast"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Pulau Kalimantan","value_en":"Borneo"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Diet","value_id":"Buah, biji & daun","value_en":"Fruit, seeds & leaves"},{"icon":"water_drop","label_id":"Kemampuan","label_en":"Talent","value_id":"Perenang & penyelam hebat","value_en":"Great swimmer & diver"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam punah","value_en":"Endangered"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Bekantan?","h_en":"What Is the Proboscis Monkey?","body_id":"Bekantan adalah monyet berhidung panjang dengan rambut hitam kemerahan. Hidung yang besar dan panjang hanya dimiliki bekantan jantan. Orang juga memanggilnya kera belanda atau monyet belanda. Hewan ini hanya hidup di Pulau Kalimantan, jadi disebut hewan endemik.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey is a long-nosed monkey with reddish-black fur. Only the male proboscis monkeys have the big, long nose. People also call it the Dutch monkey or long-nosed monkey. This animal lives only on Borneo, so it is called an endemic animal."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Bekantan tinggal di hutan, rawa, dan hutan dekat pantai di Kalimantan. Kamu bisa menemukannya di Kalimantan Selatan, Timur, dan Utara. Bekantan adalah hewan kebanggaan Provinsi Kalimantan Selatan. Ia berbagi rumah dengan teman-temannya seperti orangutan dan lutung kelabu.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey lives in forests, swamps, and coastal forests in Borneo. You can find it in South, East, and North Kalimantan. The proboscis monkey is the pride animal of South Kalimantan Province. It shares its home with friends like orangutans and gray langurs."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Perut Buncit","h_en":"Food & Its Big Belly","body_id":"Bekantan suka makan buah, biji-bijian, dan aneka daun. Daun yang dimakannya menghasilkan banyak gas saat dicerna. Itulah kenapa perut bekantan terlihat buncit dan besar. Jadi, perut buncit itu adalah ciri khas yang lucu dari bekantan!","body_en":"The proboscis monkey loves to eat fruits, seeds, and many kinds of leaves. The leaves it eats make lots of gas when digested. That is why the proboscis monkey has a round, big belly. So its big belly is a funny special feature of the proboscis monkey!"},{"icon":"water_drop","h_id":"Perenang yang Hebat","h_en":"A Great Swimmer","body_id":"Bekantan hidup berkelompok, biasanya 10 sampai 32 monyet bersama. Mereka juga jago berenang, bahkan menyeberang dari satu pulau ke pulau lain! Di sela jari kakinya ada selaput tipis yang membantunya berenang. Hidungnya punya semacam katup, jadi ia bisa menyelam beberapa detik.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey lives in groups, usually 10 to 32 monkeys together. They are also great swimmers, even crossing from one island to another! Between their toes is a thin web that helps them swim. Their nose has a kind of valve, so they can dive for a few seconds."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Bekantan perlu kita lindungi karena hutannya semakin berkurang. Kabar baiknya, di Kalimantan Selatan jumlah bekantan naik dari sekitar 3.000 menjadi 4.000 ekor. Ini terjadi karena banyak orang ikut menjaga mereka. Kalau kita menjaga hutan, bekantan bisa terus berenang dan bermain dengan bahagia.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey needs our protection because its forests are shrinking. The good news is that in South Kalimantan their number rose from about 3,000 to 4,000. This happened because many people helped protect them. If we protect the forests, proboscis monkeys can keep swimming and playing happily."}],"facts":[{"id":"Hanya bekantan jantan yang punya hidung panjang dan besar!","en":"Only male proboscis monkeys have the long, big nose!"},{"id":"Bekantan hanya hidup di Pulau Kalimantan.","en":"The proboscis monkey lives only on Borneo."},{"id":"Perutnya buncit karena banyak makan daun yang menghasilkan gas.","en":"Its belly is big from eating many gassy leaves."},{"id":"Bekantan jago berenang dan punya selaput di sela jari kaki.","en":"The proboscis monkey is a great swimmer with webbed toes."},{"id":"Bekantan adalah hewan kebanggaan Kalimantan Selatan.","en":"The proboscis monkey is the pride animal of South Kalimantan."},{"id":"Jumlahnya di Kalimantan Selatan naik menjadi sekitar 4.000 ekor!","en":"Their number in South Kalimantan rose to about 4,000!"}],"glossary":[{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan yang hidup hanya di satu tempat di dunia, seperti bekantan di Kalimantan.","def_en":"An animal that lives in only one place in the world, like the proboscis monkey in Borneo."},{"term":"Selaput","def_id":"Kulit tipis di sela jari kaki yang membantu bekantan berenang.","def_en":"Thin skin between the toes that helps the monkey swim."},{"term":"Katup","def_id":"Penutup kecil yang bisa membuka dan menutup, di sini menutup hidung saat menyelam.","def_en":"A little flap that can open and close, here to shut the nose when diving."},{"term":"Kelompok","def_id":"Sekumpulan bekantan yang hidup dan mencari makan bersama-sama.","def_en":"A group of proboscis monkeys that live and find food together."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e136b48c3214f29a.jpg","caption_id":"Wajah bekantan jantan dari dekat, dengan hidung besar dan panjang yang khas.","caption_en":"A close-up of a male proboscis monkey's face, with its big, long signature nose.","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/91931c7b866f4c18.jpg","caption_id":"Keluarga bekantan: jantan, betina, dan anak duduk bersama di tepi hutan.","caption_en":"A proboscis monkey family: a male, a female, and a young one sitting together at the forest edge.","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9361a077e9d3bc15.jpg","caption_id":"Bekantan jantan sedang makan, hidung panjangnya terlihat jelas dari samping.","caption_en":"A male proboscis monkey eating, its long nose clearly seen from the side.","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/585d5d0fc86c23e0.jpg","caption_id":"Bekantan muda dengan hidung yang masih kecil, memegang makanan dengan tangannya.","caption_en":"A young proboscis monkey with a still-small nose, holding food in its hand.","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/574c0804ed7e522c.jpg","caption_id":"Sekelompok bekantan bertengger di hutan bakau, rumah basah kesukaan mereka.","caption_en":"A group of proboscis monkeys perched in a mangrove forest, their favorite watery home.","credit":"Ade Putri Amelia Az-Zahra","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bekantan"},"ensiklopedia_bunga_bangkai":{"id":"ensiklopedia_bunga_bangkai","title_id":"Bunga Bangkai Raksasa","title_en":"Giant Corpse Flower","subtitle_id":"Bunga raksasa berbau busuk dari hutan Sumatra!","subtitle_en":"A giant smelly flower from Sumatra's forests!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan tropis Sumatra","value_en":"Sumatran tropical rainforest"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Tinggi","label_en":"Height","value_id":"Bisa lebih dari 3 meter","value_en":"Can be over 3 meters"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Mekar","label_en":"Bloom","value_id":"Hanya sekitar 7 hari","value_en":"Only about 7 days"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Kerinci & Lampung, Sumatra","value_en":"Kerinci & Lampung, Sumatra"},{"icon":"warning","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam (IUCN Red List)","value_en":"Threatened (IUCN Red List)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Bunga Bangkai?","h_en":"What Is the Corpse Flower?","body_id":"Bunga bangkai raksasa (Amorphophallus titanum) adalah tumbuhan dengan bunga majemuk terbesar di dunia. Bunga ini berasal dari Pulau Sumatra, Indonesia. Namanya 'bunga bangkai' karena baunya seperti bangkai yang busuk! Banyak orang mengira ia sama dengan Rafflesia, padahal keduanya tumbuhan yang berbeda.","body_en":"The giant corpse flower (Amorphophallus titanum) is the plant with the largest cluster of flowers in the world. It comes from the island of Sumatra in Indonesia. It is called the 'corpse flower' because it smells like rotting meat! Many people mix it up with the Rafflesia, but they are two different plants."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Bunga ini tumbuh di hutan hujan tropis Sumatra, seperti di Kerinci dan Lampung. Ia suka tanah berkapur dan tempat yang lembap di bawah pepohonan besar. Kamu juga bisa melihatnya mekar di Kebun Raya Bogor, Cibodas, dan Purwodadi.","body_en":"This flower grows in the tropical rainforests of Sumatra, like in Kerinci and Lampung. It likes limestone soil and damp, shady spots under tall trees. You can also see it bloom at the Bogor, Cibodas, and Purwodadi Botanical Gardens."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Bunga bangkai bisa tumbuh sangat tinggi, bahkan lebih tinggi dari orang dewasa! Bagian tengahnya yang menjulang disebut spadix, dikelilingi seludang besar berwarna merah hati dan hijau. Di bawah tanah ada umbi raksasa yang menyimpan makanannya, dan bijinya berwarna merah.","body_en":"The corpse flower can grow very tall, even taller than a grown-up! Its tall middle part is called the spadix, surrounded by a big leafy spathe that is dark red and green. Underground there is a giant tuber that stores its food, and its seeds are red."},{"icon":"schedule","h_id":"Kapan Mekar & Baunya","h_en":"When It Blooms & Its Smell","body_id":"Bunga ini sangat sabar! Ia menyimpan makanan di umbinya selama bertahun-tahun, lalu mekar hanya sekitar 7 hari saja. Saat mekar, bunga betinanya siap lebih dulu, baru bunga jantannya, agar tidak menyerbuki diri sendiri. Bau busuknya mengundang kumbang dan lalat untuk membantu menyerbukinya.","body_en":"This flower is very patient! It stores food in its tuber for years, then blooms for only about 7 days. When it blooms, its female flowers are ready first and the male flowers later, so it does not pollinate itself. Its stinky smell invites beetles and flies to help pollinate it."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Bunga bangkai liar makin sedikit karena hutannya berubah menjadi kebun dan rumah. Burung rangkong membantu menyebar bijinya. Dengan menjaga hutan dan burung rangkong, kita bisa membantu bunga ajaib ini tetap mekar untuk anak-anak masa depan.","body_en":"Wild corpse flowers are getting rarer because their forests are turning into farms and houses. Hornbill birds help spread their seeds. By protecting the forest and the hornbills, we can help this amazing flower keep blooming for children of the future."}],"facts":[{"id":"Ini adalah bunga majemuk terbesar di dunia!","en":"It is the largest cluster of flowers in the world!"},{"id":"Baunya seperti daging busuk untuk menarik lalat dan kumbang.","en":"It smells like rotten meat to attract flies and beetles."},{"id":"Bunganya hanya mekar sekitar 7 hari saja.","en":"Its flower blooms for only about 7 days."},{"id":"Umbinya bisa seberat 100 kilogram di bawah tanah!","en":"Its underground tuber can weigh up to 100 kilograms!"},{"id":"Bunga ini bisa tunggu bertahun-tahun sebelum mekar.","en":"This flower can wait for years before it blooms."},{"id":"Tumbuhan ini hanya ada di Indonesia.","en":"This plant is found only in Indonesia."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Spadix","def_id":"Bagian tengah bunga yang menjulang tinggi seperti tongkol.","def_en":"The tall central part of the flower that rises up like a spike."},{"term":"Seludang","def_id":"Kelopak besar yang membungkus dan melindungi bunga saat mekar.","def_en":"The big leafy hood that wraps around and protects the flower as it opens."},{"term":"Umbi","def_id":"Bagian gemuk di bawah tanah tempat tumbuhan menyimpan makanan.","def_en":"The thick underground part where the plant stores its food."},{"term":"Penyerbukan","def_id":"Cara bunga membuat biji dengan bantuan serangga yang memindahkan serbuk sari.","def_en":"How a flower makes seeds with the help of insects that move pollen."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f726ea8c7f07ce2d.jpg","caption_id":"Bunga bangkai mekar penuh, seludang merah hatinya terbuka lebar mengelilingi spadix yang menjulang.","caption_en":"A corpse flower in full bloom, its dark-red spathe wide open around the towering spadix.","credit":"Credits: US Botanic Garden.","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e00355769094147e.jpg","caption_id":"Bunga raksasa ini berdiri lebih tinggi dari seorang penjaga di sebelahnya, menunjukkan betapa besarnya.","caption_en":"This giant flower stands taller than a guard beside it, showing just how huge it is.","credit":"Shubert Ciencia from Nueva Ecija, Philippines","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a62a3929167cadac.jpg","caption_id":"Pada fase daun, tumbuhan ini tumbuh seperti pohon kecil berbatang tunggal sebelum kelak berbunga.","caption_en":"In its leaf phase, the plant grows like a small single-stemmed tree before it later flowers.","credit":"Steve Fitzgerald","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c4896d72d51fd585.jpg","caption_id":"Dekat dari pangkalnya, terlihat kuncup-kuncup bunga kecil menempel di dasar spadix yang kuning.","caption_en":"Up close at the base, tiny flower buds cluster around the bottom of the yellow spadix.","credit":"Björn S...","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3048cd57126f2150.jpg","caption_id":"Tiga orang dengan susah payah mengangkat umbi raksasa bunga ini yang beratnya lebih dari 100 kg.","caption_en":"Three people carefully lift the flower's giant tuber, which weighs more than 100 kg.","credit":"Foto © W. Barthlott","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bunga_bangkai_raksasa"},"ensiklopedia_burung_maleo_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_burung_maleo_1","title_id":"Burung Maleo","title_en":"Maleo Bird","subtitle_id":"Burung unik yang menetaskan telur dari panas bumi!","subtitle_en":"A unique bird that hatches eggs with earth's heat!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan tropis & pantai Sulawesi","value_en":"Sulawesi forests & beaches"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Sebesar ayam, sekitar 55 cm","value_en":"Chicken-sized, about 55 cm"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Buah, biji & serangga kecil","value_en":"Fruits, seeds & small insects"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Hanya Pulau Sulawesi","value_en":"Only Sulawesi Island"},{"icon":"category","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Burung megapoda","value_en":"Megapode birds"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam & dilindungi","value_en":"Threatened & protected"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Burung Maleo?","h_en":"What Is the Maleo Bird?","body_id":"Maleo (Macrocephalon maleo) adalah burung istimewa yang juga disebut kalkun sikat. Ia termasuk kelompok burung megapoda. Maleo senkawor hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia, dan tidak ada di tempat lain di dunia.","body_en":"The maleo (Macrocephalon maleo) is a special bird also called the brush-turkey. It belongs to a group of birds called megapodes. The maleo lives only on the island of Sulawesi, Indonesia, and nowhere else in the world."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Maleo tinggal di hutan tropis Sulawesi. Mereka suka pergi ke pantai berpasir atau tanah hangat dekat sumber panas bumi. Tempat hangat ini sangat penting untuk telur-telur mereka.","body_en":"The maleo lives in the tropical forests of Sulawesi. They like to go to sandy beaches or warm ground near volcanic hot spots. These warm places are very important for their eggs."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Maleo punya bulu hitam, dada putih kemerahan, dan ciri khas berupa benjolan keras di kepalanya. Benjolan ini membuatnya terlihat seperti memakai topi! Kakinya kuat untuk menggali tanah dan pasir.","body_en":"The maleo has black feathers, a pinkish-white chest, and a special hard bump on its head. This bump makes it look like it is wearing a hat! Its legs are strong for digging in soil and sand."},{"icon":"egg","h_id":"Telur Ajaib","h_en":"Magic Eggs","body_id":"Maleo tidak mengerami telurnya sendiri. Ia mengubur telur di pasir hangat atau tanah dekat panas bumi, lalu panas alam itu yang menetaskannya! Telur maleo sangat besar, jauh lebih besar dari telur ayam.","body_en":"The maleo does not sit on its eggs. It buries them in warm sand or soil near volcanic heat, and nature's warmth hatches them! Maleo eggs are very big, much larger than chicken eggs."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Burung maleo terancam karena telurnya sering diambil dan hutannya berkurang. Anak maleo harus mandiri sejak menetas. Dengan menjaga sarang dan hutan Sulawesi, kita bisa membantu burung unik ini tetap ada.","body_en":"The maleo bird is threatened because its eggs are often taken and its forests are shrinking. Baby maleos must take care of themselves from the moment they hatch. By protecting their nests and Sulawesi's forests, we can help this unique bird survive."}],"facts":[{"id":"Maleo hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia!","en":"The maleo lives only on Sulawesi Island, Indonesia!"},{"id":"Mereka menetaskan telur memakai panas bumi dan matahari.","en":"They hatch eggs using the heat of the earth and sun."},{"id":"Telur maleo jauh lebih besar daripada telur ayam.","en":"Maleo eggs are much bigger than chicken eggs."},{"id":"Anak maleo bisa langsung terbang dan mencari makan sendiri.","en":"Baby maleos can fly and find food on their own right away."},{"id":"Maleo punya benjolan keras seperti topi di kepalanya.","en":"The maleo has a hard, hat-like bump on its head."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Megapoda","def_id":"Kelompok burung berkaki besar yang mengubur telurnya agar menetas oleh panas alam.","def_en":"A group of big-footed birds that bury their eggs so nature's heat can hatch them."},{"term":"Mengerami","def_id":"Mendekap telur dengan tubuh agar tetap hangat sampai menetas; maleo justru tidak melakukannya.","def_en":"Sitting on eggs with the body to keep them warm until they hatch; the maleo does not do this."},{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan yang hanya hidup di satu daerah saja, seperti maleo di Sulawesi.","def_en":"An animal that lives in only one area, like the maleo in Sulawesi."},{"term":"Panas bumi","def_id":"Panas alami yang keluar dari dalam tanah, misalnya dekat gunung berapi.","def_en":"Natural heat that comes out of the ground, such as near a volcano."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/fddc7ccf6df38c39.jpg","caption_id":"Maleo berjalan di tanah berpasir, memperlihatkan tubuh hitam, perut merah jambu, dan benjolan keras di kepalanya.","caption_en":"A maleo walks on sandy ground, showing its black body, pinkish belly, and the hard bump on its head.","credit":"Jean-Paul Boerekamps","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9896525663b797d0.jpg","caption_id":"Berdiri tegak di rerumputan, maleo menunjukkan kaki kuat dan wajah kuning oranye khasnya.","caption_en":"Standing tall in the grass, the maleo shows its strong legs and trademark orange-yellow face.","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/abe550888eb52d60.jpg","caption_id":"Dari samping terlihat jelas benjolan hitam di kepala dan dada merah jambu burung maleo.","caption_en":"From the side you can clearly see the maleo's black head bump and pinkish chest.","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/1c5a3301bc8d33af.jpg","caption_id":"Maleo mencari makan di antara rumput hijau yang basah oleh embun pagi.","caption_en":"A maleo forages among green grass still wet with morning dew.","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maleo"},"ensiklopedia_candi_borobudur_2":{"id":"ensiklopedia_candi_borobudur_2","title_id":"Candi Borobudur","title_en":"Borobudur Temple","subtitle_id":"Candi Buddha terbesar di dunia!","subtitle_en":"The biggest Buddhist temple in the world!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Lokasi","label_en":"Location","value_id":"Magelang, Jawa Tengah","value_en":"Magelang, Central Java"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Dibangun","label_en":"Built","value_id":"Sekitar tahun 800-an M","value_en":"Around the 800s CE"},{"icon":"self_improvement","label_id":"Agama","label_en":"Religion","value_id":"Buddha Mahayana","value_en":"Mahayana Buddhism"},{"icon":"account_balance","label_id":"Bentuk","label_en":"Design","value_id":"6 teras persegi & 3 pelataran bundar","value_en":"6 square terraces & 3 round platforms"},{"icon":"filter_drama","label_id":"Stupa","label_en":"Stupas","value_id":"72 stupa berlubang + 1 stupa utama","value_en":"72 holed stupas + 1 main stupa"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Warisan Dunia UNESCO","value_en":"UNESCO World Heritage"}],"sections":[{"icon":"account_balance","h_id":"Apa Itu Borobudur?","h_en":"What Is Borobudur?","body_id":"Borobudur adalah candi Buddha raksasa di Pulau Jawa, Indonesia. Candi ini adalah candi Buddha terbesar di seluruh dunia! Bentuknya seperti gunung batu bertingkat dengan banyak stupa berbentuk lonceng di puncaknya. Kita patut bangga karena bangunan menakjubkan ini ada di negeri kita.","body_en":"Borobudur is a giant Buddhist temple on the island of Java, Indonesia. It is the biggest Buddhist temple in the whole world! It looks like a stepped stone mountain with many bell-shaped stupas at the top. We can be proud that this amazing building stands in our country."},{"icon":"history_edu","h_id":"Siapa yang Membangunnya?","h_en":"Who Built It?","body_id":"Borobudur dibangun lebih dari 1.200 tahun yang lalu, sekitar tahun 800-an Masehi. Yang membangunnya adalah para penganut agama Buddha pada masa wangsa Syailendra. Candi ini terletak di Magelang, Jawa Tengah, tak jauh dari Kota Yogyakarta. Membangunnya butuh waktu bertahun-tahun dan ribuan batu yang disusun rapi.","body_en":"Borobudur was built more than 1,200 years ago, around the 800s CE. It was built by Buddhists during the time of the Sailendra dynasty. The temple sits in Magelang, Central Java, not far from the city of Yogyakarta. Building it took many years and thousands of carefully stacked stones."},{"icon":"auto_stories","h_id":"Cerita di Dindingnya","h_en":"Stories on Its Walls","body_id":"Dinding Borobudur dihiasi 2.672 panel relief, yaitu gambar yang dipahat pada batu. Relief ini bercerita tentang ajaran Buddha, seperti buku batu raksasa! Dahulu ada 504 patung Buddha di candi ini. Di puncaknya, 72 patung Buddha duduk bersila di dalam stupa berlubang seperti lonceng.","body_en":"Borobudur's walls are decorated with 2,672 relief panels, which are pictures carved into stone. These carvings tell stories from the Buddha's teachings, like a giant stone book! Long ago there were 504 Buddha statues here. At the top, 72 Buddha statues sit cross-legged inside holed, bell-shaped stupas."},{"icon":"hiking","h_id":"Tempat untuk Berziarah","h_en":"A Place for Pilgrimage","body_id":"Borobudur dibuat sebagai tempat suci untuk berziarah. Peziarah masuk dari sisi timur, lalu berjalan mengelilingi candi searah jarum jam sambil naik ke tingkat berikutnya. Naik dari bawah ke atas melambangkan perjalanan menuju kebijaksanaan. Setiap tahun umat Buddha berkumpul di sini untuk merayakan Hari Waisak.","body_en":"Borobudur was made as a holy place for pilgrimage. Pilgrims enter from the east, then walk around the temple clockwise while climbing to the next level. Going from the bottom to the top stands for a journey toward wisdom. Every year Buddhists gather here to celebrate Vesak Day."},{"icon":"construction","h_id":"Ditemukan & Dirawat Kembali","h_en":"Found and Cared For Again","body_id":"Borobudur pernah ditinggalkan dan tertutup tanah serta tanaman selama ratusan tahun. Pada tahun 1814, candi ini ditemukan kembali dan mulai dibersihkan. Pemerintah Indonesia dan UNESCO memperbaikinya besar-besaran pada tahun 1975 sampai 1982. Sekarang Borobudur dijaga sebagai Warisan Dunia agar bisa dinikmati anak cucu kita.","body_en":"Borobudur was once abandoned and covered by soil and plants for hundreds of years. In 1814, the temple was found again and people began cleaning it. The Indonesian government and UNESCO repaired it in a big project from 1975 to 1982. Today Borobudur is protected as a World Heritage site so our grandchildren can enjoy it too."}],"facts":[{"id":"Borobudur adalah candi Buddha terbesar di dunia!","en":"Borobudur is the biggest Buddhist temple in the world!"},{"id":"Dindingnya punya 2.672 panel relief, koleksi relief Buddha terlengkap di dunia.","en":"Its walls have 2,672 relief panels, the most complete collection of Buddhist reliefs in the world."},{"id":"Di puncaknya ada 72 stupa berlubang, masing-masing berisi satu patung Buddha.","en":"At the top are 72 holed stupas, each holding one Buddha statue."},{"id":"Candi ini dibangun lebih dari 1.200 tahun yang lalu tanpa semen.","en":"The temple was built more than 1,200 years ago without any cement."},{"id":"Borobudur sempat hilang dan tertutup tanah, lalu ditemukan lagi tahun 1814.","en":"Borobudur was once lost under soil, then found again in 1814."},{"id":"Borobudur adalah tempat wisata yang paling banyak dikunjungi di Indonesia.","en":"Borobudur is the most visited tourist spot in Indonesia."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Candi","def_id":"Bangunan suci dari batu peninggalan zaman Hindu-Buddha di Nusantara.","def_en":"A stone holy building left from the Hindu-Buddhist era in the Indonesian islands."},{"term":"Stupa","def_id":"Bangunan berbentuk lonceng atau kubah yang suci dalam agama Buddha.","def_en":"A bell- or dome-shaped structure that is holy in Buddhism."},{"term":"Relief","def_id":"Gambar atau cerita yang dipahat timbul pada permukaan batu.","def_en":"A picture or story carved so it stands out on a stone surface."},{"term":"Ziarah","def_id":"Kunjungan ke tempat suci untuk berdoa dan beribadah.","def_en":"A visit to a holy place to pray and worship."},{"term":"Waisak","def_id":"Hari raya umat Buddha yang dirayakan setiap tahun di Borobudur.","def_en":"A Buddhist holy day celebrated every year at Borobudur."},{"term":"Warisan Dunia","def_id":"Tempat istimewa yang dilindungi UNESCO untuk seluruh umat manusia.","def_en":"A special place protected by UNESCO for all of humanity."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/be4bf279d82901a3.jpg","caption_id":"Para biksu dan peziarah berbaju putih berjalan mengelilingi Borobudur, persis seperti ritual ziarah.","caption_en":"Monks and white-robed pilgrims walk around Borobudur, just like the pilgrimage ritual.","credit":"Heri nugroho","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/8d64b52a927e9f09.jpg","caption_id":"Stupa-stupa Borobudur saat fajar, dengan Gunung Merapi mengepulkan asap di kejauhan.","caption_en":"Borobudur's stupas at dawn, with Mount Merapi puffing smoke in the distance.","credit":"ctsnow","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/4c76caf7d05112a1.jpg","caption_id":"Stupa berlubang seperti lonceng di teras atas, menghadap bukit hijau dan pohon kelapa.","caption_en":"Holed, bell-shaped stupas on the upper terrace, facing green hills and coconut trees.","credit":"Heaven's Army (uploader at EN.Wikipedia)","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6beb87baaa96d37c.jpg","caption_id":"Borobudur terlihat dari kejauhan, dikelilingi hutan rimbun dan perbukitan.","caption_en":"Borobudur seen from afar, surrounded by lush forest and rolling hills.","credit":"Gunkarta (en.wikipedia)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/401e6f0d2546f4f2.jpg","caption_id":"Lukisan lama menggambarkan orang berziarah ke Borobudur dengan gajah dan payung warna-warni.","caption_en":"An old painting shows people making a pilgrimage to Borobudur with elephants and colorful parasols.","credit":"Gijsbert Brandt Hooijer (1848-1934)","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/32d1ddcf8e637aa0.jpg","caption_id":"Foto hitam-putih tertua Borobudur, diambil tak lama setelah candi ditemukan kembali.","caption_en":"A very old black-and-white photo of Borobudur, taken not long after the temple was rediscovered.","credit":"Isidore van Kinsbergen","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Borobudur"},"ensiklopedia_cendrawasih":{"id":"ensiklopedia_cendrawasih","title_id":"Cendrawasih","title_en":"Bird-of-Paradise","subtitle_id":"Burung surga cantik dari tanah Papua!","subtitle_en":"The beautiful bird of paradise from Papua!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan tropis Papua","value_en":"Papuan tropical rainforest"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Burung pengicau kecil-sedang","value_en":"Small-to-medium songbird"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Buah-buahan & serangga kecil","value_en":"Fruits & small insects"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Papua & pulau sekitarnya","value_en":"Papua & nearby islands"},{"icon":"category","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Famili Paradisaeidae","value_en":"Family Paradisaeidae"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Dilindungi","value_en":"Protected"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Cendrawasih?","h_en":"What Is the Bird-of-Paradise?","body_id":"Cendrawasih adalah burung pengicau cantik dari keluarga Paradisaeidae. Banyak orang menyebutnya 'burung surga' karena bulunya yang indah dan berwarna-warni. Ada banyak jenisnya, seperti cendrawasih merah, kuning, raja, kaisar, dan raggiana.","body_en":"The bird-of-paradise is a beautiful songbird from the Paradisaeidae family. Many people call it the 'bird of heaven' because of its lovely, colorful feathers. There are many kinds, like the red, yellow, king, emperor, and raggiana birds-of-paradise."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Cendrawasih hidup di hutan-hutan lebat di Papua, Indonesia, dan pulau-pulau di sekitarnya. Mereka suka tinggal tinggi di atas pepohonan hutan hujan tropis. Karena keindahannya, burung ini menjadi kebanggaan tanah Papua dan namanya dipakai untuk teluk serta universitas di sana.","body_en":"Birds-of-paradise live in the thick forests of Papua, Indonesia, and nearby islands. They like to stay high up in the trees of the tropical rainforest. Because of their beauty, these birds are the pride of Papua, and their name is even used for a bay and a university there."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Cendrawasih jantan memiliki bulu yang sangat indah dengan warna-warna cerah seperti merah, kuning, dan hijau. Beberapa punya bulu panjang yang menjuntai seperti pita atau kawat. Bulu cantik ini hanya dimiliki oleh burung jantan; betinanya berwarna lebih kalem.","body_en":"Male birds-of-paradise have very beautiful feathers in bright colors like red, yellow, and green. Some have long feathers that flow like ribbons or wires. These lovely feathers belong only to the male birds; the females have plainer colors."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kebiasaan Menari","h_en":"Their Dancing Habit","body_id":"Cendrawasih jantan suka menari untuk menarik perhatian betina! Mereka memamerkan bulu indahnya sambil bergoyang di atas dahan. Mereka memakan buah-buahan dan serangga kecil di hutan.","body_en":"Male birds-of-paradise love to dance to attract the females! They show off their beautiful feathers while swaying on the branches. They eat fruits and small insects in the forest."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Cendrawasih harus kita jaga agar tidak punah. Mereka terancam karena hutan tempat tinggalnya berkurang dan perburuan bulunya. Dengan menjaga hutan Papua, kita membantu burung surga ini terus terbang bebas dan menari.","body_en":"We must protect birds-of-paradise so they do not disappear. They are threatened because their forest homes are shrinking and people hunt them for their feathers. By protecting Papua's forests, we help these heavenly birds keep flying free and dancing."}],"facts":[{"id":"Cendrawasih dijuluki 'burung surga' karena keindahannya.","en":"The bird-of-paradise is nicknamed the 'bird of heaven' for its beauty."},{"id":"Burung jantan menari untuk memikat pasangannya.","en":"Male birds dance to win a partner."},{"id":"Hanya burung jantan yang punya bulu hias super cantik.","en":"Only the male birds have super pretty show feathers."},{"id":"Cendrawasih adalah lambang kebanggaan tanah Papua.","en":"The bird-of-paradise is a symbol of pride for Papua."},{"id":"Ada belasan jenis cendrawasih di Indonesia.","en":"There are over a dozen kinds of birds-of-paradise in Indonesia."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Paradisaeidae","def_id":"Nama keluarga ilmiah untuk semua jenis burung cendrawasih.","def_en":"The scientific family name for all kinds of birds-of-paradise."},{"term":"Pengicau","def_id":"Kelompok burung yang pandai bersuara dan berkicau, seperti cendrawasih.","def_en":"A group of birds that are good at singing and chirping, like the bird-of-paradise."},{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan atau tumbuhan yang hanya hidup di satu daerah tertentu saja.","def_en":"An animal or plant that lives only in one particular area."},{"term":"Punah","def_id":"Keadaan ketika suatu jenis hewan habis dan tidak ada lagi di dunia.","def_en":"When a kind of animal runs out and no longer exists in the world."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/47ba731e94dfca1a.jpg","caption_id":"Cendrawasih jantan bertengger gagah, memamerkan bulu cokelat keemasan dan ekor putih panjang yang menjuntai.","caption_en":"A male bird-of-paradise perches proudly, showing off its golden-brown plumage and long flowing white tail.","credit":"Philip Nalangan","license":"CC BY 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cenderawasih_%28disambiguasi%29"},"ensiklopedia_gajah_sumatra":{"id":"ensiklopedia_gajah_sumatra","title_id":"Gajah Sumatra","title_en":"Sumatran Elephant","subtitle_id":"Mamalia terbesar dan tercerdas di Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"Indonesia's biggest and smartest mammal!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan rawa & dataran rendah","value_en":"Swamp & lowland forests"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Setinggi 3,5 m, sampai 6 ton","value_en":"Up to 3.5 m tall, 6 tons"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Herbivora: rumput, daun, kulit kayu","value_en":"Herbivore: grass, leaves, bark"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Hanya Pulau Sumatra","value_en":"Only Sumatra Island"},{"icon":"category","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Subspesies gajah Asia","value_en":"Asian elephant subspecies"},{"icon":"warning","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Sangat terancam punah","value_en":"Critically endangered"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Gajah Sumatra?","h_en":"What Is the Sumatran Elephant?","body_id":"Gajah sumatra (Elephas maximus sumatranus) adalah jenis gajah Asia yang hanya hidup di Pulau Sumatra. Ia adalah mamalia terbesar di Indonesia! Tubuhnya sedikit lebih kecil daripada gajah dari India, dan biasanya hanya gajah jantan yang punya gading.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant (Elephas maximus sumatranus) is a kind of Asian elephant that lives only on the island of Sumatra. It is the biggest mammal in Indonesia! Its body is a little smaller than the elephant from India, and usually only the males have tusks."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Gajah sumatra hidup di hutan-hutan luas, seperti hutan rawa, hutan gambut, dan hutan hujan dataran rendah. Mereka butuh wilayah jelajah yang sangat luas untuk berkeliling, dan satu gajah saja bisa butuh ratusan hektar. Mereka juga suka tempat yang dekat dengan sumber air.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant lives in wide forests, like swamp forests, peat forests, and lowland rainforests. They need a very large area to roam around, and a single elephant can need hundreds of hectares. They also like places close to water."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Gajah sumatra bisa setinggi 3,5 meter di bahu dan beratnya mencapai beberapa ton! Telinganya yang besar membantunya mendengar dan menjaga tubuh tetap sejuk. Belalainya yang panjang dipakai untuk meraih makanan dan air seperti tangan.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant can be 3.5 meters tall at the shoulder and weigh several tons! Its big ears help it hear well and keep its body cool. Its long trunk is used to grab food and water like a hand."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Gajah sumatra adalah herbivora, jadi ia hanya makan tumbuhan! Ia suka rumput, semak muda, daun, dan kulit kayu yang lembut, dan bisa makan sampai 200 kg sehari. Gajah sangat cerdas dan punya otak besar. Bayi gajah dikandung selama 22 bulan sebelum lahir.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant is a herbivore, so it eats only plants! It likes grass, young shrubs, leaves, and soft bark, and can eat up to 200 kg a day. Elephants are very smart and have a big brain. A baby elephant grows for 22 months before it is born."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Gajah sumatra sangat terancam punah karena hutannya banyak berubah menjadi perkebunan. Gajah penting sekali karena membantu menyebarkan biji tanaman di hutan. Dengan menjaga hutan dan hidup damai bersama gajah, kita bisa menyelamatkan sahabat raksasa ini.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant is highly endangered because much of its forest has been turned into plantations. Elephants are very important because they help spread plant seeds in the forest. By protecting the forest and living peacefully with elephants, we can save this giant friend."}],"facts":[{"id":"Gajah sumatra adalah mamalia terbesar di Indonesia!","en":"The Sumatran elephant is the biggest mammal in Indonesia!"},{"id":"Otaknya lebih besar dari mamalia darat lainnya.","en":"Its brain is bigger than other land mammals'."},{"id":"Bayi gajah dikandung selama 22 bulan, hampir 2 tahun!","en":"A baby elephant grows for 22 months, almost 2 years!"},{"id":"Gajah bisa hidup sampai sekitar 70 tahun.","en":"Elephants can live up to about 70 years."},{"id":"Gajah membantu menanam hutan dengan menyebar biji.","en":"Elephants help grow forests by spreading seeds."},{"id":"Belalai gajah dipakai seperti tangan untuk meraup makanan.","en":"An elephant's trunk works like a hand to scoop up food."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Subspesies","def_id":"Kelompok khusus di dalam satu jenis hewan; gajah sumatra adalah subspesies gajah Asia.","def_en":"A special group within one kind of animal; the Sumatran elephant is a subspecies of the Asian elephant."},{"term":"Herbivora","def_id":"Hewan yang hanya makan tumbuhan dan tidak makan daging.","def_en":"An animal that eats only plants and no meat."},{"term":"Belalai","def_id":"Hidung panjang gajah yang dipakai seperti tangan untuk meraih makanan dan air.","def_en":"An elephant's long nose, used like a hand to reach food and water."},{"term":"Wilayah jelajah","def_id":"Daerah luas tempat hewan berkeliling untuk mencari makan dan air.","def_en":"The wide area an animal roams around to find food and water."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/990889d90c287246.jpg","caption_id":"Gajah sumatra jantan bergading berdiri di sungai, dengan hutan hijau di belakangnya.","caption_en":"A tusked male Sumatran elephant stands in a river, with green forest behind it.","credit":"Léodras","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/22f9acabeae4d8b6.jpg","caption_id":"Induk gajah menjaga anaknya yang masih kecil di tepi hutan Taman Nasional Tesso Nilo.","caption_en":"A mother elephant watches over her little calf at the edge of Tesso Nilo National Park.","credit":"Afrianto silalahi","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/88199b85ba995c0c.jpg","caption_id":"Gajah berenang di sungai hijau jernih, telinganya yang besar terkembang lebar.","caption_en":"An elephant bathes in a clear green river, its big ears spread wide.","credit":"kusuma wijaya","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/46667cb5f2bff657.jpg","caption_id":"Manusia dan gajah bermain air bersama di sungai, contoh hidup damai berdampingan.","caption_en":"People and elephants splash together in a river, a picture of peaceful coexistence.","credit":"Panyahatan Siregar","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gajah_sumatra"},"ensiklopedia_harimau_sumatra_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_harimau_sumatra_1","title_id":"Harimau Sumatra","title_en":"Sumatran Tiger","subtitle_id":"Kucing besar penjaga hutan Pulau Sumatra","subtitle_en":"The big cat guarding Sumatra's forests","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan dataran rendah sampai pegunungan","value_en":"Lowland to mountain forests"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Jantan sampai 250 cm, berat ~140 kg","value_en":"Males up to 250 cm, about 140 kg"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Babi hutan, rusa, unggas, kadang ikan","value_en":"Wild boar, deer, birds, sometimes fish"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Hanya di Pulau Sumatra, Indonesia","value_en":"Only on Sumatra island, Indonesia"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Kritis, tinggal sekitar 400-500 ekor","value_en":"Critically endangered, about 400-500 left"},{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Kucing besar (Panthera tigris)","value_en":"Big cat (Panthera tigris)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Harimau Sumatra?","h_en":"What Is the Sumatran Tiger?","body_id":"Harimau sumatra adalah kucing besar yang hanya hidup di Pulau Sumatra, Indonesia. Ia adalah harimau paling kecil di antara semua jenis harimau di dunia. Tubuhnya yang mungil membuatnya gesit menjelajahi hutan. Ia satu-satunya harimau sunda yang masih hidup sampai sekarang, jadi sangat istimewa.","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger is a big cat that lives only on the island of Sumatra, Indonesia. It is the smallest of all tiger types in the world. Its small body makes it quick and nimble in the forest. It is the only Sunda tiger still alive today, which makes it very special."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Harimau sumatra tinggal di hutan-hutan Pulau Sumatra. Ia bisa hidup di hutan dataran rendah, lahan gambut, sampai hutan hujan di pegunungan. Banyak yang tinggal di taman nasional dan cagar alam yang dilindungi. Di jari-jarinya ada selaput, jadi ia juga pandai berenang!","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger lives in the forests of Sumatra island. It can live in lowland forests, peat swamps, and rainforests high in the mountains. Many live in protected national parks and nature reserves. It has webbing between its toes, so it is also a great swimmer!"},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Bulu harimau sumatra berwarna oranye tua dengan garis hitam yang lebar dan rapat. Warnanya paling gelap di antara semua harimau di dunia. Harimau jantan punya lebih banyak janggut dan surai di wajahnya. Loreng ini membantunya bersembunyi di balik bayang-bayang hutan, seperti pakaian penyamaran.","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger's fur is deep orange with wide, close-set black stripes. Its color is the darkest of all tigers in the world. Males have more beard and mane around the face. These stripes help it hide among the forest shadows, like a camouflage suit."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Harimau sumatra adalah pemburu yang sabar dan pandai. Ia memakan babi hutan, rusa, kijang, unggas, dan kadang ikan. Sebagai pemangsa utama, ia menjaga jumlah hewan lain di hutan tetap seimbang. Induk harimau biasanya melahirkan 2 atau 3 anak yang sangat lucu dan dijaga dengan penuh kasih.","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger is a patient and clever hunter. It eats wild boar, deer, muntjac, birds, and sometimes fish. As a top predator, it keeps the number of other animals in the forest balanced. A mother tiger usually has 2 or 3 adorable cubs that she cares for lovingly."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Harimau sumatra sangat langka, hanya tersisa sekitar 400-500 ekor di alam liar. Hutannya makin sempit karena ditebang untuk ladang dan kebun, sehingga ia sulit mencari rumah. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga hutan tetap lestari dan hijau. Dengan kerja sama, harimau gagah ini bisa terus hidup bahagia!","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger is very rare, with only about 400-500 left in the wild. Its forest is shrinking because it is cleared for fields and plantations, making it hard to find a home. We can help by keeping forests healthy and green. Working together, this brave tiger can keep living happily!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Harimau sumatra adalah harimau terkecil di dunia!","en":"The Sumatran tiger is the smallest tiger in the world!"},{"id":"Warna bulunya paling gelap di antara semua harimau.","en":"Its fur is the darkest of all tigers."},{"id":"Ada selaput di jari kakinya supaya bisa berenang cepat.","en":"It has webbed toes so it can swim fast."},{"id":"Loreng setiap harimau berbeda, seperti sidik jari manusia.","en":"Every tiger's stripes are unique, like a human fingerprint."},{"id":"Di alam liar, harimau sumatra bisa hidup sampai 15 tahun.","en":"In the wild, a Sumatran tiger can live up to 15 years."},{"id":"Anak harimau baru membuka matanya pada hari kesepuluh.","en":"Tiger cubs open their eyes on the tenth day."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan atau tumbuhan yang hanya hidup di satu tempat khusus di dunia.","def_en":"An animal or plant that lives in only one special place in the world."},{"term":"Pemangsa utama","def_id":"Hewan pemburu di puncak rantai makanan yang tidak diburu hewan lain.","def_en":"A top hunter at the head of the food chain that no other animal hunts."},{"term":"Kritis (terancam punah)","def_id":"Keadaan saat hewan sangat langka dan bisa hilang selamanya jika tidak dijaga.","def_en":"When an animal is very rare and could disappear forever unless it is protected."},{"term":"Habitat","def_id":"Tempat alami sebuah hewan tinggal, mencari makan, dan berkembang biak.","def_en":"The natural place where an animal lives, finds food, and raises its young."},{"term":"Kamuflase","def_id":"Warna atau pola tubuh yang membantu hewan menyatu dengan sekitarnya.","def_en":"Body colors or patterns that help an animal blend into its surroundings."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2ea82aae5a4338e2.jpg","caption_id":"Harimau sumatra menatap dengan tenang sambil berbaring, memperlihatkan wajah dan loreng yang khas.","caption_en":"A Sumatran tiger gazes calmly while resting, showing its distinctive face and stripes.","credit":"Nichollas Harrison","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5e0df62e7237ee3e.jpg","caption_id":"Tubuh harimau yang gagah terlihat penuh saat ia berjalan di atas batu, lorengnya lebar dan rapat.","caption_en":"The tiger's powerful body is shown in full as it walks across the rocks, its stripes wide and close-set.","credit":"Captain Herbert","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3deabfd4d2601a73.jpg","caption_id":"Wajah harimau dari dekat memperlihatkan kumis panjang dan janggut tebal khas harimau sumatra.","caption_en":"A close-up of the tiger's face shows the long whiskers and thick beard typical of the Sumatran tiger.","credit":"Moonlight0551 from Australia","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5c5afa2d73eaab29.jpg","caption_id":"Seekor harimau sumatra melangkah di tanah terbuka dekat tepi hutan, gesit dan waspada.","caption_en":"A Sumatran tiger steps across open ground near the forest edge, nimble and alert.","credit":"Official Website of Ministry of Environment and Forestry Indonesia","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harimau_sumatra"},"ensiklopedia_hiu_paus":{"id":"ensiklopedia_hiu_paus","title_id":"Hiu Paus","title_en":"Whale Shark","subtitle_id":"Ikan terbesar di dunia yang ramah","subtitle_en":"The world's biggest, friendliest fish","data_card":[{"icon":"waves","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Lautan tropis yang hangat","value_en":"Warm tropical oceans"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Rata-rata ~9,7 meter, berat sampai 9 ton","value_en":"About 9.7 meters long, up to 9 tons"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Plankton dan makhluk laut kecil","value_en":"Plankton and tiny sea creatures"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Samudra tropis dunia, termasuk Indonesia","value_en":"Tropical seas worldwide, including Indonesia"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam, sering terjerat jaring nelayan","value_en":"Threatened, often caught in fishing nets"},{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Ikan hiu (Rhincodon typus)","value_en":"Shark fish (Rhincodon typus)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"waves","h_id":"Apa Itu Hiu Paus?","h_en":"What Is the Whale Shark?","body_id":"Hiu paus adalah ikan terbesar di seluruh dunia! Walaupun namanya hiu, ia lembut dan tidak berbahaya bagi manusia. Ia disebut hiu paus karena tubuhnya besar dan cara makannya menyaring air laut seperti paus. Di Indonesia ia juga dipanggil hiu tutul atau geger lintang karena punggungnya bertotol seperti bintang.","body_en":"The whale shark is the biggest fish in the whole world! Even though it is a shark, it is gentle and harmless to people. It is called a whale shark because of its huge body and the way it eats by filtering seawater, just like a whale. In Indonesia it is also called 'hiu tutul' or 'geger lintang' because of the star-like spots on its back."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Hiu paus berenang di lautan tropis yang hangat di seluruh dunia. Ia suka mengembara jauh dan termasuk ikan yang suka bermigrasi. Di Indonesia, hiu paus bisa ditemui di banyak tempat penyelaman yang indah. Ia bahkan bisa menyelam sangat dalam, lebih dari 1.000 meter ke dasar laut!","body_en":"The whale shark swims in warm, tropical oceans all around the world. It loves to wander far and is a fish that migrates. In Indonesia, whale sharks can be spotted at many beautiful diving spots. It can even dive very deep, more than 1,000 meters down into the sea!"},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Tubuh hiu paus berwarna abu-abu dengan perut putih. Punggungnya penuh bintik dan garis putih kekuningan yang tampak seperti taburan bintang di langit malam. Pola bintik ini berbeda pada setiap hiu, seperti sidik jari. Mulutnya sangat lebar dan datar di ujung kepalanya, dengan dua mata kecil di sisinya.","body_en":"The whale shark's body is gray with a white belly. Its back is covered in yellowish-white spots and stripes that look like stars sprinkled across the night sky. This spot pattern is different on every shark, like a fingerprint. Its mouth is very wide and flat at the front of its head, with two small eyes on the sides."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Hiu paus makan dengan cara menyaring air laut lewat mulutnya yang besar. Makanan kesukaannya adalah plankton, yaitu makhluk laut yang sangat kecil. Ia berenang pelan dengan mulut terbuka lebar, lalu air keluar lewat insang dan makanan tertinggal di dalam. Walau giginya banyak dan kecil-kecil, ia tidak memakainya untuk mengunyah.","body_en":"The whale shark eats by filtering seawater through its big mouth. Its favorite food is plankton, which are tiny sea creatures. It swims slowly with its mouth wide open, then water flows out through its gills while the food stays inside. Even though it has many tiny teeth, it does not use them to chew."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa?","h_en":"Why Is It Special?","body_id":"Hiu paus sangat ramah, kadang membiarkan penyelam berenang pelan di dekatnya. Ia bisa hidup sampai 70 tahun dan dipercaya sudah ada sejak 60 juta tahun lalu. Sayangnya, ia bisa terancam karena tertangkap jaring nelayan tanpa sengaja. Yuk, kita jaga laut tetap bersih agar raksasa lembut ini terus berenang bahagia!","body_en":"The whale shark is very friendly and sometimes lets divers swim slowly near it. It can live up to 70 years and is believed to have existed since 60 million years ago. Sadly, it can be in danger from getting caught in fishing nets by accident. Let's keep our oceans clean so this gentle giant can keep swimming happily!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Hiu paus adalah ikan terbesar di dunia!","en":"The whale shark is the biggest fish in the world!"},{"id":"Ia bisa hidup sampai 70 tahun.","en":"It can live up to 70 years."},{"id":"Pola bintik di punggungnya unik, seperti sidik jari.","en":"The spots on its back are unique, like a fingerprint."},{"id":"Hiu paus bisa menyelam lebih dari 1.000 meter ke dasar laut.","en":"Whale sharks can dive more than 1,000 meters deep."},{"id":"Walau besar, hiu paus jinak dan tidak berbahaya.","en":"Despite its size, the whale shark is tame and harmless."},{"id":"Hiu paus suka makan plankton yang sangat kecil.","en":"Whale sharks love eating tiny plankton."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Plankton","def_id":"Makhluk laut yang sangat kecil dan mengapung, menjadi makanan banyak hewan laut.","def_en":"Very tiny sea creatures that float in the water and feed many ocean animals."},{"term":"Menyaring (filter)","def_id":"Cara makan dengan mengambil makanan kecil dari air dan membuang airnya.","def_en":"A way of eating by taking tiny food from the water and letting the water out."},{"term":"Insang","def_id":"Bagian tubuh ikan untuk bernapas dan tempat air keluar saat menyaring makanan.","def_en":"The body part a fish uses to breathe, and where water exits when it filters food."},{"term":"Bermigrasi","def_id":"Berpindah jauh dari satu tempat ke tempat lain untuk mencari makan atau berbiak.","def_en":"Travelling a long way from one place to another to find food or to breed."},{"term":"Tropis","def_id":"Daerah hangat di dekat garis khatulistiwa, seperti laut di sekitar Indonesia.","def_en":"Warm regions near the equator, such as the seas around Indonesia."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/0db4e5bbcb6017eb.jpg","caption_id":"Hiu paus berenang dengan anggun, memperlihatkan bintik-bintik putih di punggung abu-abunya yang lebar.","caption_en":"A whale shark glides gracefully, showing the white spots across its wide gray back.","credit":"User:Zac Wolf (original), en:User:Stefan (cropping)","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/ea8a69023305e034.jpg","caption_id":"Seorang penyelam berenang di dekat mulut hiu paus yang sangat lebar dan datar untuk menyaring makanan.","caption_en":"A snorkeler swims near the whale shark's very wide, flat mouth used to filter its food.","credit":"Jaontiveros","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e82213409de96120.jpg","caption_id":"Dua hiu paus raksasa berenang tenang di akuarium besar, menunjukkan betapa besar tubuhnya.","caption_en":"Two giant whale sharks swim calmly in a huge aquarium, showing just how big they are.","credit":"Jordy Meow","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/ef8e657a0d08a540.jpg","caption_id":"Pengunjung memandang takjub saat hiu paus melintas di balik kaca akuarium yang besar.","caption_en":"Visitors watch in wonder as a whale shark passes behind the large aquarium glass.","credit":"Zac Wolf","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hiu_paus"},"ensiklopedia_hutan_mangrove":{"id":"ensiklopedia_hutan_mangrove","title_id":"Hutan Mangrove","title_en":"Mangrove Forest","subtitle_id":"Hutan ajaib penjaga pantai dan rumah satwa","subtitle_en":"Magical coastal forest, home to wildlife","data_card":[{"icon":"water_drop","label_id":"Lokasi","label_en":"Location","value_id":"Tepi laut berlumpur, teluk, dan muara sungai","value_en":"Muddy seashores, bays, and river mouths"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Tumbuhan utama","label_en":"Main plants","value_id":"Pohon bakau, api-api, dan nipah","value_en":"Mangrove, api-api, and nipa trees"},{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Hewan penghuni","label_en":"Animals","value_id":"Ikan, kepiting, udang, dan burung","value_en":"Fish, crabs, shrimp, and birds"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Manfaat","label_en":"Benefit","value_id":"Menahan ombak dan melindungi pantai","value_en":"Holds back waves and protects the coast"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Sumatra, Kalimantan, dan Papua","value_en":"Sumatra, Kalimantan, and Papua"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terluas di dunia, sebagian perlu dijaga","value_en":"Largest in the world, some needs caring for"}],"sections":[{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Apa Itu Hutan Mangrove?","h_en":"What Is a Mangrove Forest?","body_id":"Hutan mangrove, atau hutan bakau, adalah hutan istimewa yang tumbuh di tepi laut. Pohon-pohonnya berdiri di tanah berlumpur yang sering tergenang air pasang. Hanya tumbuhan khusus yang bisa hidup di sini karena airnya asin. Hutan ini sering tumbuh di teluk yang tenang dan di muara sungai tempat lumpur mengendap.","body_en":"A mangrove forest is a special forest that grows along the seashore. Its trees stand in muddy soil that is often flooded by the tide. Only special plants can live here because the water is salty. These forests often grow in calm bays and at river mouths where mud settles."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Tumbuhnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Grow?","body_id":"Hutan mangrove tumbuh di tempat-tempat yang hangat di dekat garis khatulistiwa. Indonesia punya hutan mangrove terluas di seluruh dunia! Hutan ini banyak ditemukan di pantai timur Sumatra, Kalimantan, dan sekitar Teluk Bintuni di Papua. Sekitar seperempat hutan mangrove dunia ada di negara kita.","body_en":"Mangrove forests grow in warm places near the equator. Indonesia has the largest mangrove forests in the whole world! They are found along the east coast of Sumatra, in Kalimantan, and around Bintuni Bay in Papua. About a quarter of the world's mangroves are in our country."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Pohon yang Hebat","h_en":"Amazing Trees","body_id":"Pohon bakau punya akar khusus yang menjulur seperti kaki-kaki yang kokoh. Sebagian akarnya bahkan menyembul ke atas lumpur untuk bernapas. Ada banyak jenis pohon mangrove, dan sekitar 39 jenis tumbuh di Indonesia. Pohon-pohon ini tumbuh berlapis-lapis, dari tepi laut sampai ke daratan.","body_en":"Mangrove trees have special roots that stretch out like sturdy legs. Some roots even poke up above the mud to breathe. There are many kinds of mangrove trees, and about 39 kinds grow in Indonesia. They grow in layers, from the seashore all the way inland."},{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Rumah Banyak Hewan","h_en":"Home to Many Animals","body_id":"Hutan mangrove adalah rumah yang nyaman bagi banyak hewan. Ikan kecil, kepiting, dan udang bersembunyi di antara akar-akarnya. Burung-burung indah, seperti jalak bali, juga suka tinggal di sini. Tempat ini seperti taman bermain yang penuh kehidupan!","body_en":"The mangrove forest is a cozy home for many animals. Small fish, crabs, and shrimp hide among its roots. Beautiful birds, like the Bali myna, also love to live here. This place is like a playground full of life!"},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Pelindung Pantai","h_en":"Guardian of the Coast","body_id":"Hutan mangrove adalah perisai alami yang melindungi pantai. Akar-akarnya yang rapat menahan ombak besar agar tidak merusak daratan. Hutan ini juga mencegah tanah pantai terkikis air laut. Yuk, kita jaga hutan mangrove agar pantai dan hewan-hewannya tetap aman dan sehat!","body_en":"The mangrove forest is a natural shield that protects the coast. Its thick roots hold back big waves so they cannot harm the land. The forest also stops the shore from being washed away by the sea. Let's protect mangrove forests so our coasts and animals stay safe and healthy!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Indonesia punya hutan mangrove terluas di dunia!","en":"Indonesia has the largest mangrove forest in the world!"},{"id":"Seperempat mangrove dunia ada di Indonesia.","en":"A quarter of the world's mangroves are in Indonesia."},{"id":"Akar bakau menahan ombak besar agar pantai aman.","en":"Mangrove roots hold back big waves to keep the coast safe."},{"id":"Sekitar 39 jenis pohon bakau tumbuh di Indonesia.","en":"About 39 kinds of mangrove trees grow in Indonesia."},{"id":"Ikan, kepiting, dan burung tinggal di antara akarnya.","en":"Fish, crabs, and birds live among its roots."},{"id":"Pohon bakau bisa hidup di air laut yang asin.","en":"Mangrove trees can live in salty seawater."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Air pasang","def_id":"Saat permukaan air laut naik dan menggenangi tepi pantai.","def_en":"When the sea level rises and floods the edge of the shore."},{"term":"Muara sungai","def_id":"Tempat sungai bertemu laut, sering berlumpur dan tenang.","def_en":"The place where a river meets the sea, often muddy and calm."},{"term":"Akar napas","def_id":"Akar bakau yang menyembul ke atas lumpur agar pohon bisa bernapas.","def_en":"Mangrove roots that poke up above the mud so the tree can breathe."},{"term":"Salinitas","def_id":"Banyaknya kadar garam di dalam air, membuat air terasa asin.","def_en":"The amount of salt in the water, which makes it taste salty."},{"term":"Ekosistem","def_id":"Tempat tumbuhan, hewan, dan alam hidup bersama dan saling membutuhkan.","def_en":"A place where plants, animals, and nature live together and need each other."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6ff699218b04654d.jpg","caption_id":"Semak bakau hijau berdiri di atas akar tunjang yang kokoh di tepi pantai berpasir.","caption_en":"Green mangrove shrubs stand on sturdy prop roots along a sandy shore.","credit":"CEphoto, Uwe Aranas","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9e46ea2e529bcdeb.jpg","caption_id":"Saat air surut, terlihat akar bakau yang melengkung dan akar napas kecil menyembul dari lumpur.","caption_en":"At low tide, arching mangrove roots and small breathing roots poke up from the mud.","credit":"Ron from Nieuwegein / South Moreton Oxfordshire, Netherlands / UK","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b4e2647dc204423d.jpg","caption_id":"Pemandangan setengah di atas dan setengah di bawah air memperlihatkan akar bakau yang menjadi tempat berlindung ikan.","caption_en":"A half-above and half-below water view shows the mangrove roots that shelter fish.","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c211ef295f34d967.jpg","caption_id":"Hutan mangrove yang lebat membentang di tepi pantai di bawah langit biru cerah.","caption_en":"A thick mangrove forest stretches along the coast under a bright blue sky.","credit":"CEphoto, Uwe Aranas","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hutan_mangrove"},"ensiklopedia_jalak_bali_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_jalak_bali_1","title_id":"Jalak Bali","title_en":"Bali Myna","subtitle_id":"Burung putih cantik kebanggaan Pulau Bali","subtitle_en":"Bali's beautiful white pride bird","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan & savana","value_en":"Forest & savanna"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Sekitar 25 cm","value_en":"About 25 cm"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Diet","value_id":"Serangga & buah","value_en":"Insects & fruit"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Bali Barat","value_en":"West Bali"},{"icon":"pets","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Burung pengicau","value_en":"Songbird"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Sangat langka","value_en":"Critically rare"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Jalak Bali?","h_en":"What Is the Bali Myna?","body_id":"Jalak bali adalah burung pengicau cantik berukuran sedang, panjangnya sekitar 25 cm. Burung ini hanya ditemukan di hutan bagian barat Pulau Bali. Ia satu-satunya hewan asli khas Bali, jadi sangat istimewa. Pada tahun 1991, jalak bali dipilih menjadi lambang fauna Provinsi Bali.","body_en":"The Bali myna is a beautiful medium-sized songbird, about 25 cm long. This bird is found only in the forests of western Bali. It is the only animal native to Bali, so it is very special. In 1991, the Bali myna was chosen as the official animal symbol of Bali Province."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Bulu jalak bali hampir seluruhnya berwarna putih bersih. Hanya ujung sayap dan ekornya yang berwarna hitam. Di sekeliling matanya ada pelupuk berwarna biru tua yang sangat cantik. Burung jantan punya jambul indah di kepalanya.","body_en":"The Bali myna's feathers are almost entirely pure white. Only the tips of its wings and tail are black. Around its eyes is a lovely deep-blue patch. The male has a beautiful crest on its head."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Jalak bali suka tinggal di hutan mangrove, hutan rawa, dan daerah savana. Rumah aslinya ada di Taman Nasional Bali Barat. Ia membuat sarang di dalam lubang pohon, cukup tinggi dari tanah. Burung ini suka terbang berombongan bersama teman-temannya.","body_en":"The Bali myna loves to live in mangrove forests, swamp forests, and savanna areas. Its natural home is in West Bali National Park. It builds its nest inside tree holes, fairly high off the ground. This bird loves to fly in flocks with its friends."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kebiasaan Lucu","h_en":"Fun Habits","body_id":"Jalak bali punya kicauan khas berupa siulan dan lengkingan yang nyaring. Ia bahkan pandai menirukan suara burung lain! Burung ini sangat suka kebersihan dan senang bermain air untuk mandi. Setelah mandi, ia berjemur di bawah sinar matahari agar bulunya kering dan berkilau.","body_en":"The Bali myna has a special song of whistles and bright, ringing calls. It is even good at copying the sounds of other birds! This bird loves cleanliness and enjoys splashing in water to bathe. After bathing, it suns itself so its feathers dry and shine."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Jalak bali termasuk burung yang sangat langka di alam liar. Jumlahnya pernah menurun sampai tinggal sedikit sekali. Untungnya, banyak orang baik bekerja keras menjaga dan menangkarkannya. Yuk, kita sayangi jalak bali agar burung cantik ini terus berkicau di Bali!","body_en":"The Bali myna is a very rare bird in the wild. Its numbers once dropped down to very few. Luckily, many kind people work hard to protect and breed them. Let's care for the Bali myna so this beautiful bird keeps singing in Bali!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Jalak bali adalah satu-satunya hewan khas asli Bali!","en":"The Bali myna is the only animal native to Bali!"},{"id":"Bulunya hampir 90 persen berwarna putih bersih.","en":"About 90 percent of its feathers are pure white."},{"id":"Ia menjadi lambang fauna Provinsi Bali sejak 1991.","en":"It has been Bali Province's animal symbol since 1991."},{"id":"Jalak bali pandai menirukan suara burung lain.","en":"The Bali myna is good at copying other birds' sounds."},{"id":"Ia membuat sarang di dalam lubang pohon.","en":"It builds its nest inside tree holes."},{"id":"Burung ini sangat suka mandi dan menjaga kebersihan.","en":"This bird loves bathing and staying clean."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hewan atau tumbuhan yang hanya hidup di satu tempat di dunia.","def_en":"An animal or plant that lives in only one place in the world."},{"term":"Pengicau","def_id":"Burung yang pandai bernyanyi dan berkicau.","def_en":"A bird that is good at singing and chirping."},{"term":"Jambul","def_id":"Bulu yang berdiri di atas kepala burung.","def_en":"Feathers that stand up on top of a bird's head."},{"term":"Penangkaran","def_id":"Tempat hewan dijaga dan dikembangbiakkan agar tidak punah.","def_en":"A place where animals are kept and bred so they don't go extinct."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a6fa2ef43c702575.jpg","caption_id":"Jalak bali bertengger, memamerkan bulu putih dan pelupuk biru khasnya.","caption_en":"A Bali myna perched, showing its white feathers and signature blue eye-patch.","credit":"JJ Harrison","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/8e23caa6af095eb7.jpg","caption_id":"Jalak bali di antara dahan dan buah-buahan hutan.","caption_en":"A Bali myna among branches and forest fruits.","credit":"Ady Kristanto","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/000c823cf42ebd18.jpg","caption_id":"Tampak depan jalak bali dengan dada putih bersih.","caption_en":"Front view of a Bali myna with a clean white chest.","credit":"Stavenn","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/1e55d1be9f083cac.jpg","caption_id":"Jalak bali bertengger tenang di sebuah ranting.","caption_en":"A Bali myna perched calmly on a twig.","credit":"User:Cburnett","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jalak_bali"},"ensiklopedia_kantong_semar":{"id":"ensiklopedia_kantong_semar","title_id":"Kantong Semar","title_en":"Pitcher Plant","subtitle_id":"Tumbuhan ajaib pemakan serangga!","subtitle_en":"A magical insect-eating plant!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Rawa & hutan lembap","value_en":"Swamps & damp forests"},{"icon":"height","label_id":"Tinggi","label_en":"Height","value_id":"Memanjat hingga 15-20 m","value_en":"Climbs up to 15-20 m"},{"icon":"water_drop","label_id":"Cara makan","label_en":"How it eats","value_id":"Menjebak serangga di kantong","value_en":"Traps insects in its pouch"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Kalimantan & Sumatra","value_en":"Borneo & Sumatra"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Nepenthes (130+ jenis)","value_en":"Nepenthes (130+ kinds)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Kantong Semar?","h_en":"What Is the Pitcher Plant?","body_id":"Kantong semar adalah tumbuhan yang memakan serangga! Para ilmuwan menyebut kelompoknya Nepenthes. Tumbuhan ini punya kantong berisi cairan khusus yang bisa melarutkan serangga kecil. Dari serangga itulah ia mendapat makanan tambahan.","body_en":"The pitcher plant is a plant that eats insects! Scientists call its group Nepenthes. It has a pouch filled with a special liquid that can dissolve tiny insects. That is how it gets extra food."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Kantong semar suka tempat lembap seperti rawa-rawa. Ia tumbuh di Indonesia, terutama di pulau Kalimantan dan Sumatra. Di Kalimantan Barat, orang menyebutnya entuyut. Ada yang hidup di tepi pantai, ada pula yang tinggi di pegunungan.","body_en":"Pitcher plants love damp places like swamps. They grow in Indonesia, especially on the islands of Borneo and Sumatra. In West Kalimantan, people call it entuyut. Some live near the beach, and others live high in the mountains."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Kantong semar memanjat tanaman lain dan bisa tumbuh sangat tinggi. Di ujung daunnya ada sulur yang berubah menjadi kantong perangkap. Ada kantong atas yang menggantung untuk menangkap nyamuk dan lalat. Ada juga kantong bawah dekat tanah untuk menjebak semut.","body_en":"Pitcher plants climb other plants and can grow very tall. At the tip of each leaf is a tendril that turns into a trap-pouch. The upper pouch hangs high to catch mosquitoes and flies. The lower pouch sits near the ground to trap ants."},{"icon":"water_drop","h_id":"Cara Lembut Menangkap Serangga","h_en":"How It Gently Traps Insects","body_id":"Bibir kantong licin dan harum, jadi serangga datang untuk mencicipi. Saat menginjak tepi yang licin, serangga tergelincir masuk ke dalam kantong. Di dalam ada cairan berenzim yang perlahan mengubah serangga menjadi makanan. Begitulah tumbuhan ini mendapat nutrisi tanpa harus berburu.","body_en":"The rim of the pouch is slippery and sweet-smelling, so insects come for a taste. When they step on the slick edge, they slide down into the pouch. Inside is a special liquid with enzymes that slowly turns the insect into food. That is how the plant gets nutrients without hunting."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa & Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Why It's Special & Let's Protect It","body_id":"Kantong semar tumbuh di tanah miskin makanan, jadi ia pintar mencari nutrisi sendiri. Bahkan kelelawar kecil suka tidur di dalam kantongnya yang aman! Karena unik, kita harus menjaga rawa dan hutan tempatnya hidup. Dengan melindungi rumahnya, tumbuhan ajaib ini bisa terus tumbuh.","body_en":"Pitcher plants grow in soil that is poor in food, so they cleverly find their own nutrients. Tiny bats even like to sleep safely inside their pouches! Because they are so unique, we must protect the swamps and forests where they live. By saving their home, this magical plant can keep growing."}],"facts":[{"id":"Kantong semar memakan serangga, bukan dimakan serangga!","en":"The pitcher plant eats insects instead of being eaten by them!"},{"id":"Ada lebih dari 130 jenis kantong semar di dunia.","en":"There are more than 130 kinds of pitcher plants in the world."},{"id":"Kelelawar berbulu wol suka tidur aman di dalam kantongnya.","en":"Woolly bats like to sleep safely inside the pouch."},{"id":"Cairan di dalam kantong bisa melarutkan serangga kecil.","en":"The liquid inside the pouch can dissolve tiny insects."},{"id":"Di Kalimantan, kantongnya dipakai sebagai wadah membuat kue!","en":"In Borneo, the pouch is used as a container for making cakes!"},{"id":"Ada kantong semar yang tumbuh tinggi di gunung, lebih dari 3.000 meter!","en":"Some pitcher plants grow high on mountains, over 3,000 meters up!"}],"glossary":[{"term":"Insektivora","def_id":"Tumbuhan atau hewan yang memakan serangga sebagai makanan.","def_en":"A plant or animal that eats insects for food."},{"term":"Nepenthes","def_id":"Nama ilmiah untuk kelompok tumbuhan kantong semar.","def_en":"The scientific name for the group of pitcher plants."},{"term":"Sulur","def_id":"Bagian tipis dan panjang di ujung daun yang berubah menjadi kantong.","def_en":"A thin, long part at the tip of a leaf that turns into the pouch."},{"term":"Enzim","def_id":"Cairan khusus yang membantu melarutkan serangga menjadi makanan.","def_en":"A special liquid that helps dissolve insects into food."},{"term":"Nutrisi","def_id":"Zat makanan yang dibutuhkan agar tumbuhan bisa hidup dan tumbuh.","def_en":"The food substances a plant needs to live and grow."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3c337722596ebff7.jpg","caption_id":"Kantong bawah dengan bibir merah cerah, siap menjebak semut yang lewat.","caption_en":"A lower pouch with a bright red rim, ready to trap passing ants.","credit":"Kleo Marlo Sialongo","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e2749697e68a1792.jpg","caption_id":"Sekelompok kantong hijau tumbuh rapat di tepi air yang lembap.","caption_en":"A cluster of green pouches grows close together by the damp water's edge.","credit":"en:User:Rbrtjong","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/4ebbe0488c825f13.jpg","caption_id":"Kantong atas menggantung di antara dahan untuk menangkap serangga terbang.","caption_en":"An upper pouch hangs among the branches to catch flying insects.","credit":"Pavel Kirillov from St.Petersburg, Russia","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/0beaf77174ac2dc2.jpg","caption_id":"Sebuah tangan menunjukkan betapa besar kantong semar ini bisa tumbuh.","caption_en":"A hand shows just how big this pitcher plant pouch can grow.","credit":"NoverKelana","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kantong_semar"},"ensiklopedia_komodo_2":{"id":"ensiklopedia_komodo_2","title_id":"Komodo","title_en":"Komodo Dragon","subtitle_id":"Kadal terbesar di dunia dari Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"The world's biggest lizard, from Indonesia!","data_card":[{"icon":"grass","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Padang rumput & hutan belukar","value_en":"Grasslands & scrub forest"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"2-3 m, hingga 100 kg","value_en":"2-3 m, up to 100 kg"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Pemakan daging","value_en":"Meat-eater"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Nusa Tenggara Timur","value_en":"East Nusa Tenggara"},{"icon":"shield","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Rentan, dilindungi","value_en":"Vulnerable, protected"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Biawak (Varanidae)","value_en":"Monitor lizards (Varanidae)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Komodo?","h_en":"What Is the Komodo Dragon?","body_id":"Komodo adalah biawak raksasa dan kadal terbesar di dunia! Panjangnya bisa 2 sampai 3 meter, sepanjang sebuah mobil kecil. Orang asli pulau Komodo menyebutnya ora. Hewan ini hanya hidup di Indonesia, jadi kita patut bangga!","body_en":"The Komodo dragon is a giant monitor lizard and the biggest lizard in the world! It can be 2 to 3 meters long, about as long as a small car. The local people of Komodo Island call it ora. This animal lives only in Indonesia, so we can be proud!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Komodo hanya hidup di beberapa pulau di Nusa Tenggara Timur, Indonesia. Pulau-pulaunya bernama Komodo, Rinca, Flores, Gili Motang, dan Gili Dasami. Mereka suka padang rumput terbuka dan hutan belukar. Tempat tinggalnya kini dilindungi sebagai Taman Nasional Komodo.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon lives only on a few islands in East Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia. The islands are called Komodo, Rinca, Flores, Gili Motang, and Gili Dasami. They like open grasslands and bushy forests. Their home is now protected as Komodo National Park."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Komodo punya kulit tebal berwarna abu-abu sampai cokelat dan ekor sepanjang tubuhnya. Lidahnya panjang dan bercabang, dipakai untuk mencium bau dari jauh. Komodo bahkan bisa mencium makanan dari jarak beberapa kilometer! Cakarnya kuat untuk menggali lubang tempat berlindung.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon has thick gray-to-brown skin and a tail as long as its body. Its long, forked tongue is used to smell from far away. A Komodo can even smell food from several kilometers away! Its strong claws help dig burrows for shelter."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Komodo adalah pemakan daging dan memburu hewan dengan cara mengendap-endap diam-diam. Ia suka menyendiri dan hanya berkumpul saat makan atau berkembang biak. Walau besar, komodo bisa berlari cepat, berenang, bahkan menyelam. Saat masih muda, ia juga pandai memanjat pohon dengan cakarnya.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon is a meat-eater and hunts by quietly sneaking up on animals. It likes to be alone and only gathers to eat or to breed. Even though it is big, it can run fast, swim, and even dive. When young, it is also good at climbing trees with its claws."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa & Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Why It's Special & Let's Protect It","body_id":"Komodo adalah hewan langka yang hanya ada di Indonesia, jadi sangat istimewa. Sayangnya rumahnya makin sempit karena ulah manusia. Pemerintah melindunginya dan membuat Taman Nasional Komodo. Dengan menjaga hutan dan pulaunya, komodo bisa hidup bahagia untuk waktu yang lama.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon is a rare animal found only in Indonesia, so it is very special. Sadly, its home is getting smaller because of people. The government protects it and created Komodo National Park. By caring for its forests and islands, the Komodo dragon can live happily for a long time."}],"facts":[{"id":"Komodo adalah kadal terbesar di dunia!","en":"The Komodo dragon is the biggest lizard in the world!"},{"id":"Lidahnya yang bercabang bisa mencium bau dari berkilo-kilometer jauhnya.","en":"Its forked tongue can smell from kilometers away."},{"id":"Komodo bisa berlari hingga 20 km per jam dalam jarak pendek.","en":"A Komodo can run up to 20 km per hour over short distances."},{"id":"Ia pandai berenang dan bisa menyelam sedalam 4,5 meter.","en":"It is a good swimmer and can dive 4.5 meters deep."},{"id":"Komodo punya sekitar 60 gigi tajam di mulutnya.","en":"A Komodo has about 60 sharp teeth in its mouth."},{"id":"Komodo hanya hidup liar di Indonesia, tidak di tempat lain di dunia!","en":"Komodo dragons live in the wild only in Indonesia, nowhere else!"}],"glossary":[{"term":"Biawak","def_id":"Kadal besar berkaki empat dengan lidah bercabang; komodo termasuk biawak.","def_en":"A large four-legged lizard with a forked tongue; the Komodo is a monitor lizard."},{"term":"Lidah bercabang","def_id":"Lidah yang terbelah dua di ujungnya, dipakai untuk mencium bau.","def_en":"A tongue that splits in two at the tip, used to smell."},{"term":"Sabana","def_id":"Padang rumput luas yang terbuka, tempat komodo suka berjalan.","def_en":"A wide, open grassland where the Komodo likes to roam."},{"term":"Rentan","def_id":"Hewan yang jumlahnya makin sedikit dan perlu kita lindungi.","def_en":"An animal whose numbers are getting small and needs our protection."},{"term":"Taman nasional","def_id":"Daerah khusus yang dijaga agar hewan dan tumbuhannya tetap aman.","def_en":"A special protected area where animals and plants are kept safe."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/7d2a3b45ec0eb402.jpg","caption_id":"Komodo besar berjalan di jalan setapak, lidahnya menjulur untuk mencium bau.","caption_en":"A big Komodo walks along a trail, its tongue flicking out to smell the air.","credit":"Charles J. Sharp","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d5599131a75bee94.jpg","caption_id":"Berjemur di atas batu di antara dedaunan hijau yang segar.","caption_en":"Basking on a rock among fresh green leaves.","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d9c808ccbd1c5e2b.jpg","caption_id":"Dua komodo berjalan bersama di pulau Rinca yang berumput.","caption_en":"Two Komodo dragons walk together on grassy Rinca Island.","credit":"Markofjohnson","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/14ec90a093111f14.jpg","caption_id":"Lihat dekat kaki dan cakarnya yang kuat untuk menggali dan berjalan.","caption_en":"A close look at its foot and strong claws, used for digging and walking.","credit":"Markofjohnson at English Wikipedia","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Komodo"},"ensiklopedia_orangutan":{"id":"ensiklopedia_orangutan","title_id":"Orang Utan","title_en":"Orangutan","subtitle_id":"Kera cerdas penghuni pohon hutan hujan!","subtitle_en":"The clever ape of the rainforest trees!","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan tropis","value_en":"Tropical rainforest"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Jantan ~75 kg, betina ~37 kg","value_en":"Male ~75 kg, female ~37 kg"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Buah, daun, madu, serangga","value_en":"Fruit, leaves, honey, insects"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Region","value_id":"Kalimantan & Sumatra","value_en":"Borneo & Sumatra"},{"icon":"warning","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam kritis","value_en":"Critically endangered"},{"icon":"groups","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Kera besar (Pongo)","value_en":"Great apes (Pongo)"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Orang Utan?","h_en":"What Is the Orangutan?","body_id":"Orang utan adalah kera besar berbulu cokelat kemerahan. Namanya berasal dari bahasa Melayu yang berarti orang hutan. Ada tiga jenis orang utan: Kalimantan, Sumatra, dan Tapanuli. Mereka adalah saudara jauh kita yang sangat pintar.","body_en":"The orangutan is a great ape with reddish-brown hair. Its name comes from the Malay words meaning person of the forest. There are three kinds of orangutan: Bornean, Sumatran, and Tapanuli. They are our clever distant cousins."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Orang utan hidup di hutan hujan Indonesia dan Malaysia. Sekarang mereka hanya ditemukan di pulau Kalimantan dan Sumatra. Mereka adalah kera besar yang paling suka tinggal di atas pohon. Hampir sepanjang hari dihabiskan di antara dahan-dahan yang tinggi.","body_en":"Orangutans live in the rainforests of Indonesia and Malaysia. Today they are found only on the islands of Borneo and Sumatra. They are the great apes that love living in trees the most. Almost all day is spent high among the branches."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Orang utan punya lengan yang sangat panjang dan kaki yang pendek, sempurna untuk berayun di pohon. Tubuhnya tertutup rambut cokelat kemerahan. Orang utan jantan dewasa lebih besar dan punya bantalan lebar di kedua pipinya. Jantan juga sering berteriak panjang yang terdengar dari jauh.","body_en":"Orangutans have very long arms and short legs, perfect for swinging through trees. Their bodies are covered in reddish-brown hair. Adult males are bigger and have wide pads on their cheeks. Males also make long calls that can be heard from far away."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Makanan kesukaan orang utan adalah buah-buahan. Mereka juga makan daun, kulit kayu, madu, serangga, dan telur burung. Orang utan sangat pintar dan bisa memakai alat untuk membantu mencari makan. Setiap malam mereka membuat sarang baru dari ranting dan daun untuk tidur.","body_en":"The orangutan's favorite food is fruit. They also eat leaves, tree bark, honey, insects, and bird eggs. Orangutans are very smart and can use tools to help find food. Every night they build a new nest from twigs and leaves to sleep in."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa & Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Why It's Special & Let's Protect It","body_id":"Orang utan adalah salah satu primata paling cerdas di dunia. Sayangnya ketiga jenisnya kini sangat terancam punah. Hutan tempat tinggalnya banyak ditebang, dan itu membuat mereka kehilangan rumah. Dengan menjaga hutan, kita membantu orang utan tetap hidup bebas dan bahagia.","body_en":"Orangutans are among the smartest primates in the world. Sadly, all three kinds are now in great danger of disappearing. Many of their forests have been cut down, leaving them without a home. By protecting the forests, we help orangutans stay free and happy."}],"facts":[{"id":"Orang utan berarti orang hutan dalam bahasa Melayu.","en":"Orangutan means person of the forest in Malay."},{"id":"Mereka kera besar yang paling suka tinggal di atas pohon.","en":"They are the great apes that love living in trees the most."},{"id":"Orang utan membuat sarang baru dari ranting setiap malam.","en":"Orangutans build a new nest from twigs every night."},{"id":"Mereka sangat pintar dan bisa memakai alat untuk mencari makan.","en":"They are very clever and can use tools to find food."},{"id":"Orang utan bisa hidup lebih dari 30 tahun.","en":"Orangutans can live more than 30 years."},{"id":"Lengan orang utan lebih panjang daripada kakinya untuk berayun.","en":"An orangutan's arms are longer than its legs for swinging."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Kera besar","def_id":"Kelompok primata bertubuh besar tanpa ekor, seperti orang utan dan gorila.","def_en":"A group of large, tailless primates, like orangutans and gorillas."},{"term":"Arboreal","def_id":"Hewan yang menghabiskan sebagian besar hidupnya di atas pohon.","def_en":"An animal that spends most of its life up in the trees."},{"term":"Bantalan pipi","def_id":"Lipatan lebar di pipi orang utan jantan dewasa.","def_en":"The wide cheek pads on an adult male orangutan."},{"term":"Primata","def_id":"Kelompok hewan pintar seperti kera, monyet, dan manusia.","def_en":"A group of clever animals like apes, monkeys, and humans."},{"term":"Terancam punah","def_id":"Hewan yang jumlahnya sangat sedikit dan bisa hilang dari bumi.","def_en":"An animal so few in number that it could vanish from the Earth."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b30a1e77d5d9e4fc.jpg","caption_id":"Orang utan duduk di dahan sambil memegang kelapa dengan jari-jarinya yang lihai.","caption_en":"An orangutan sits on a branch, holding a coconut with its clever fingers.","credit":"Eleifert","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c430a7d4906c53b7.jpg","caption_id":"Tiga jenis orang utan jantan: Kalimantan, Sumatra, dan Tapanuli.","caption_en":"The three kinds of male orangutan: Bornean, Sumatran, and Tapanuli.","credit":"Eric Kilby, Aiwok, Tim Laman","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/63fb91ec52199d0b.jpg","caption_id":"Orang utan Tapanuli jantan (kiri) dan betina (kanan) di hutan Sumatra.","caption_en":"A male (left) and female (right) Tapanuli orangutan in the Sumatran forest.","credit":"Tim Laman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orang_utan"},"ensiklopedia_penyu_hijau_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_penyu_hijau_1","title_id":"Penyu Hijau","title_en":"Green Sea Turtle","subtitle_id":"Penyu laut besar yang menjelajahi samudra hangat","subtitle_en":"A big sea turtle that roams warm oceans","data_card":[{"icon":"waves","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Laut tropis & subtropis yang hangat","value_en":"Warm tropical & subtropical seas"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Cangkang sampai sekitar 1 meter","value_en":"Shell up to about 1 meter"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Lamun & rumput laut (dewasa)","value_en":"Seagrass & seaweed (as adults)"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Samudra Atlantik & Pasifik; tangkar di Ujung Genteng","value_en":"Atlantic & Pacific Oceans; bred at Ujung Genteng"},{"icon":"warning","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Terancam, jumlahnya makin sedikit","value_en":"Threatened, numbers are falling"},{"icon":"category","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Reptil laut, satu-satunya jenis Chelonia","value_en":"Sea reptile, the only Chelonia species"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Penyu Hijau?","h_en":"What Is a Green Sea Turtle?","body_id":"Penyu hijau (Chelonia mydas) adalah penyu laut yang besar dan termasuk reptil. Ia hidup di laut dan membawa rumahnya sendiri, yaitu cangkang yang kuat. Namanya 'hijau' bukan karena cangkangnya hijau, tetapi karena ada lemak berwarna hijau di bawah cangkangnya. Penyu hijau adalah satu-satunya jenis dalam golongan Chelonia.","body_en":"The green sea turtle (Chelonia mydas) is a large sea turtle and a reptile. It lives in the ocean and carries its own home, a strong shell. It is called 'green' not because the shell is green, but because of the green fat under its shell. The green sea turtle is the only species in the Chelonia group."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Penyu hijau berenang di semua laut tropis dan subtropis yang hangat, terutama di Samudra Atlantik dan Samudra Pasifik. Ia suka air hangat yang jernih. Di Indonesia, penyu ini dirawat dan ditangkarkan di Ujung Genteng, Sukabumi, agar jumlahnya tetap terjaga.","body_en":"Green sea turtles swim in all warm tropical and subtropical seas, especially the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans. They love clear, warm water. In Indonesia, they are cared for and bred at Ujung Genteng in Sukabumi to help keep their numbers safe."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Penyu hijau punya cangkang keras di atas tubuhnya untuk melindungi diri. Cangkang ini terdiri dari bagian atas (karapaks) dan bagian bawah (plastron). Kaki-kakinya berbentuk seperti dayung supaya bisa berenang cepat di air. Ia bernapas dengan paru-paru, jadi harus naik ke permukaan untuk menghirup udara.","body_en":"The green sea turtle has a hard shell on top of its body for protection. The shell has an upper part (carapace) and a lower part (plastron). Its legs are shaped like paddles so it can swim quickly through the water. It breathes with lungs, so it must come up to the surface for air."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Penyu hijau dewasa suka makan tumbuhan laut, seperti lamun dan rumput laut. Itulah sebabnya ia sering disebut penyu pemakan tumbuhan. Induk penyu kembali ke pantai untuk bertelur di pasir, lalu bayi-bayi kecilnya menetas dan bergegas menuju laut.","body_en":"Adult green sea turtles love eating sea plants, such as seagrass and seaweed. That is why they are known as plant-eating turtles. Mother turtles return to the beach to lay eggs in the sand, then the tiny babies hatch and hurry to the sea."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Jumlah penyu hijau makin sedikit karena diburu untuk diambil cangkang, telur, dan dagingnya. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga laut dan pantai tetap bersih dari sampah. Jika kita semua peduli, penyu hijau bisa terus berenang bahagia di laut.","body_en":"Green sea turtles are becoming fewer because they are hunted for their shells, eggs, and meat. We can help by keeping the sea and beaches clean and free of trash. If we all care, green sea turtles can keep swimming happily in the ocean."}],"facts":[{"id":"Namanya 'hijau' karena lemak hijau di bawah cangkangnya!","en":"It is called 'green' because of the green fat under its shell!"},{"id":"Penyu hijau adalah satu-satunya spesies dalam golongan Chelonia.","en":"The green sea turtle is the only species in the Chelonia group."},{"id":"Kakinya seperti dayung untuk berenang di laut.","en":"Its legs are like paddles for swimming in the sea."},{"id":"Ia bernapas dengan paru-paru dan harus naik untuk mengambil udara.","en":"It breathes with lungs and must surface for air."},{"id":"Induk penyu kembali ke pantai untuk bertelur di pasir.","en":"Mother turtles return to the beach to lay eggs in the sand."},{"id":"Penyu hijau dewasa suka makan rumput laut dan lamun.","en":"Adult green sea turtles love to eat seaweed and seagrass."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Karapaks","def_id":"Bagian atas cangkang penyu yang keras dan melindungi punggungnya.","def_en":"The hard upper part of a turtle's shell that protects its back."},{"term":"Plastron","def_id":"Bagian bawah cangkang penyu yang menutupi perutnya.","def_en":"The lower part of a turtle's shell that covers its belly."},{"term":"Lamun","def_id":"Rumput laut yang tumbuh di dasar laut dan menjadi makanan penyu hijau.","def_en":"A grass that grows on the sea floor and is food for green sea turtles."},{"term":"Subtropis","def_id":"Daerah laut yang hangat, dekat dengan daerah tropis.","def_en":"Warm sea areas that lie next to the tropical zone."},{"term":"Menetas","def_id":"Saat bayi penyu keluar dari telurnya.","def_en":"When a baby turtle comes out of its egg."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a0443bdd8b758053.jpg","caption_id":"Penyu hijau berenang di atas terumbu karang dengan kaki seperti dayung.","caption_en":"A green sea turtle glides over a coral reef with its paddle-like legs.","credit":"Brocken Inaglory","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3f165b798896b430.jpg","caption_id":"Penyu hijau dewasa merumput di hamparan lamun di dasar laut.","caption_en":"An adult green sea turtle grazes on a bed of seagrass on the sea floor.","credit":"P.Lindgren","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/55b6d280e713b6d1.jpg","caption_id":"Penyu hijau berenang naik ke permukaan untuk menghirup udara.","caption_en":"A green sea turtle swims up toward the surface to take a breath of air.","credit":"Brocken Inaglory","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/8665f0e91260185d.jpg","caption_id":"Sekelompok penyu hijau beristirahat di pantai berpasir.","caption_en":"A group of green sea turtles resting on a sandy beach.","credit":"E bailey","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e3dc74e7f0e3cb54.jpg","caption_id":"Penyu hijau berenang di air dangkal yang jernih dekat pantai.","caption_en":"A green sea turtle swims in clear, shallow water near the shore.","credit":"Tokugawapants at English Wikipedia + PiccoloNamek (Modifie version)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Penyu_hijau"},"ensiklopedia_rafflesia_arnoldii":{"id":"ensiklopedia_rafflesia_arnoldii","title_id":"Rafflesia Arnoldii (Padma Raksasa)","title_en":"Rafflesia Arnoldii","subtitle_id":"Bunga terbesar di dunia dari hutan Indonesia","subtitle_en":"The world's biggest flower from Indonesia's forests","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Hutan hujan lembap di Sumatra & Kalimantan","value_en":"Damp rainforests of Sumatra & Borneo"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Lebar 70-110 cm, berat sekitar 11 kg","value_en":"70-110 cm wide, about 11 kg heavy"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Lama Mekar","label_en":"Bloom Time","value_id":"Hanya sekitar 5-7 hari lalu layu","value_en":"Only about 5-7 days, then it wilts"},{"icon":"place","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Bengkulu, 'Bumi Rafflesia'; Taman Nasional Kerinci Seblat","value_en":"Bengkulu, 'Land of Rafflesia'; Kerinci Seblat National Park"},{"icon":"warning","label_id":"Status","label_en":"Status","value_id":"Langka & terancam, dilindungi sejak 1993","value_en":"Rare & threatened, protected since 1993"},{"icon":"spa","label_id":"Cara Hidup","label_en":"Way of Life","value_id":"Parasit, menempel pada akar merambat Tetrastigma","value_en":"Parasite, attached to the Tetrastigma vine"}],"sections":[{"icon":"local_florist","h_id":"Apa Itu Rafflesia?","h_en":"What Is Rafflesia?","body_id":"Rafflesia arnoldii adalah bunga terbesar di dunia! Saat mekar, lebarnya bisa mencapai sekitar 70 sampai 110 sentimeter, kira-kira selebar ban mobil, dan beratnya bisa sampai 11 kilogram. Bunga raksasa ini juga salah satu bunga nasional kebanggaan Indonesia.","body_en":"Rafflesia arnoldii is the biggest flower in the world! When it blooms, it can grow about 70 to 110 centimeters wide, roughly as wide as a car tire, and it can weigh up to 11 kilograms. This giant flower is also one of Indonesia's proud national flowers."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Rafflesia tumbuh di hutan hujan yang lembap di Pulau Sumatra dan Kalimantan. Daerah Bengkulu dikenal sebagai 'Bumi Rafflesia' karena bunga ini pertama ditemukan di sana pada tahun 1818. Taman Nasional Kerinci Seblat adalah tempat penting untuk menjaganya.","body_en":"Rafflesia grows in the damp rainforests of Sumatra and Borneo. The Bengkulu area is known as the 'Land of Rafflesia' because the flower was first found there in 1818. Kerinci Seblat National Park is an important place that protects it."},{"icon":"spa","h_id":"Bunga Tanpa Daun & Akar","h_en":"A Flower With No Leaves or Roots","body_id":"Rafflesia sangat unik karena tidak punya daun, akar, atau batang, hanya bunganya saja! Karena tak punya daun, ia tidak bisa membuat makanan sendiri. Jadi ia hidup sebagai parasit, menempel pada tumbuhan merambat bernama Tetrastigma dan mengambil makanan dari sana, seperti tamu yang menumpang makan.","body_en":"Rafflesia is very unusual because it has no leaves, roots, or stem, just the flower! Because it has no leaves, it cannot make its own food. So it lives as a parasite, attached to a climbing vine called Tetrastigma and takes food from it, like a guest borrowing a meal."},{"icon":"schedule","h_id":"Mekar & Baunya","h_en":"Blooming & Its Smell","body_id":"Rafflesia punya lima kelopak besar berwarna merah dengan bintik-bintik putih. Bunga ini hanya mekar sekitar lima sampai tujuh hari, lalu layu dan mati. Baunya kuat seperti bau bangkai, jadi orang menyebutnya 'bunga bangkai'. Bau itu memanggil lalat untuk membantu bunga membuat benih.","body_en":"Rafflesia has five big red petals with white spots. The flower blooms for only about five to seven days, then it wilts and dies. It smells strong like something rotten, so people call it the 'corpse flower'. That smell calls flies to help the flower make seeds."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Rafflesia sangat langka dan terancam punah karena hutan tempatnya hidup banyak ditebang. Sejak tahun 1993, bunga ini dilindungi sebagai puspa langka Indonesia. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga hutan tetap utuh agar bunga raksasa ini terus mekar.","body_en":"Rafflesia is very rare and endangered because the forests where it lives are being cut down. Since 1993, this flower has been protected as a rare flower of Indonesia. We can help by keeping forests safe so this giant flower can keep blooming."}],"facts":[{"id":"Rafflesia arnoldii adalah bunga terbesar di dunia!","en":"Rafflesia arnoldii is the biggest flower in the world!"},{"id":"Saat mekar, lebarnya bisa sampai 70-110 cm dan beratnya sekitar 11 kilogram.","en":"When open it can be 70-110 cm wide and weigh about 11 kilograms."},{"id":"Bunganya hanya mekar sekitar 5-7 hari lalu layu.","en":"The flower blooms for only about 5-7 days, then wilts."},{"id":"Baunya seperti bangkai, itu sebabnya disebut 'bunga bangkai'.","en":"It smells rotten, which is why it's called the 'corpse flower'."},{"id":"Rafflesia tidak punya daun, akar, atau batang, hanya bunga!","en":"Rafflesia has no leaves, roots, or stem, just the flower!"},{"id":"Namanya dari Thomas Stamford Raffles dan Dr. Joseph Arnold.","en":"It is named after Thomas Stamford Raffles and Dr. Joseph Arnold."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Parasit","def_id":"Makhluk hidup yang menempel pada makhluk lain dan mengambil makanannya.","def_en":"A living thing that attaches to another and takes its food."},{"term":"Tetrastigma","def_id":"Tumbuhan merambat (liana) yang menjadi tempat hidup dan sumber makanan Rafflesia.","def_en":"A climbing vine that Rafflesia lives on and takes its food from."},{"term":"Kelopak","def_id":"Bagian bunga yang lebar dan berwarna; Rafflesia punya lima kelopak merah.","def_en":"The wide, colorful part of a flower; Rafflesia has five red petals."},{"term":"Mekar","def_id":"Saat bunga membuka penuh dan terlihat indah.","def_en":"When a flower opens up fully and looks beautiful."},{"term":"Endemik","def_id":"Hanya hidup di satu daerah tertentu dan tidak di tempat lain.","def_en":"Found living only in one certain place and nowhere else."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/385c30fce59c6dae.jpg","caption_id":"Rafflesia mekar penuh di lantai hutan, dengan kuncup lain di belakangnya.","caption_en":"A Rafflesia in full bloom on the forest floor, with another bud behind it.","credit":"Maizal Chaniago","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/df932888e453e9ab.jpg","caption_id":"Lima kelopak merah berbintik putih mengelilingi lubang di tengah bunga.","caption_en":"Five red petals with white spots circle the opening at the center of the flower.","credit":"ma_suska","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5bdda5cecc92b796.jpg","caption_id":"Rafflesia tumbuh di tengah hutan hujan yang lembap dan hijau.","caption_en":"A Rafflesia growing in the middle of a damp, green rainforest.","credit":"SofianRafflesia","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Padma_raksasa"},"ensiklopedia_rumah_gadang":{"id":"ensiklopedia_rumah_gadang","title_id":"Rumah Gadang","title_en":"Rumah Gadang","subtitle_id":"Rumah adat Minangkabau dengan atap melengkung seperti tanduk kerbau!","subtitle_en":"The Minangkabau traditional house with a roof curved like buffalo horns!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Minangkabau, Sumatra Barat","value_en":"Minangkabau, West Sumatra"},{"icon":"home","label_id":"Ciri khas","label_en":"Feature","value_id":"Atap gonjong (tanduk kerbau)","value_en":"Gonjong roof (buffalo horns)"},{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Bahan","label_en":"Material","value_id":"Kayu, ijuk, dan bambu","value_en":"Wood, palm fiber, and bamboo"},{"icon":"festival","label_id":"Fungsi","label_en":"Use","value_id":"Rumah adat keluarga besar","value_en":"Home for the extended family"},{"icon":"diversity_3","label_id":"Pemilik","label_en":"Owner","value_id":"Diwariskan kepada perempuan","value_en":"Passed down to women"}],"sections":[{"icon":"home","h_id":"Apa Itu Rumah Gadang?","h_en":"What Is the Rumah Gadang?","body_id":"Rumah Gadang adalah rumah adat suku Minangkabau di Sumatra Barat, Indonesia. Namanya berarti 'rumah besar'. Yang paling istimewa adalah atapnya yang melengkung runcing ke atas, mirip tanduk kerbau. Karena bentuk atap ini, rumah ini juga disebut Rumah Bagonjong. Sebuah rumah gadang bisa menjadi tempat tinggal satu keluarga besar bersama-sama.","body_en":"The Rumah Gadang is the traditional house of the Minangkabau people in West Sumatra, Indonesia. Its name means 'big house'. The most special part is its roof, which curves up into sharp points like a buffalo's horns. Because of this roof, the house is also called Rumah Bagonjong. One rumah gadang can be home to a whole big family living together."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Rumah Gadang berasal dari Alam Minangkabau di Sumatra Barat. Rumah ini hanya boleh dibangun di sebuah desa adat yang disebut nagari. Di halaman depannya biasanya ada bangunan kecil bernama rangkiang, yaitu lumbung untuk menyimpan padi. Tidak jauh dari rumah, sering dibangun pula sebuah surau sebagai tempat ibadah dan belajar.","body_en":"The Rumah Gadang comes from the Minangkabau homeland in West Sumatra. It may only be built in a traditional village called a nagari. In front of the house there are usually small buildings called rangkiang, which are barns for storing rice. Not far from the house, a small prayer house called a surau is often built for worship and study."},{"icon":"build","h_id":"Bagaimana Dibangun?","h_en":"How Is It Built?","body_id":"Rumah Gadang dibuat dari tiang-tiang kayu yang panjang dan kuat. Dindingnya dari papan kayu, lalu dinding bagian belakang dari bambu. Atapnya dahulu dibuat dari ijuk, yaitu serat hitam dari pohon enau, yang bisa tahan puluhan tahun. Yang hebat, untuk menyambung kayu tidak dipakai paku, melainkan pasak kayu, jadi rumah ini dibangun seperti menyusun balok raksasa.","body_en":"The Rumah Gadang is built from long, strong wooden posts. Its walls are made of wooden planks, while the back wall is made of bamboo. Long ago its roof was made of ijuk, the black fiber from the sugar palm tree, which could last for tens of years. Amazingly, the wood is joined with wooden pegs instead of nails, so the house is built like stacking giant building blocks."},{"icon":"auto_awesome","h_id":"Tahan Gempa & Penuh Ukiran","h_en":"Earthquake-Safe & Full of Carvings","body_id":"Sumatra Barat sering terkena gempa, jadi Rumah Gadang dibuat tahan gempa. Tiangnya tidak ditanam ke tanah, tetapi hanya berdiri di atas batu datar yang lebar. Saat gempa, rumah bergoyang pelan seperti sedang menari, lalu kembali tegak lagi. Dinding depannya juga penuh ukiran indah bermotif bunga, daun, dan akar yang melingkar-lingkar.","body_en":"West Sumatra often has earthquakes, so the Rumah Gadang is built to be earthquake-safe. Its posts are not planted in the ground but simply stand on wide, flat stones. During an earthquake, the house sways gently as if it is dancing, then stands tall again. The front wall is also covered with beautiful carvings of flowers, leaves, and curling vines."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Rumah Milik Perempuan","h_en":"A House That Belongs to Women","body_id":"Di adat Minangkabau, Rumah Gadang diwariskan dari ibu kepada anak perempuan. Jumlah kamar tidur mengikuti jumlah perempuan dewasa yang tinggal di sana. Bagian sayap kanan dan kiri rumah disebut anjung, dipakai untuk tempat pengantin duduk atau saat menobatkan kepala adat. Karena itu rumah ini juga dijuluki Rumah Baanjuang.","body_en":"In Minangkabau custom, the Rumah Gadang is passed down from mother to daughter. The number of bedrooms matches the number of grown-up women living there. The right and left wings of the house are called anjung, used as a seat for a bride or for crowning the customary leader. That is why the house is also nicknamed Rumah Baanjuang."}],"facts":[{"id":"Atap Rumah Gadang melengkung runcing seperti tanduk kerbau.","en":"The Rumah Gadang roof curves into sharp points like buffalo horns."},{"id":"Rumah ini dibangun tanpa paku, hanya memakai pasak dari kayu.","en":"The house is built without nails, using only wooden pegs."},{"id":"Tiangnya berdiri di atas batu, jadi rumah ini tahan gempa.","en":"Its posts stand on stones, making the house earthquake-safe."},{"id":"Dinding depannya penuh ukiran bunga, daun, dan akar.","en":"Its front wall is covered with carvings of flowers, leaves, and vines."},{"id":"Rumah Gadang diwariskan kepada anak perempuan dalam keluarga.","en":"The Rumah Gadang is passed down to the daughters in the family."},{"id":"Di halaman ada rangkiang, lumbung kecil untuk menyimpan padi.","en":"In the yard there is a rangkiang, a small barn for storing rice."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Rumah adat","def_id":"Rumah tradisional khas suatu daerah yang dibangun menurut adat setempat.","def_en":"A traditional house of a region, built according to local custom."},{"term":"Gonjong","def_id":"Puncak atap yang runcing dan melengkung ke atas seperti tanduk kerbau.","def_en":"The roof peak that is pointed and curves upward like a buffalo's horn."},{"term":"Minangkabau","def_id":"Suku asli dari Sumatra Barat yang membangun Rumah Gadang.","def_en":"The native people of West Sumatra who build the Rumah Gadang."},{"term":"Rangkiang","def_id":"Bangunan lumbung kecil di depan rumah untuk menyimpan padi.","def_en":"A small barn building in front of the house for storing rice."},{"term":"Ijuk","def_id":"Serat hitam dari pohon enau yang dahulu dipakai untuk atap.","def_en":"Black fiber from the sugar palm tree once used for roofing."},{"term":"Pasak","def_id":"Paku dari kayu untuk menyambung bagian-bagian rumah.","def_en":"A wooden peg used to join the parts of the house together."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e814415018eb952f.jpg","caption_id":"Rumah Gadang berwarna-warni dengan atap gonjong runcing dan dinding penuh ukiran, terpantul di kolam.","caption_en":"A colorful Rumah Gadang with pointed gonjong roofs and carved walls, reflected in a pond.","credit":"MichaelJLowe","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/98c629ac8c0d3521.jpg","caption_id":"Deretan Rumah Gadang tua di sebuah desa, atapnya menjulang di bawah langit mendung.","caption_en":"A row of old Rumah Gadang in a village, their roofs rising under a cloudy sky.","credit":"RaiyaniM","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/104ecd45492b3bb0.jpg","caption_id":"Foto lama keluarga Minangkabau berpakaian adat di depan Rumah Gadang mereka.","caption_en":"An old photo of a Minangkabau family in traditional dress in front of their Rumah Gadang.","credit":"Christiaan Benjamin Nieuwenhuis","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c904235336bebf18.jpg","caption_id":"Model mini Rumah Gadang memperlihatkan tiang-tiang kayu dan atap ijuk dari dekat.","caption_en":"A small model of a Rumah Gadang shows the wooden posts and palm-fiber roof up close.","credit":"Tropenmuseum","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/622c0db0fbcccceb.jpg","caption_id":"Rumah Gadang dengan atap seng dan dinding tembok, perpaduan gaya lama dan baru.","caption_en":"A Rumah Gadang with a tin roof and plastered wall, mixing old and new styles.","credit":"Alfatajri","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rumah_Gadang"},"ensiklopedia_tarsius":{"id":"ensiklopedia_tarsius","title_id":"Tarsius","title_en":"Tarsier","subtitle_id":"Primata mungil bermata besar dari Sulawesi","subtitle_en":"A tiny big-eyed primate from Sulawesi","data_card":[{"icon":"forest","label_id":"Habitat","label_en":"Habitat","value_id":"Pohon-pohon di hutan yang rimbun","value_en":"Trees in leafy forests"},{"icon":"straighten","label_id":"Ukuran","label_en":"Size","value_id":"Sangat kecil, muat di telapak tangan","value_en":"Very small, fits in your palm"},{"icon":"bug_report","label_id":"Makanan","label_en":"Food","value_id":"Serangga seperti jangkrik & belalang","value_en":"Insects like crickets & grasshoppers"},{"icon":"public","label_id":"Daerah","label_en":"Range","value_id":"Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia","value_en":"The island of Sulawesi, Indonesia"},{"icon":"dark_mode","label_id":"Aktif","label_en":"Active","value_id":"Malam hari (nokturnal)","value_en":"At night (nocturnal)"},{"icon":"category","label_id":"Kelompok","label_en":"Group","value_id":"Primata kecil, famili Tarsiidae","value_en":"Small primate, family Tarsiidae"}],"sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Tarsius?","h_en":"What Is a Tarsier?","body_id":"Tarsius adalah primata yang sangat kecil, kerabat jauh dari monyet dan manusia. Tubuhnya mungil dan bisa muat di telapak tangan orang dewasa. Tarsius termasuk famili Tarsiidae. Walau kecil, tarsius punya mata yang sangat besar dan menggemaskan!","body_en":"The tarsier is a very small primate, a distant relative of monkeys and humans. Its tiny body can fit in an adult's palm. The tarsier belongs to the family Tarsiidae. Even though it is small, the tarsier has huge, adorable eyes!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Tarsius berasal dari pulau-pulau di Asia Tenggara. Semua spesies dalam genus Tarsius ditemukan di Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia. Mereka tinggal di pohon-pohon dalam hutan yang rimbun dan berpegangan erat pada dahan.","body_en":"Tarsiers come from islands in Southeast Asia. Every species in the genus Tarsius is found on the island of Sulawesi, Indonesia. They live up in the trees of leafy forests and cling tightly to the branches."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Mata Raksasa & Tubuh","h_en":"Giant Eyes & Body","body_id":"Mata tarsius sangat besar dibanding tubuhnya, membantunya melihat dalam gelap. Ia punya jari-jari panjang untuk berpegangan erat di dahan pohon. Tarsius juga bisa memutar kepalanya jauh ke belakang untuk melihat sekeliling tanpa menggerakkan tubuhnya.","body_en":"A tarsier's eyes are huge compared to its body, helping it see in the dark. It has long fingers for gripping tree branches tightly. A tarsier can also turn its head far around to look behind itself without moving its body."},{"icon":"dark_mode","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan Malam","h_en":"Food & Night Habits","body_id":"Tarsius aktif di malam hari dan tidur saat siang. Dengan mata besarnya, ia berburu serangga seperti jangkrik dan belalang. Ia melompat dengan lincah dari satu dahan ke dahan lain untuk menangkap makanan.","body_en":"Tarsiers are active at night and sleep during the day. With their big eyes, they hunt insects like crickets and grasshoppers. They leap nimbly from branch to branch to catch their food."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Tarsius adalah hewan istimewa yang hanya hidup di tempat tertentu, jadi kita harus menjaganya. Hutan tempat tinggalnya perlu dilindungi agar tarsius punya rumah yang aman. Dengan menjaga hutan, kita membantu tarsius tetap melompat bahagia.","body_en":"The tarsier is a special animal that lives only in certain places, so we must take care of it. The forests it lives in need protection so the tarsier has a safe home. By protecting forests, we help tarsiers keep leaping happily."}],"facts":[{"id":"Tarsius adalah primata yang sangat kecil, bisa muat di telapak tangan.","en":"The tarsier is a tiny primate that can fit in your palm."},{"id":"Matanya sangat besar untuk melihat dalam gelap.","en":"Its eyes are very big for seeing in the dark."},{"id":"Tarsius aktif di malam hari dan tidur saat siang.","en":"Tarsiers are active at night and sleep during the day."},{"id":"Ia bisa memutar kepalanya jauh ke belakang.","en":"It can turn its head far around to look behind."},{"id":"Jari-jarinya panjang untuk berpegangan erat di dahan.","en":"Its fingers are long for gripping branches tightly."},{"id":"Semua tarsius dari genus ini ditemukan di Pulau Sulawesi.","en":"All tarsiers of this genus are found on the island of Sulawesi."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Primata","def_id":"Kelompok hewan yang mencakup monyet, kera, dan manusia.","def_en":"A group of animals that includes monkeys, apes, and humans."},{"term":"Nokturnal","def_id":"Hewan yang aktif di malam hari dan tidur di siang hari.","def_en":"An animal that is active at night and sleeps during the day."},{"term":"Genus","def_id":"Kelompok hewan atau tumbuhan yang berkerabat dekat.","def_en":"A group of animals or plants that are close relatives."},{"term":"Serangga","def_id":"Hewan kecil berkaki enam seperti jangkrik dan belalang.","def_en":"Small six-legged animals like crickets and grasshoppers."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5cc5af4876e10978.jpg","caption_id":"Tarsius berpegangan erat pada batang pohon dengan jari-jarinya yang panjang.","caption_en":"A tarsier clings tightly to a tree trunk with its long fingers.","credit":"Lip Kee Yap","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/bf0952f593d2b213.jpg","caption_id":"Mata besar dan telinga lebar tarsius membantunya berburu serangga di malam hari.","caption_en":"A tarsier's big eyes and wide ears help it hunt insects at night.","credit":"Meldy Tamenge","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tarsius_%28genus%29"},"kuliner_gado_gado":{"id":"kuliner_gado_gado","title_id":"Gado-gado","title_en":"Gado-gado","subtitle_id":"Salad sayur Indonesia yang disiram bumbu kacang!","subtitle_en":"An Indonesian vegetable salad drizzled with peanut sauce!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Jakarta & Pulau Jawa","value_en":"Jakarta & the island of Java"},{"icon":"eco","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Salad sayur + bumbu kacang","value_en":"Vegetable salad + peanut sauce"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Bahan utama","label_en":"Main ingredients","value_id":"Sayur, tahu, tempe, telur, kentang","value_en":"Vegetables, tofu, tempeh, egg, potato"},{"icon":"local_dining","label_id":"Rasa","label_en":"Taste","value_id":"Gurih, sedikit manis, segar","value_en":"Savory, a little sweet, fresh"},{"icon":"rice_bowl","label_id":"Disajikan","label_en":"Served with","value_id":"Lontong & kerupuk","value_en":"Lontong & crackers"}],"sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Gado-gado?","h_en":"What Is Gado-gado?","body_id":"Gado-gado adalah salad sayur khas Indonesia yang disiram bumbu kacang yang gurih. Isinya bermacam sayuran seperti kangkung, kacang panjang, kol, dan tauge, ditambah tahu, tempe, telur rebus, dan kentang. Karena penuh sayuran, gado-gado sering disebut salad-nya Indonesia. Makanan ini sehat sekaligus mengenyangkan.","body_en":"Gado-gado is an Indonesian vegetable salad covered with a savory peanut sauce. It is filled with many vegetables such as water spinach, long beans, cabbage, and bean sprouts, plus tofu, tempeh, boiled egg, and potato. Because it is full of vegetables, gado-gado is often called Indonesia's salad. This dish is healthy and filling at the same time."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Nama 'gado-gado' berasal dari kata 'gado' atau 'digado', yang dalam bahasa Jawa berarti makan lauk tanpa nasi. Makanan ini berkembang di Pulau Jawa dan menjadi sangat terkenal di Jakarta. Karena bahannya sederhana dan mudah didapat, gado-gado dengan cepat disukai banyak orang di seluruh Indonesia.","body_en":"The name 'gado-gado' comes from the word 'gado' or 'digado', which in Javanese means eating the side dishes without rice. This food grew up on the island of Java and became very famous in Jakarta. Because its ingredients are simple and easy to find, gado-gado quickly became loved by many people across Indonesia."},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","h_id":"Bahan & Cara Membuatnya","h_en":"Ingredients & How It's Made","body_id":"Sayuran seperti tauge, kacang panjang, dan kol direbus sebentar, sementara mentimun dipakai mentah. Sayuran lalu ditata bersama tahu, tempe, telur rebus, dan kentang. Bumbu kacang dibuat dengan menghaluskan kacang tanah goreng, bawang putih, cabai, gula merah, dan air jeruk. Bumbu itu disiramkan di atas sayuran, lalu ditaburi kerupuk atau emping.","body_en":"Vegetables like bean sprouts, long beans, and cabbage are boiled briefly, while cucumber is used raw. The vegetables are then arranged together with tofu, tempeh, boiled egg, and potato. The peanut sauce is made by grinding fried peanuts, garlic, chili, palm sugar, and lime juice. The sauce is poured over the vegetables, then topped with crackers or emping chips."},{"icon":"local_dining","h_id":"Rasa & Cara Menyantapnya","h_en":"Taste & How It's Eaten","body_id":"Gado-gado terasa gurih dan sedikit manis dari bumbu kacang, segar dari sayuran, dan renyah dari kerupuk. Semua isi diaduk rata supaya setiap suapan penuh rasa. Gado-gado bisa dimakan begitu saja, atau bersama lontong dan nasi agar lebih kenyang. Makanan ini enak disantap kapan saja, baik siang maupun malam.","body_en":"Gado-gado tastes savory and a little sweet from the peanut sauce, fresh from the vegetables, and crunchy from the crackers. Everything is mixed together so each bite is full of flavor. Gado-gado can be eaten on its own, or with lontong and rice to be more filling. This dish is tasty any time, whether at lunch or in the evening."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Makanan Saudara Gado-gado","h_en":"Gado-gado's Cousins","body_id":"Gado-gado punya banyak 'saudara' di Indonesia yang juga memakai bumbu kacang. Ada pecel dari Jawa Timur, lotek dan karedok dari Jawa Barat, serta rujak yang lebih manis dan pedas. Setiap daerah punya cara sendiri membuat bumbu kacangnya, sehingga rasanya berbeda-beda walau sama-sama lezat.","body_en":"Gado-gado has many 'cousins' in Indonesia that also use peanut sauce. There is pecel from East Java, lotek and karedok from West Java, and rujak which is sweeter and spicier. Each region has its own way of making the peanut sauce, so the taste is different even though they are all delicious."}],"facts":[{"id":"Nama 'gado-gado' artinya makan lauk saja tanpa nasi.","en":"The name 'gado-gado' means eating just the side dishes without rice."},{"id":"Gado-gado sering disebut sebagai salad khas Indonesia.","en":"Gado-gado is often called Indonesia's very own salad."},{"id":"Bumbu kacangnya dibuat dari kacang tanah yang dihaluskan dengan gula merah dan jeruk.","en":"Its peanut sauce is made from ground peanuts with palm sugar and lime."},{"id":"Di sebagian daerah, bumbu kacang diulek dadakan tepat sebelum disajikan.","en":"In some areas, the peanut sauce is ground fresh right before serving."},{"id":"Gado-gado penuh sayuran, jadi termasuk makanan yang sehat.","en":"Gado-gado is full of vegetables, so it is a healthy dish."},{"id":"Pecel, lotek, dan karedok adalah saudara gado-gado yang juga pakai bumbu kacang.","en":"Pecel, lotek, and karedok are gado-gado's cousins that also use peanut sauce."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Gado-gado","def_id":"Salad sayur Indonesia yang disiram bumbu kacang.","def_en":"An Indonesian vegetable salad drizzled with peanut sauce."},{"term":"Bumbu kacang","def_id":"Saus kental dan gurih dari kacang tanah yang dihaluskan.","def_en":"A thick, savory sauce made from ground peanuts."},{"term":"Tempe","def_id":"Makanan dari kedelai yang difermentasi dan dipadatkan, khas Indonesia.","def_en":"A food made from fermented, pressed soybeans, special to Indonesia."},{"term":"Tahu","def_id":"Makanan lembut berwarna putih yang dibuat dari sari kacang kedelai.","def_en":"A soft white food made from soybean milk."},{"term":"Tauge","def_id":"Tunas muda kacang hijau yang renyah, sering dipakai di gado-gado.","def_en":"Crunchy young sprouts of mung beans, often used in gado-gado."},{"term":"Kerupuk","def_id":"Camilan tipis dan renyah yang digoreng, sebagai pelengkap makanan.","def_en":"A thin, crispy fried snack served alongside food."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5822ba951dec9719.jpg","caption_id":"Sepiring gado-gado dengan bumbu kacang kental, telur rebus, tahu, kacang panjang, dan kerupuk.","caption_en":"A plate of gado-gado with thick peanut sauce, boiled egg, tofu, long beans, and crackers.","credit":"Takeaway","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b808de8db32fec33.jpg","caption_id":"Gado-gado lengkap dengan sayuran segar, mentimun, telur, dan emping yang renyah.","caption_en":"A full gado-gado with fresh vegetables, cucumber, egg, and crispy emping chips.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/825176f2be8f19e1.jpg","caption_id":"Gado-gado dalam wadah besar, dihias telur rebus dan irisan mentimun untuk disantap bersama.","caption_en":"Gado-gado in a big tray, topped with boiled eggs and cucumber slices to share.","credit":"Supardisahabu","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/73d86bcd259f22c6.jpg","caption_id":"Gado-gado diaduk di atas cobek batu agar sayuran tercampur rata dengan bumbu kacang.","caption_en":"Gado-gado being mixed on a stone mortar so the vegetables blend well with the peanut sauce.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gado-gado"},"kuliner_nasi_goreng":{"id":"kuliner_nasi_goreng","title_id":"Nasi Goreng","title_en":"Nasi Goreng (Fried Rice)","subtitle_id":"Nasi yang digoreng dengan kecap manis, makanan favorit sejuta orang Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"Rice fried with sweet soy sauce, a favorite food of millions in Indonesia!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Indonesia (populer se-Asia)","value_en":"Indonesia (popular across Asia)"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Bahan utama","label_en":"Main ingredients","value_id":"Nasi, kecap manis, dan bumbu","value_en":"Rice, sweet soy sauce, and spices"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Rasa","label_en":"Taste","value_id":"Gurih dan sedikit manis","value_en":"Savory with a touch of sweet"},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Makanan utama sehari-hari","value_en":"An everyday main dish"},{"icon":"storefront","label_id":"Dijual","label_en":"Sold by","value_id":"Gerobak & warung pinggir jalan","value_en":"Carts and roadside stalls"}],"sections":[{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Apa Itu Nasi Goreng?","h_en":"What Is Nasi Goreng?","body_id":"Nasi goreng adalah nasi yang digoreng di dalam wajan bersama bumbu-bumbu. Di Indonesia, yang membuatnya istimewa adalah kecap manis, yang memberi warna cokelat dan rasa gurih-manis. Biasanya ditambah telur, sayuran, ayam, atau makanan laut. Nasi goreng adalah salah satu makanan yang paling disukai di Indonesia dan bisa dimakan pagi, siang, atau malam.","body_en":"Nasi goreng is rice fried in a pan together with seasonings. In Indonesia, what makes it special is sweet soy sauce, which gives it a brown color and a sweet-savory taste. It is usually mixed with egg, vegetables, chicken, or seafood. Nasi goreng is one of the most loved foods in Indonesia and can be eaten morning, noon, or night."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Nasi goreng populer di banyak negara Asia, tetapi versi Indonesia punya ciri khas sendiri karena memakai kecap manis. Dahulu nasi goreng sering dibuat dari nasi sisa kemarin agar tidak terbuang. Nasi yang sudah dingin justru lebih enak digoreng karena tidak lembek. Dari kebiasaan hemat inilah lahir banyak sekali ragam nasi goreng.","body_en":"Nasi goreng is popular in many Asian countries, but the Indonesian version has its own character because it uses sweet soy sauce. Long ago, nasi goreng was often made from yesterday's leftover rice so it would not be wasted. Cold rice is actually better for frying because it does not get mushy. From this thrifty habit, many kinds of nasi goreng were born."},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","h_id":"Bagaimana Dimasak?","h_en":"How Is It Cooked?","body_id":"Membuat nasi goreng cukup cepat. Pertama, bawang putih dan bawang merah ditumis sampai harum. Lalu telur diorak-arik, ditambah ayam atau sayuran. Setelah itu nasi dimasukkan dan diaduk cepat dengan kecap manis dan sedikit garam. Semua diaduk di atas api besar sampai panas merata dan wangi. Nasi goreng pun siap dihidangkan selagi hangat.","body_en":"Making nasi goreng is quite fast. First, garlic and shallots are stir-fried until fragrant. Then an egg is scrambled in, with chicken or vegetables added. After that the rice goes in and is stirred quickly with sweet soy sauce and a little salt. Everything is tossed over high heat until it is evenly hot and smells wonderful. The nasi goreng is then ready to serve while warm."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Banyak Sekali Ragamnya","h_en":"So Many Kinds","body_id":"Hampir setiap daerah di Indonesia punya nasi goreng sendiri. Ada nasi goreng kampung, nasi goreng seafood, dan nasi goreng ikan asin. Ada juga nasi goreng Jawa yang gurih, dan di Jawa Timur ada nasi goreng merah yang memakai saus tomat, bukan kecap. Jadi nasi goreng bisa berbeda rasa dan warna di setiap tempat.","body_en":"Almost every region in Indonesia has its own nasi goreng. There is village nasi goreng, seafood nasi goreng, and salted-fish nasi goreng. There is also savory Javanese nasi goreng, and in East Java there is red nasi goreng that uses tomato sauce instead of soy sauce. So nasi goreng can taste and look different in each place."},{"icon":"storefront","h_id":"Jajanan Kaki Lima","h_en":"Street-Food Favorite","body_id":"Di kota-kota Indonesia, penjual nasi goreng sering berkeliling membawa gerobak. Pada malam hari mereka berhenti di jalan dan memasak langsung di tempat. Suara sendok yang dipukulkan ke wajan menjadi tanda bahwa tukang nasi goreng sudah datang. Nasi goreng biasa disajikan dengan telur ceplok, kerupuk, acar, dan irisan timun.","body_en":"In Indonesian cities, nasi goreng sellers often roam around pushing a cart. At night they stop along the street and cook right on the spot. The sound of a spoon tapping the pan is a sign that the nasi goreng seller has arrived. Nasi goreng is usually served with a fried egg, crackers, pickles, and slices of cucumber."}],"facts":[{"id":"Kecap manis adalah bahan yang membuat nasi goreng Indonesia berbeda.","en":"Sweet soy sauce is what makes Indonesian nasi goreng different."},{"id":"Nasi goreng paling enak dibuat dari nasi dingin sisa kemarin.","en":"Nasi goreng tastes best when made from cold, leftover rice."},{"id":"Penjual nasi goreng keliling memukul wajan agar orang tahu mereka datang.","en":"Roaming nasi goreng sellers tap the pan so people know they have arrived."},{"id":"Setiap daerah di Indonesia punya nasi goreng dengan rasa khasnya sendiri.","en":"Each region in Indonesia has nasi goreng with its own special taste."},{"id":"Nasi goreng sering ditemani telur ceplok, kerupuk, dan acar.","en":"Nasi goreng is often paired with a fried egg, crackers, and pickles."},{"id":"Nasi goreng terkenal sampai ke Belanda dan negara-negara tetangga.","en":"Nasi goreng is famous all the way to the Netherlands and neighboring countries."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Nasi goreng","def_id":"Nasi yang digoreng di wajan bersama bumbu, telur, dan lauk.","def_en":"Rice fried in a pan together with seasonings, egg, and toppings."},{"term":"Kecap manis","def_id":"Saus kedelai kental dan manis khas Indonesia, pemberi warna cokelat.","def_en":"A thick, sweet Indonesian soy sauce that gives a brown color."},{"term":"Menumis","def_id":"Menggoreng cepat dengan sedikit minyak sambil diaduk-aduk.","def_en":"To stir-fry quickly with a little oil while tossing the food."},{"term":"Telur ceplok","def_id":"Telur yang digoreng utuh dengan kuning di tengahnya.","def_en":"An egg fried whole with the yolk in the middle."},{"term":"Kerupuk","def_id":"Camilan tipis yang renyah, sering jadi teman makan nasi goreng.","def_en":"A thin, crunchy cracker often eaten alongside nasi goreng."},{"term":"Kaki lima","def_id":"Pedagang makanan di pinggir jalan, sering memakai gerobak.","def_en":"A street food vendor by the roadside, often using a cart."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5801720d4ba9466e.jpg","caption_id":"Nasi goreng merah dengan telur ceplok, kerupuk, ayam suwir, dan kol di atas daun pisang.","caption_en":"Reddish nasi goreng with a fried egg, cracker, shredded chicken, and cabbage on a banana leaf.","credit":"Crisco 1492","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/18f7e40acb18e954.jpg","caption_id":"Nasi goreng kecap berwarna cokelat dengan acar timun dan wortel di piring putih.","caption_en":"Brown soy-sauce nasi goreng with cucumber and carrot pickles on a white plate.","credit":"Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2437def0744ad284.jpg","caption_id":"Nasi goreng dalam mangkuk cokelat, ditaburi gulungan telur dadar yang diiris tipis.","caption_en":"Nasi goreng in a brown bowl, topped with thin slices of rolled omelette.","credit":"Luca Nebuloni","license":"CC BY 2.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nasi_goreng"},"kuliner_rendang":{"id":"kuliner_rendang","title_id":"Rendang","title_en":"Rendang","subtitle_id":"Daging berbumbu Minangkabau yang dimasak berjam-jam sampai empuk dan hitam!","subtitle_en":"Minangkabau spiced meat slow-cooked for hours until tender and dark!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Minangkabau, Sumatra Barat","value_en":"Minangkabau, West Sumatra"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Bahan utama","label_en":"Main ingredients","value_id":"Daging sapi, santan, dan rempah","value_en":"Beef, coconut milk, and spices"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Rasa","label_en":"Taste","value_id":"Gurih, pedas, dan kaya rempah","value_en":"Savory, spicy, and rich with spices"},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Lauk untuk teman nasi","value_en":"A side dish to go with rice"},{"icon":"schedule","label_id":"Lama masak","label_en":"Cooking time","value_id":"Sekitar 4-5 jam","value_en":"About 4-5 hours"}],"sections":[{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Apa Itu Rendang?","h_en":"What Is Rendang?","body_id":"Rendang adalah lauk daging berbumbu yang berasal dari Minangkabau, Sumatra Barat. Daging dimasak pelan-pelan dengan santan dan banyak rempah sampai bumbunya meresap dan berwarna cokelat kehitaman. Rasanya gurih, sedikit pedas, dan sangat kaya. Rendang biasa dimakan bersama nasi hangat dan menjadi salah satu makanan kebanggaan Indonesia.","body_en":"Rendang is a spiced meat dish from Minangkabau in West Sumatra. The meat is cooked slowly with coconut milk and many spices until the flavor soaks in and it turns dark brown. It tastes savory, a little spicy, and very rich. Rendang is usually eaten with warm rice and is one of Indonesia's most beloved foods."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Rendang lahir di tanah Minangkabau. Dahulu orang Minang gemar merantau, yaitu pergi jauh ke daerah lain. Mereka butuh bekal makanan yang awet dan tahan lama. Karena rendang dimasak sampai kering, ia bisa bertahan berminggu-minggu tanpa basi. Maka rendang menjadi bekal sempurna untuk perjalanan jauh, dan kini terkenal sampai ke luar negeri.","body_en":"Rendang was born in the Minangkabau land. Long ago the Minang people loved to merantau, which means to travel far to other regions. They needed food supplies that would last a long time. Because rendang is cooked until dry, it can keep for weeks without spoiling. So rendang became the perfect food to carry on long journeys, and now it is famous even in other countries."},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","h_id":"Bagaimana Dimasak?","h_en":"How Is It Cooked?","body_id":"Memasak rendang butuh kesabaran. Mula-mula santan dan bumbu dimasak bersama daging sampai mendidih, warnanya masih kuning. Lalu api dikecilkan dan terus diaduk pelan-pelan. Lama-kelamaan santan mengental menjadi cokelat keemasan, disebut kalio. Kalau diteruskan sampai kering dan hitam, barulah jadi rendang. Semua proses ini bisa memakan waktu empat sampai lima jam!","body_en":"Cooking rendang takes patience. First the coconut milk and spices are cooked with the meat until it boils, and it is still yellow. Then the heat is lowered and it is stirred slowly. Little by little the coconut milk thickens into golden brown, called kalio. If you keep going until it is dry and dark, only then does it become rendang. All of this can take four to five hours!"},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Bumbu Ajaib Rendang","h_en":"Rendang's Magic Spices","body_id":"Rendang memakai banyak rempah seperti cabai, serai, lengkuas, kunyit, jahe, bawang putih, dan bawang merah. Bumbu-bumbu ini bukan hanya membuat rasanya enak, tetapi juga bekerja seperti pengawet alami yang melawan kuman. Itulah rahasianya kenapa rendang bisa tahan lama. Karena gizinya terjaga, rendang sering dikirim sebagai bantuan makanan untuk korban bencana.","body_en":"Rendang uses many spices such as chili, lemongrass, galangal, turmeric, ginger, garlic, and shallots. These spices not only make it delicious but also work like a natural preserver that fights germs. That is the secret of why rendang lasts so long. Because it stays nutritious, rendang is often sent as food aid for disaster victims."},{"icon":"emoji_events","h_id":"Rendang Juara Dunia","h_en":"World-Champion Rendang","body_id":"Pada tahun 2011, rendang dipilih sebagai makanan terlezat nomor satu di dunia oleh CNN International. Pada tahun 2018, rendang resmi menjadi salah satu dari lima makanan nasional Indonesia. Bagi masyarakat Minangkabau, rendang juga punya makna khusus dan selalu hadir di acara adat, pesta, dan saat menyambut tamu istimewa.","body_en":"In 2011, rendang was chosen as the number one most delicious food in the world by CNN International. In 2018, rendang officially became one of Indonesia's five national dishes. For the Minangkabau people, rendang also has a special meaning and is always served at traditional ceremonies, feasts, and when welcoming honored guests."}],"facts":[{"id":"Pada 2011, rendang dinobatkan sebagai makanan terlezat di dunia oleh CNN.","en":"In 2011, rendang was named the most delicious food in the world by CNN."},{"id":"Rendang dimasak sangat lama, sekitar empat sampai lima jam.","en":"Rendang is cooked for a very long time, about four to five hours."},{"id":"Karena dimasak sampai kering, rendang bisa tahan berminggu-minggu.","en":"Because it is cooked until dry, rendang can last for weeks."},{"id":"Rempah dalam rendang bekerja seperti pengawet alami melawan kuman.","en":"The spices in rendang work like a natural preserver against germs."},{"id":"Dahulu rendang dibuat dari daging rusa sebelum memakai daging sapi.","en":"Long ago rendang was made from deer meat before using beef."},{"id":"Rendang adalah salah satu dari lima makanan nasional Indonesia.","en":"Rendang is one of Indonesia's five national dishes."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Rendang","def_id":"Lauk daging Minangkabau yang dimasak lama dengan santan dan rempah.","def_en":"A Minangkabau meat dish cooked slowly with coconut milk and spices."},{"term":"Santan","def_id":"Cairan putih dari kelapa parut yang membuat masakan gurih.","def_en":"The white liquid from grated coconut that makes food creamy and savory."},{"term":"Rempah","def_id":"Bumbu dari tumbuhan seperti cabai, jahe, dan kunyit yang menambah rasa.","def_en":"Seasonings from plants such as chili, ginger, and turmeric that add flavor."},{"term":"Kalio","def_id":"Rendang setengah jadi yang masih basah dan berwarna cokelat keemasan.","def_en":"Half-cooked rendang that is still moist and golden brown."},{"term":"Merantau","def_id":"Pergi jauh meninggalkan kampung halaman, kebiasaan orang Minang.","def_en":"To travel far away from one's home village, a Minangkabau custom."},{"term":"Lauk","def_id":"Makanan pendamping yang dimakan bersama nasi.","def_en":"A side dish eaten together with rice."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2d2d80ccc29f7c5b.jpg","caption_id":"Rendang sapi yang sudah matang, berwarna cokelat hitam, disajikan dengan ketupat.","caption_en":"Finished beef rendang, dark brown in color, served with woven rice cakes.","credit":"Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9994fb623f08aa04.jpg","caption_id":"Ibu-ibu berpakaian adat Minang memasak rendang dalam kuali besar di depan Rumah Gadang.","caption_en":"Women in Minangkabau dress cook rendang in big pots in front of a Rumah Gadang.","credit":"Government of West Sumatra Province","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e877670c14e66af2.jpg","caption_id":"Tahap awal: santan kuning mendidih bersama daging dan bumbu di dalam kuali.","caption_en":"Early stage: yellow coconut milk boils together with the meat and spices in the pan.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b3dfb3a7a76ee4a9.jpg","caption_id":"Tahap tengah: santan mulai mengental dan berwarna oranye kecokelatan, disebut kalio.","caption_en":"Middle stage: the coconut milk thickens and turns orange-brown, called kalio.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/04d8bc802340047b.jpg","caption_id":"Tahap akhir: bumbu mengering dan menghitam, daging pun siap menjadi rendang.","caption_en":"Final stage: the spices dry and darken, and the meat is ready to become rendang.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rendang"},"kuliner_sate":{"id":"kuliner_sate","title_id":"Sate","title_en":"Satay","subtitle_id":"Daging ditusuk dan dibakar di atas bara, disiram bumbu kacang!","subtitle_en":"Skewered meat grilled over coals, drizzled with peanut sauce!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Jawa, Indonesia (Ponorogo)","value_en":"Java, Indonesia (Ponorogo)"},{"icon":"kebab_dining","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Daging tusuk yang dibakar","value_en":"Grilled meat on skewers"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Bahan utama","label_en":"Main ingredients","value_id":"Ayam, kambing, atau sapi","value_en":"Chicken, goat, or beef"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Rasa","label_en":"Taste","value_id":"Gurih, manis, sedikit berasap","value_en":"Savory, sweet, a little smoky"},{"icon":"rice_bowl","label_id":"Disajikan","label_en":"Served with","value_id":"Bumbu kacang, nasi atau lontong","value_en":"Peanut sauce, rice or lontong"}],"sections":[{"icon":"kebab_dining","h_id":"Apa Itu Sate?","h_en":"What Is Satay?","body_id":"Sate adalah makanan dari potongan daging kecil yang ditusuk dengan lidi atau tusuk bambu, lalu dibakar di atas bara arang sampai matang dan harum. Setelah matang, sate biasanya disiram bumbu kacang atau kecap manis. Sate sangat terkenal di seluruh Indonesia dan dianggap salah satu masakan nasional kita.","body_en":"Satay is a food made from small pieces of meat threaded onto thin sticks or bamboo skewers, then grilled over hot charcoal until cooked and fragrant. Once done, satay is usually drizzled with peanut sauce or sweet soy sauce. Satay is famous all over Indonesia and is seen as one of our national dishes."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Sate berasal dari Pulau Jawa, Indonesia. Banyak orang percaya kota asalnya adalah Ponorogo di Jawa Timur. Dari Jawa, sate menyebar ke seluruh Nusantara, lalu ke negara tetangga seperti Malaysia, Singapura, dan Thailand. Sate bahkan terkenal sampai ke Belanda. Setiap daerah membuat sate dengan resep khasnya sendiri.","body_en":"Satay comes from the island of Java, Indonesia. Many people believe its home town is Ponorogo in East Java. From Java, satay spread across the whole archipelago, then to neighboring countries like Malaysia, Singapore, and Thailand. Satay even became famous as far away as the Netherlands. Each region makes satay with its own special recipe."},{"icon":"local_fire_department","h_id":"Bahan & Cara Membuatnya","h_en":"Ingredients & How It's Made","body_id":"Daging untuk sate bisa berupa ayam, kambing, sapi, atau yang lain. Daging dipotong kecil, diberi bumbu seperti kunyit atau kecap manis, lalu ditusuk satu per satu. Tusukan daging itu dibakar di atas arang sambil dikipas, supaya matang merata dan keluar bau harum yang menggoda. Asap dari bara inilah yang membuat sate terasa istimewa.","body_en":"The meat for satay can be chicken, goat, beef, or others. The meat is cut into small pieces, seasoned with spices like turmeric or sweet soy sauce, then threaded onto skewers one by one. The skewers are grilled over charcoal while being fanned, so they cook evenly and give off a tempting aroma. The smoke from the coals is what makes satay taste so special."},{"icon":"rice_bowl","h_id":"Rasa & Cara Menyantapnya","h_en":"Taste & How It's Eaten","body_id":"Sate terasa gurih, sedikit manis, dan harum oleh asap arang. Paling enak disantap saat masih hangat, dengan siraman bumbu kacang yang kental atau kecap manis. Biasanya sate dimakan bersama nasi hangat atau lontong, ditambah irisan bawang merah, mentimun, dan kadang sambal. Kita bisa menemukan sate dari gerobak keliling sampai restoran besar.","body_en":"Satay tastes savory, a little sweet, and smells wonderful from the charcoal smoke. It is best enjoyed while still warm, with thick peanut sauce or sweet soy sauce poured over it. Satay is usually eaten with warm rice or lontong (rice cake), plus slices of shallot, cucumber, and sometimes chili sauce. You can find satay everywhere, from pushcart sellers to big restaurants."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Aneka Sate Nusantara","h_en":"Many Kinds of Satay","body_id":"Indonesia punya koleksi jenis sate paling banyak di dunia! Ada Sate Ponorogo dengan daging ayam yang dipotong memanjang, Sate Madura dengan bumbu kacang manis, Sate Padang dengan kuah kuning kental, dan Sate Lilit dari Bali yang dililitkan pada batang serai. Setiap sate punya rasa dan cerita yang berbeda.","body_en":"Indonesia has the biggest collection of satay types in the world! There is Satay Ponorogo with long-sliced chicken, Satay Madura with sweet peanut sauce, Satay Padang with a thick yellow gravy, and Satay Lilit from Bali that is wrapped around lemongrass sticks. Each satay has its own flavor and story."}],"facts":[{"id":"Sate dipilih sebagai peringkat ke-14 dalam daftar '50 Makanan Terlezat di Dunia' versi CNN.","en":"Satay was ranked 14th on CNN's list of the 'World's 50 Most Delicious Foods'."},{"id":"Hampir semua jenis daging bisa dibuat sate, bahkan udang dan telur puyuh!","en":"Almost any kind of meat can be made into satay, even shrimp and quail eggs!"},{"id":"Indonesia punya jenis sate paling banyak di dunia, lebih dari 50 macam.","en":"Indonesia has the most types of satay in the world, more than 50 kinds."},{"id":"Pada Sate Ponorogo, setiap tusuk berisi satu potong daging ayam yang diiris panjang.","en":"In Satay Ponorogo, each skewer holds one piece of chicken sliced long."},{"id":"Kantor gubernur di Bandung dijuluki 'Gedung Sate' karena hiasan atapnya mirip tusuk sate.","en":"A government building in Bandung is nicknamed 'Gedung Sate' because its roof ornament looks like a satay skewer."},{"id":"Banyak makanan di dunia mirip sate, seperti yakitori dari Jepang dan kebab dari Turki.","en":"Many foods around the world are like satay, such as yakitori from Japan and kebab from Turkey."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Sate","def_id":"Potongan daging yang ditusuk dan dibakar di atas bara arang.","def_en":"Pieces of meat threaded on a skewer and grilled over charcoal."},{"term":"Tusuk sate","def_id":"Lidi atau batang bambu tipis tempat daging ditusuk.","def_en":"A thin stick or bamboo skewer that the meat is threaded onto."},{"term":"Bumbu kacang","def_id":"Saus kental dan gurih yang dibuat dari kacang tanah yang dihaluskan.","def_en":"A thick, savory sauce made from ground peanuts."},{"term":"Bara arang","def_id":"Potongan arang yang membara dan panas, dipakai untuk membakar sate.","def_en":"Glowing, hot pieces of charcoal used to grill the satay."},{"term":"Lontong","def_id":"Nasi yang dipadatkan dan dibungkus daun, dipotong untuk teman makan sate.","def_en":"Rice pressed and wrapped in leaves, sliced to eat alongside satay."},{"term":"Kecap manis","def_id":"Saus kedelai berwarna cokelat tua yang manis dan kental, khas Indonesia.","def_en":"A dark, sweet, thick soybean sauce that is special to Indonesia."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/ab984e0f411917f6.jpg","caption_id":"Sate ayam Ponorogo di atas bumbu kacang, dengan irisan bawang merah dan jeruk nipis.","caption_en":"Ponorogo chicken satay over peanut sauce, with sliced shallots and lime.","credit":"Gunawan Kartapranata","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sate"},"kuliner_soto_nusantara":{"id":"kuliner_soto_nusantara","title_id":"Soto Nusantara","title_en":"Soto of the Archipelago","subtitle_id":"Sup berkuah hangat dengan ratusan resep dari seluruh Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"A warm soupy dish with hundreds of recipes from all over Indonesia!","data_card":[{"icon":"public","label_id":"Asal","label_en":"Origin","value_id":"Pesisir utara Jawa Tengah","value_en":"North coast of Central Java"},{"icon":"soup_kitchen","label_id":"Jenis","label_en":"Type","value_id":"Sup berkuah dari kaldu","value_en":"A soup made from broth"},{"icon":"restaurant","label_id":"Bahan utama","label_en":"Main ingredients","value_id":"Kaldu daging ayam atau sapi & sayur","value_en":"Chicken or beef broth & vegetables"},{"icon":"local_fire_department","label_id":"Rasa","label_en":"Taste","value_id":"Gurih, hangat, harum rempah","value_en":"Savory, warm, fragrant with spices"},{"icon":"rice_bowl","label_id":"Disajikan","label_en":"Served with","value_id":"Nasi, lontong, atau bihun","value_en":"Rice, lontong, or rice vermicelli"}],"sections":[{"icon":"soup_kitchen","h_id":"Apa Itu Soto?","h_en":"What Is Soto?","body_id":"Soto adalah makanan berkuah khas Indonesia yang mirip sup. Kuahnya dibuat dari kaldu daging yang dimasak bersama rempah-rempah sampai harum, lalu diisi potongan daging dan sayuran. Daging yang paling sering dipakai adalah ayam dan sapi. Soto disajikan hangat dan cocok dimakan kapan saja, terutama saat cuaca dingin.","body_en":"Soto is an Indonesian soupy dish that is like a soup. Its broth is made from meat stock cooked with spices until fragrant, then filled with pieces of meat and vegetables. The meats most often used are chicken and beef. Soto is served warm and is great to eat any time, especially when the weather is cool."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Dari Mana Asalnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Come From?","body_id":"Soto banyak ditemukan pertama kali di kota-kota pelabuhan di pesisir utara Jawa Tengah, seperti Tegal, Pekalongan, Semarang, dan Kudus. Karena ramai oleh pedagang dari berbagai bangsa, resep soto pun ikut menyebar dan berubah-ubah. Dari sana, soto berkembang ke seluruh Nusantara dan setiap daerah membuat versinya sendiri.","body_en":"Soto was first found in port cities on the north coast of Central Java, such as Tegal, Pekalongan, Semarang, and Kudus. Because these cities were busy with traders from many nations, soto recipes spread and changed along the way. From there, soto grew across the whole archipelago and each region made its own version."},{"icon":"local_fire_department","h_id":"Bahan & Cara Membuatnya","h_en":"Ingredients & How It's Made","body_id":"Untuk membuat soto, daging direbus lama hingga menghasilkan kaldu yang gurih. Bumbu seperti kunyit, jahe, serai, bawang putih, dan bawang merah dihaluskan, ditumis, lalu dimasukkan ke dalam kuah. Daging yang sudah empuk disuwir atau dipotong kecil. Saat disajikan, soto dituang di atas nasi atau bihun dan ditaburi bawang goreng serta seledri.","body_en":"To make soto, the meat is boiled for a long time to create a savory broth. Spices like turmeric, ginger, lemongrass, garlic, and shallots are ground, fried, then added to the broth. The tender meat is shredded or cut small. When served, soto is poured over rice or vermicelli and topped with fried shallots and celery."},{"icon":"rice_bowl","h_id":"Rasa & Cara Menyantapnya","h_en":"Taste & How It's Eaten","body_id":"Soto terasa gurih dan hangat, dengan aroma rempah yang harum. Banyak orang menambahkan perasan jeruk nipis, sambal, dan kecap supaya rasanya makin segar dan sesuai selera. Soto biasa dimakan bersama nasi, lontong, atau bihun, ditambah pelengkap seperti kerupuk, perkedel, telur, dan emping yang renyah.","body_en":"Soto tastes savory and warm, with a fragrant smell of spices. Many people add a squeeze of lime, chili sauce, and sweet soy sauce to make it fresher and just right for their taste. Soto is usually eaten with rice, lontong, or vermicelli, plus sides like crackers, potato patties, egg, and crispy emping chips."},{"icon":"diversity_3","h_id":"Soto dari Berbagai Daerah","h_en":"Soto from Many Regions","body_id":"Hampir setiap daerah di Indonesia punya soto sendiri! Soto Ayam Lamongan berkuah kuning dan ditaburi koya, Soto Betawi dari Jakarta memakai santan atau susu sehingga gurih, Soto Banjar dari Kalimantan harum oleh kayu manis dan cengkih, sedangkan Coto Makassar dari Sulawesi berkuah kental dan kaya rempah. Karena begitu banyak ragamnya, soto disebut Soto Nusantara.","body_en":"Almost every region in Indonesia has its own soto! Soto Ayam Lamongan has a yellow broth sprinkled with koya, Soto Betawi from Jakarta uses coconut milk or dairy to make it creamy, Soto Banjar from Kalimantan is fragrant with cinnamon and cloves, while Coto Makassar from Sulawesi has a thick, spice-rich broth. Because there are so many kinds, soto is called Soto Nusantara, the soto of the archipelago."}],"facts":[{"id":"Hampir setiap kota di Indonesia punya jenis soto khasnya sendiri.","en":"Almost every city in Indonesia has its own special kind of soto."},{"id":"Soto punya banyak nama daerah, seperti sroto, sauto, tauto, dan coto.","en":"Soto has many local names, such as sroto, sauto, tauto, and coto."},{"id":"Soto Betawi dibuat gurih dengan santan atau susu.","en":"Soto Betawi is made creamy with coconut milk or dairy."},{"id":"Warna kuning pada banyak soto berasal dari kunyit.","en":"The yellow color in many sotos comes from turmeric."},{"id":"Koya, taburan dari kerupuk dan bawang putih, membuat Soto Lamongan makin gurih.","en":"Koya, a topping of crushed crackers and garlic, makes Soto Lamongan even tastier."},{"id":"Soto paling enak disantap selagi hangat, apalagi saat hujan.","en":"Soto is best enjoyed while warm, especially when it rains."}],"glossary":[{"term":"Soto","def_id":"Makanan berkuah khas Indonesia yang dibuat dari kaldu daging dan rempah.","def_en":"An Indonesian soupy dish made from meat broth and spices."},{"term":"Kaldu","def_id":"Air rebusan daging atau tulang yang gurih, menjadi dasar kuah soto.","def_en":"The savory liquid from boiling meat or bones, used as the base of soto broth."},{"term":"Kunyit","def_id":"Rempah berwarna kuning yang membuat kuah soto berwarna dan harum.","def_en":"A yellow spice that gives soto broth its color and aroma."},{"term":"Bawang goreng","def_id":"Irisan bawang merah yang digoreng renyah dan ditaburkan di atas soto.","def_en":"Slices of shallot fried until crispy and sprinkled on top of soto."},{"term":"Koya","def_id":"Taburan gurih dari kerupuk dan bawang putih yang dihaluskan.","def_en":"A savory topping of crackers and garlic ground together."},{"term":"Lontong","def_id":"Nasi yang dipadatkan dan dibungkus daun, sering dimakan dengan soto.","def_en":"Rice pressed and wrapped in leaves, often eaten with soto."}],"gallery":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/068a2245a5a30674.jpg","caption_id":"Soto ayam berkuah kuning dengan suwiran ayam, bawang goreng, emping, dan irisan tomat.","caption_en":"Chicken soto with a yellow broth, shredded chicken, fried shallots, emping chips, and sliced tomato.","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a2dbe61a12196d14.jpg","caption_id":"Soto Banjar dari Kalimantan dengan perasan jeruk nipis, suwiran ayam, dan perkedel.","caption_en":"Soto Banjar from Kalimantan with a squeeze of lime, shredded chicken, and a potato patty.","credit":"Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soto"}};
